:15','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('764797b2-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Peaceful Valley Orchards','Located in Pittstown, a town known for fruit production for over one hundred years, Peaceful Valley Orchards is representative of one of America’s oldest traditions. Peaceful Valley Orchards boasts of a beautiful location as well as great Jersey Fresh fruits and vegetables. We grow a variety of our own produce, including asparagus, lettuce, tomatoes, squash, apples, peaches, pears and sweet corn. Peaceful Valley Orchards grows over 25 varieties of apples, over 5 varieties of pears, plums, and of course Jersey peaches. Not only do we carry Jersey Fresh produce, but we also bake our own pies, loaf cakes, cookies, and bread. We also have a large variety of local pork products. During the summer months, our farm is filled with great activities, such as our Strawberry Festival, cut your own flowers and Farm Camp for the kids. In September we start booking our Fall School Tours and pick your apples and pumpkins begin. In October, Peaceful Valley Orchards hosts our Fall Festival, complete with pumpkin and apple picking, hayrides, a strawbale maze, and pig roast. For Thanksgiving, we carry farm-raised, all natural turkeys perfect for your holiday meal.','(908)730-7748','fruit@peacefulvalleyorchards.com','Meredith Compton','','May-Oct. 31st - Monday thru Friday 9-6:30 Saturday and Sunday 9-5:30 Nov. 1st - Thanksgiving: We will only be open on the weekends 9-5:30','','http://www.peacefulvalleyorchards.com/','','150 Pittstown Road','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed1ec7f1-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','08867','Hay Rides, Farm Tours, Petting Zoo, Others:straw bale maze','School Tours, Private Parties, Host Fundraisers/Events','Sweet Corn Celebration:(8/14/2011 - 8/14/2011)','2012-02-29 15:17:15','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('764b80f6-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Peterson Farm','The Peterson Farm is a diversified familly farm in the heart of Hunterdon County. On 150 acres of preserved land, John and Matt raise hay, grain, sweet corn, and Black Angus beef. Everyone helps with Pick-Your-Own Strawberries in June and with Christmas Trees and Wreaths in December. 4-H is big around here with milking goats and shooting sports.','908.782.0707','info@PetersonFarm.net','John A. Peterson, Jr.','','Open Daily during picking season. Visit our website for the latest information. ','','http://www.petersonfarm.net/','','438 Quakertown Road','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed1ec7f1-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','08822 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:15','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('764fa155-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Abenaki Acres Farm','Abenaki Acres Farm is an alpaca fleece and breeding production farm. We have over 90 alpacas of all colors and a couple of llamas too. We provide tours for individuals interested in seeing a production farm in operation; to learn more about alpacas and the role they play in fiber production. Alpaca fleece is a sought after fiber by anyone looking to create a luxurious garments with exceptional softness. It is a fiber that can be spun right after shearing without any washing and chemical treatments and the resulting garment can be worn next to your skin unlike some of the \"rougher\" fibers. We have an on-site farm store with raw fleece, roving, yarns, and garments from our own herd and supplemented by alpaca products from other companies. We also visit schools with our alpacas to educate kids on this type of livestock as well as have scout troops and others visit the farm as part of their programs. We also have seminars - visit www.AbenakiAcres.com/events.asp for a list of events.','908-782-0025','Alpacas@AbenakiAcres.com'