weet corn, peppers, eggplant to tomatoes and everything in between. The autumn which is a very busy time at the farm provides a pick your own pumpkin patch, corn maze with a hayride and educational school tours. There are approximately 45 different varieties of pumpkins, gourds and squash. The market also has an Oz Room and people can tour the gourd room and school tour room. Cider and all the fall crops are for sale. The winter time brings Christmas trees and wreaths which range from original designs to the traditional to custom made orders.','(732) 583-6780','wememail@verizon.net','Peggy O\'Connell','','9:00am - 6:00PM 7 days a week','','','','191 State Route 34','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed1ec7f1-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','07747','Corn Maze, Hay Rides, Petting Zoo','School Tours, Private Parties','','2012-02-29 15:17:16','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('76c42a9b-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Earth Friendly Organic Farm','Earth Friendly Organic Farm was built in 1984 as a solar passive contemporary home which utilizes the warm temperatures from the greenhouses to heat the premises. Over 1200 blueberry bushes surround the 8 acre farm. U-Pickers visit non-stop throughout the summer months for organic blueberries, blackberries, raspberries, garden vegetables and persimmons in the fall. Free range chickens provide fresh eggs daily. Earth Friendly is also a bed and breakfast serving the local community. Three guest rooms are light, airy, have private or adjoining baths and scenic views. The house is comfortable, quiet and has a \"home away from home\" feeling. Also available are yoga and tai chi workshops for those who want to de-stress and renew at one day or weekend R&R retreats.','(609) 259-9744 ','roz@earthfriendlyorganicfarm.com','Rosalind Ressner','','U-Pickers Welcome - Blueberries (June 15th through August 30th) - Blackberries (August) - Raspberries (September) Vegetables (July/August) - Persimmons (October) School Tours (available throughout month of July)','','http://www.earthfriendlyorganicfarm.com/','','17 Olde Noah Hunt Rd.','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed1ec7f1-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','08510','Others:Tai Chi and Yoga - Private/Group Classes - One Day or Weekend Retreats','School Tours, Others:Blueberry Jam Session and Luncheon - Wednesday, July 11th','','2012-02-29 15:17:16','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('76c8427e-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Rifkin Farms','We are located on Route 527 in Manalapan, N.J. We are a bedding plant grower with all types of flowers and vegetable plants. We carry all types of hanging baskets and container gardening. We also carry Proven Winners, annuals and some perrinials. When we open our farm market, we carry the freshest of homegrown produce,. We are growers of sweet corn , tomatoes, peppers, eggplant and other vegetables that are picked daily. We also carry a line of breads and rolls, pies, salad dressings and many other items. In the fall we have a beautiful assortment of Mums, pumpkins and gourds. We also carry a variety of all different squashes. Butternut and acorn, turks turbins and gooseneck gourds to name a few. A visit to our farm will surely be a pleasant experience!','732-462-5694','hcorn13@aol.com','Hal Rifkin','','9:00 to 5:00p.m. 7 days a week . Open May 1st till Nov.1st.','','http://www.rifkinfarms.com/','','98 Smithburg Road','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed1ec7f1-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','07726','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:16','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('76cd6af1-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Battleview Orchards','Battleview Orchards was established in 1908 and it is presently farmed by the 4th generation of the Applegate Family. The farm includes a Country Store and 120 acres of fruit that is marketed through our Pick Your Own operation and the store. Country Store features a wide variety of fruits & vegetables including Jersey Fresh Produce when in season, Fresh Baked Pies, Breads, Pastries, Cookies and our famous Apple Cider Donuts that are made fresh daily. We press our own fresh Apple Cider and Hot Apple Cider samples are available in the winter months. Fruit and Gift Baskets are available with a wide variety of gourmet items. Battleview offers Pick your Own Strawberries, Sour Cherries, Peaches, Nectarines, Apples and Pumpkins. In the Fall, Hayrides are offered on the weekends. School/Group Tours are offered during the Fall season.','(732) 462-0756 ','','Lisa Applegate','','Country Store--OPEN ALL YEAR 9am-6pm(April through December) 9am - 5pm (Jan. - Mar.) Pick Your Own--Hours vary according to season and crop availability. Call for picking hours.','','http://www.battlevieworchards.com/','','91 Wemrock Rd.','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed1ec7f1-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','07728 ','Hay Rides','School Tours','','2012-02-29 15:17:16','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('76d2a30f-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Patterson Greenhouses','Patterson Greenhouses is a family owned and operated farm dating back to the 1800\'s. Its mainstay has been dairy cows for many of these years and potatoes before that, but the last decade and a half brought about many changes. The dairy cows were sold in 1987 and we soon switched our focus to mums and pumpkins. With the selling of the cows, our large inventory of hay and straw could be sold instead of consumed. This aspect of our business has not changed over the years. In 1989, we ventured into another new area of farming, the greenhouse industry. Starting with a single greenhouse, a couple small fields, and a limited amount of knowledge, the road to becoming a successful business seemed rough. However, we did not feel that our goal was unattainable. Alan Patterson went to college to study horticulture while Don (aka Dad Patterson) learned from other farmers in the area and old fashioned trial and error. It did not take long to get a good grasp in the growing of bedding plants and mums, but it did take a lot of hard work. Every day of the week, including Sunday (unless it\'s the summer and there are waves at the beach), Don and Alan wake up before the sun rises to work in the fields or greenhouses. Also, there are very few nights when the two of them are done with their work before the sun sets. After deciding that we should not limit ourselves to only summer and fall products, we began to grow Christmas trees and other winter goods such as wreathes and grave blankets. It took a considerable amount of time before the Christmas trees were ready for sale, but in 1997 our first trees were sold. The next year, we sold twice as many as the year before and our trees have never looked better. The retail aspects of the business have always been handled by Kate (aka Mom Patterson) and Sharon (known to most by her uncanny ability to run across rocks with bare feet on a daily basis). Together, they have worked hard to make sure that the customer always gets what they want. The other Pattersons, who you may have seen on occasion, are Cindy, who works in New York City, Rich, who is a graphic designer and can create web pages, and Dave, who is a high school math teacher. Over the years, Patterson Greenhouses has grown to become a very respectable business with a large inventory and caring employees. We hope to continue to grow to meet the needs of our customers as the years go on. ','(732) 431-5271','pattersonghs@aol.com','Alan  Patterson','','Our hours are from 8:00 am until 7:00 pm, unless darkness falls before 7:00 pm. In the fall/winter months we close at dark, this includes Christmas tree season when we close at 5:00 pm.','','http://www.pattersongreenhouses.com/','','636 Adelphia Rd','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed1ec7f1-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','07728','Others:Choose and Cut Christmas Trees','','','2012-02-29 15:17:16','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('76d702b0-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Kauffman Farms','Small family operated farm. April opens with pansys. Mothers Day weekend open with bedding plants, hanging baskets, and vegatable plants. Home grown and local vegatables and fruits available as the season provides.','(732) 620-3186','kauffmanfarms@msn.com','Doug & Debi Kauffman','','april weekends only, may - oct mon- sat 9 am - 6 pm, Sunday 10am-5pm Nov Closed, Dec weekends 10 am - 4 pm, weekdays by appointment only. Closed Dec 25 though March.','','','','93 Squankum-Yellowbrook Rd.','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed1ec7f1-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','07727 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:16','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('76da9252-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','A. Casola Farms','Fourth generation farm. Large retail/wholesale nursery, greenhouses and all ancillary items. Specializing in being the original Pick-Your -Own Pumpkin Farm.Fall season features hayrides,haunted hayrides, jersey devil hunt, pony rides, petting zoo, corn maze, pick your own pumpkin, bakery, roast corn, homemade pies and donuts, food, halloween shop, face painting, picnic area, birthday parties, antique tractor museum, class trips, banjo player','(732) 332-1533','funonourfarm@aol.com','Kim Casola','','Open Mid march through December. 7 days a week 7am-7pm','','http://www.casolafarms.com/','','178 State Route 34','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed1ec7f1-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','07733','Corn Maze, Hay Rides, Farm Tours, Petting Zoo, Visual Zoo (non-petting), Haunted House/Barn','School Tours, Pr