lity is also used for Birthday Parties, Scout outings, as well as for fund-raising events for charities. The store is currently operated by Charles and Carolyn Granatell of West Milford and is located at 1750 Union Valley Road. More information: www.efarmstore.com ','973-728-6030','info@efarmstore.com','Carolyn Granatell','','We open at 10 am everyday. Closing hours vary with seasons - please call for current hours (973-728-6030).','','http://www.efarmstore.com/','','1750 Union Valley Road','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed1ec7f1-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','07480 ','Hay Rides, Farm Tours, Petting Zoo','School Tours, Private Parties, Corporate Events, Host Fundraisers/Events, Others:Great area for outdoor functions! Lots of room for tables, band, catering, etc.','','2012-02-29 15:17:17','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('77544610-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Ploch\'s Farm','Ploch\'s Farm has been a family run 15-acre farm since 1867. It is the last remaining working farm in the City of Clifton and is the second largest farm in the County of Passaic. Fruit and vegetables are picked daily in order to ensure freshness and quality. Ploch\'s Farm produce includes: tomatoes, corn, peaches, plums, beets, swiss chard, arugula, dandelion, lettuce, romaine, peppers, eggplant, cucumbers, onions, potatoes, garlic, and parsley. As Autumn begins so do extra-large pumpkins, gourds, butternut squash, acorn squash, Mums, apples, and pears. Ploch\'s farm also participates in Pick-Your-Own Pumpkins and Corn Mazes during the Autumn season. (Please call or email for appropriate dates and times.) In addition to produce, Ploch\'s Farm also sells, Gelotti Ice Cream and Italian Ices, homemade breads and pies, fresh-cut flowers, salad dressings, jellies and jams, and gifts from Lin\'s County Corner. The farm is only open for vegetables during the season of July 24 thru October 22 and will 