l: Mon-Fri by appointment','','http://www.qualitykoi.com/','','104 East Quillytown Road','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed1ec7f1-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','08069','Farm Tours, Others:Seminars and Koi Events','School Tours, Others:Lectures for groups/clubs','','2012-02-29 15:17:17','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('775cc727-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Scarecrow Hollow Cornfield Maze','Explore Salem County\'s rich heritage of the family farm as you get lost in our Corn Maze. More than a walk through the corn stalks, our maze is an interactive game with clever clue signs and more than 3 miles of trails. Scarecrow Hollow is located at 335 Quinton-Hancocks Bridge Road, Salem, NJ - just 2 miles off State Rt. 49. We offer food, hay wagon rides, pick-your-own pumpkins, gift shop, hay bale maze, tricycle maze for the little ones, pedal car track for the bigger ones, rope maze, and much more. For birthday parties, corporate picnics, team building, private parties and bonfires, family reunions, school tours, scouting and youth groups, and any other event that calls for the ultimate in family fun, call us at (856) 935-3469. Ample parking for cars, vans and buses is available. Scarecrow Hollow is a division of Wood Farms, established in 1966. We started doing the corn maze in an effort to educate the public about how food is grown and provide them with an enjoyable farm experience. For more information, please visit our website at www.scarecrowhollow.org.','856-935-3469','flowood@hughes.net','Florence Wood','','Opening September 25, closing October 31, 2010. Open Saturday 10am to 6pm - Sunday 12pm to 6pm. Open daily for school tours by appointment, beginning September 27,2010. Open Columbus day 10AM-6PM. Flashlight mazes are held Friday & Saturday evenings in Oc','','http://www.scarecrowhollow.org/','','335 Quinton-Hancocks Bridge Road','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b52