l-free produce. We also sell wholesale to local delis and caterers. Farm tours centering on our sustainable methods of production are avalible by appointment to school groups and other interested parties. Please visit our website for more information.','973-868-3137','amarchese@morangiefarm.com','Andrew Marchese','','','','http://www.morangiefarm.com/','','50 Willow Ave','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed1ec7f1-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','07977','Farm Tours, Others:Sustainabilty and Organic Methods Lectures and Tours','School Tours, Private Parties','','2012-02-29 15:17:17','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('77765fc9-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','English Farm','Welcome to English Farm located in scenic Liberty Corner. We have hayrides and a corn maze open every weekend. Our farm has been family owned for 8 generations. The farm includes a working farm, a farm market, and barnyard animals: cows, pigs, sheep, chickens and rabbits. We are open to the public from July through October selling our own eggs, seasonal vegetables including tomatoes, corn, squash, peppers to name a few. We have flowers, pumpkins and gourds in the fall.','(908) 647-3420','lists@englishfarm.org','C. English','','October hours SAT 10:00 - 6:00 SUN 11:00 - 5:00 MON & FRI 12:00 - 5:00, closed Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday Come enjoy our hayrides and corn maze!!','','http://www.englishfarm.org/','','3625 Valley Road','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed1ec7f1-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','07938','Corn Maze, Hay Rides','','','2012-02-29 15:17:17','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7779a828-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Ripple Hill Farm','Peach and Apple Orchards','908-647-1300','casorge@usa.net','Catherine Sorge','','September/October Sundays 12-4PM','','','','181 Mountain Road','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed1ec7f1-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','07920 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:17','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('777b4135-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Bardy Farms And Greenhouses','Established 1904 in central New Jersey we provide fresh fruits, vegetables, and flowers year round. We sell a large selection of garden bedding plants, hanging baskets, vegetable plants (including heirloom varieties), perannials, shrubs.hardy mums, asters and roses. Our greenhouses have all your lawn and garden needs. Seasonal items include Easter Flowers, Mother\'s Day Plants, pumpkins and Christmas trees, Wreaths and Grave Blankets. Our farm market provides fresh baked pies and breads ,cider donuts, gourmet cheeses, milk, jellies and apple cider in season. Organic selections included meats, cheeses, milk , frozen berries, frozen and fresh vegetables. ','(732) 356-4244','bardyfarms@aol.com','Robert Bardy','','7 am to 6 pm seven days a week year round (closed Christmas Day and New Years Day)','','http://www.bardyfarms.com/','','149 Washington Valley Rd.','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed1ec7f1-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','07059 ','Others:Greenhouse and farm market tours in season by appointment only','','','2012-02-29 15:17:17','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('777cafd5-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Upper Meadows Farm','Begun in 1987, Upper Meadows Farm has been devoted to sustainable holistic agriculture. Joining the Certified Organic community in 1991, we have maintained certification by NOFA-NJ ever since. We have evolved from our beginnings on 4 1/2 acres to our current size of 153 acres, all certified organic. During the course of which time, we have raised pigs, sheep, goats, rabbits, chickens, turkeys, and cattle, for meat, fur, fiber, eggs, and milk. We have also expanded our vegetable production from the traditional \"kitchen garden,\" which remains as one of our fields, to approximately 12 acres today, that serves our CSA as well as other markets. We are gradually expanding our fruit capabilities and planted 37 Apple and Pear trees in 2003.We have continued to plant some fruit trees each year since. We have been working to expand our berry bush and will be planting blueberries, which we last had available in 1994 and moving our raspberry patch. We are planning on planting new grape varieties to augment our concord vines. We have devoted an additional 1/2 acre to perennial flower production. We make hay when the sun shines and rotate our grain crops, which have been oats, wheat, rye, spelt, flax, buckwheat, and corn. All our livestock are pasture based and we are always working to improve and expand our pasture which we consider the foundation of our agricultural health. We will offer fresh pork again in the spring of 2007. We have several very busy beehives and have raw honey available year round while supplies last.Also while supplies last, we have maple syrup courtesy of our trees with a measure of hard work added for flavor.','973-293-8171','leonard@uppermeadowsfarm.com','Leonard Pollara','','For folks who would like to purchase goods at market rather than a CSA share, we have several market options. If none of the times listed are suitable for your needs please do not hesitate to call and arrange to stop by. Upper Meadows Farm On-Farm Market ','','http://www.uppermeadowsfarm.com/','','12 Pollara Lane','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed1ec7f1-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','07827 ','Farm Tours','School Tours, Others:All interactions are event and situation specific. Email your request and we\'ll respond.','','2012-02-29 15:17:17','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('777db779-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Spring Brook Farm','Spring Brook Farm is a NJ Farmland Preservation farm, with about 8 acres devoted to Christmas trees. It is situated in Sussex County near Stokes State Forrest. To find us from I-80, take Rt 15 North to Rt 206 North, to County Rt. 560, which will be a left turn at the bottom of the hill after passing Stokes State Forest. (Fratellis Restaurant is on the corner). Spring Brook Farm will be about 2 miles, on Rt 560, on the right, and just before the school. We (Fred and Lorraine) have been selling choose and cut your own Christmas trees here since 1989. We are usually joined on the weekends by our son-in-law Mark and/or grandaughter, Corry, who help us greet customers, answer questions, provide saws, bag the tree, and assist in tying it on your vehicle, if necessary. Please call us with any questions.','973-948-7440','ayerlooms@gmail.com','Fred or Lorraine  Ayers','','From Thanksgiving until Christmas we are open Saturdays and Sundays from 9:00 A.M. until 4:30 P.M. If a weekday is more convenient for you, please call, and we\'ll do our best to make other arrangements for you.','','','','84 County Route 560','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed1ec7f1-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','07851','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:17','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('777e9a88-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Owassa Tree Farm','Choose and Cut Christmas Trees. Choose from 200 Colorado Blue Spruce, Douglas-fir and Concolor-fir live trees.','973-948-4037','hrrowan@ptd.net','Harold Rowan','','9 - 5 daily, Nov 25 - Dec 24','','','','144 West Owassa Tpke.','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed1ec7f1-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','07860','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:17','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('777fb66c-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Sussex County Strawberry Farm','Sussex County Strawberry Farm, located in northern New Jersey, consists of two families who have been growing quality fruit for over 30 years. Not only are we growing berries, but we\'re growing a reputation for having the best berries. In addition, we grow and sell a wide variety of pumpkins, squash and gourds. Our Farm takes pride in offering quality produce in a friendly, family environment. We look forward to seeing you soon! ','973-579-5055','johnwolters@earthlink.net','John Wolters','','Fall Season Hours: Mon thru Sat: 9:00 am to 6:00 pm ; Sunday: 10:00 am to 5:00 pm','','http://www.sussexcountystrawberryfarm.com/','','565 Route 206 North','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed1ec7f1-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','07821 ','Hay Rides, Others:Hayrides weekends in October','','','2012-02-29 15:17:17','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7780d246-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','LL Pittenger Farm','The 180 acre LL Pittenger Farm allows Lou Tommaso the ability to produce and market natural meat products and a variety of quality hay. The land is devoted to providing pasture for the animals and crop production. All of the animals are humanely raised and are on a strict vegetarian diet. No hormones, antibiotics or steroids are fed, as Lou strives to keep the meat as natural as possible. “The animals’ diet is a vital part of producing quality meat”, Tommaso said. \"The food they consume plays a bigger part than their breeding or genetics.\" Lou raises beef cattle, pigs, lambs and has been on the leading edge of farmers exploring the marketability of quality goat meat in New Jersey. The pigs are fed a combination of soybean, oats and corn as well as hay and some greens. The beef cattle are on pasture year round, with supplemental corn silage and hay. A small allotment of grain is fed the last 6 weeks, to increase marbling in the meat. Goats and lambs are pastured and also receive soybean, oats and corn. Lou grows the majority of his own feed and patronizes other local farms for additional feed products. All of the meats are available in freezer orders or individual cuts, vacuum-packed and frozen for direct retail sales. In order to sell the individual cuts, the meat must be processed and labeled under stringent USDA guidelines. This option allows the consumer the opportunity to select their favorite steaks, chops, roasts, etc, and purchase smaller quantities than are available with freezer orders. LL Pittenger Farm is in production year-round. There is a constant, fresh supply of meat available. Customers can shop at the farm stand by appointment, or can purchase meat from Lou Tommaso at the Olde Lafayette Village or Blairstown Farmers’ markets June - Oct. ','973-786-6147','louistommaso@earthlink.net','Louis Tommaso','','Farm store open most days - hours by appointment only','','http://www.llpittengerfarm.com/','','143 Creek Rd','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed1ec7f1-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','07821','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:17','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7781e0cc-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Glenn Brook Nursery','Glenn Brook Nursery LLC was founded in 1990 by Glenn Phiefer. Glenn began by purchasing 30 acres of land in Lafayette, New Jersey, on which he built a house and one cold-frame greenhouse. The business has gradually expanded to its present 10 greenhouses, plus additional outside growing areas, totaling over ten acres. We constantly update our facilities and methods to bring you the best products available. Constant expansion keeps us able to meet all your needs. From its inception, our goal is to supply you, our customer, with numerous different types of plants, including many hard to find varieties at larger container sizes whenever you need them. For example, when you need a 3 gallon Bleeding Heart in October, we will have it for you! We consistently fulf