ou come to visit. The farm is tucked away from the crowds and congestion of busy Route 22, yet there is convenient parking right on the highway. Prior to its transformation into a Christmas tree farm, for 85 years or more, beef cattle grazed on these 45 acres. The loam soil is rich in organic matter that supports the growth of over 40 varieties of popular and exotic evergreens. This year\'s harvest includes Douglas, Concolor, Fraser and Balsam Fir and Blue Spruce and more exotic varieties like Vetch, Niko, Korean and Grand Fir. We have a large selection of real trees in all sizes. There are small trees to display on tables, perfect for children and seniors and trees in the 6-10 ft range and larger, up to 16 ft tall. You will find trees in pots to transplant, outdoors in Spring. Some trees are sheared tight and full. Some trees are sheared lightly. Our trees have long and short needles, hard and soft needles. They come in many shades of green and blue, some with white under needles. They are healthy, moist and sweet smelling. Come early for the best selection. Perfect Christmas trees hold their needles, guaranteed. Our trees come from the finest seed sources available. John, a NJ tree Christmas tree farmer since 1960, picks premium varieties known for outstanding needle retention. It takes knowledge, care, dedication and skill to produce Christmas trees of this quality. Every tree that leaves our farm is ready for display. We shake the tree to remove old needles, nests and debris. We trim the trunk so it fits nicely in your stand. Then we wrap the tree for easy transport home. Our trees are clean and easy to handle. We make our own wreaths from our own tree boughs. Our garland and swags are top quality. They stay fresh and green longer than anything you can get at the mall. We can\'t completely reverse the effects of deforestation and global warming, but we can discover how planting trees can help to combat climate change. While they\'re growing, Real Christmas Trees support life by absorbing carbon dioxide and other gases while emitting fresh oxygen. ','908-387-1225','pctree@verizon.net','Cynthia Curtis','','Starting Nov. 23, 2007 Daily 10:00 AM until 8:00 PM Sunday 10:00 until 6:00 Hayrides every weekend, Petting Zoo Dec. 1 and 2 & 8 and 9','','http://www.perfectchristmastree.com/','','999 US Highway 22','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed1ec7f1-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','08865','Hay Rides, Farm Tours, Petting Zoo','School Tours, Private Parties, Host Fundraisers/Events, Others:4th Annual','','2012-02-29 15:17:17','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7792fa3b-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Horse Sleigh Farm','Visit Horse Sleigh Farm for the BEST family farm experience! This year is our best yet! Check out this amazing list we have! Bring both friends & family for tons of fun! Come at night on Fridays or Saturdays for extra scare! -Huge 10+ Acre Corn Maze -Children\'s Maze with that -Home Grown Pumpkins -Home Grown Squash -Pumpkin Painting -Pumpkin Carving -Pony Rides -Hay Rides -Haunted Hay Rides -Haunted Corn Maze -Delicious Food & Drinks, -HUGE Hay Mountain -Corn Box -Game Tent -Animal Petting -Water Buffalo Sightings -Hay Maze -Corn Cannon -Tightrope Challenge -Photo Opportunities -Hot Air Balloon Rides -Horse Drawn Wagon Rides -Pig Roasts See our main site at www.HorseSleighFarm.com NJ\'s BEST FARM! Special Events Hot Air Balloon Rides October 10th. Ride on a Hot Air Balloon! Have the experience of a life time. Bring Friends! Horse Wagon Hay Rides October 10th & 11th, October 14th & 25th. Bring Friends! Pony Rides Every Weekend! Bring Friends! Haunted Hayride Every Friday & Sat Night. Scary Stuff! Bring Friends! Haunted Corn Maze Every Friday & Sat Night. They\'ll get you when you least expect it! Bring Friends! Laser Tag Night Maze November 6th & 7th! Be there! Bring Friends!','908-246-3044','horsesleighfarm@aol.com','Shaw