 her husband Travis Hewett.   Born and raised near the banks of the Lockwood Folly River, the couple has roots buried deep in the rich soil of Brunswick County. With unmistakable southern drawls, they speak well to the importance of supporting their local community and artisans, while providing specialty products to area. Whether they\'re celebrating their own farming heritage at a family pig-pickin\' or seeking new vendors for the marketplace, their excitement is contagious. ','910-754-5445 ','tlhewett@atmc.net ','Lindsay W. Hewett','','Monday through Friday 9:00AM - 6:00PM Saturday 9:30AM - 2:30PM Closed on Sundays ','','www.lockwoodfollymarketplace.com ','','48 Stone Chimney Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28462 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:25','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7c479fc4-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Mawji Foods, Inc. ','We have a new product on the market called \"Manja! Gourmet Glaze & Drizzle\", available in 16 and 32 oz. bottles. We first introduced this unique sauce from our restaurant (Mama Brava\'s) in the early 90\'s as a wing sauce, and have won numerous awards, including \"Best on the Beach\" Wings in Myrtle Beach, and WWAY- TVs \"Best Wings in Southeastern NC\". Our glaze is versatile and can be used on pulled pork, ribs, barbecue chicken pizza, shrimp, sushi, cooked vegetables, and as a dip. We like to think the flavors are complex, similar to a fine wine. Original is a little bit sweet, a little bit spicy, and well balanced so the heat does not overpower the palate. We never use corn syrup, and all sauce products are gluten free.   The first \"test run\" (75 gallons at Bobbee\'s Bottling) was in spring, 2011. The bottles sold out in less than five months. Currently, distribution is limited to our restaurant in Shallotte, Hill\'s Grocery stores, Piggly Wiggly in Leland, and a few specialty 