 the mid-west and Canada. Mama Brava\'s was asked to serve a five year contract with the prestigious West Point Academy where it received the highest rating for culinary excellence ever presented to a franchise in the history of the institution.   As the youngest of 13 children, Karim Mawji was quickly recognized as a major talent in the family business. He reduced the oil in the fresh pizza dough recipe, and added fresh vegetables as natural sweeteners to the marinara. In 1988, he moved to the Carolina\'s with his wife, Debora. They opened several restaurants along the coast, and eventually settled into the small hamlet of Shallotte, NC. With more than 30 years of performing his craft upon a brick oven, Karim has rightfully earned the title of Master Pizza Chef.   The popular wing sauce recipe can be credited to Karim\'s business partner and wife. In a spur of the moment decision to raise money for the American Red Cross, Karim decided to compete against the big guys along Myrtle Beach\'s famed \"Restaurant Row\". But since he had never cooked wings at his restaurant before, he called Debora on the phone and asked her to come up with a recipe for wing sauce, quick! Off the top of her head, she suggested a unique combination of ingredients that would surely taste different from the rest. This last minute creation earned them the highly coveted \"Best on the Beach\" Buffalo Wing trophy, snatching the title from a nationally acclaimed franchise. Imagine their surprise! This popular wing sauce has subsequently won three additional awards for excellence, and is now available in bottles under the brand name \"Manja! Gourmet Glaze & Drizzle\". ','910-616-8916 ','mawjifoods@gmail.com ','Debora or Karim Mawji','','Monday through Saturday. 11 AM - 2 PM for lunch. 4 PM to 9 PM for dinner. ','','www.mawjifoods.com ','','119 Holden Beach Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28470 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:25','a1c3e20e-f181