an old family home site in rural Brunswick County. We are open year round with herb & vegetable plants, plus cut flowers as bedding plants for the season.   We sell fresh-cut herbs and edible flowers to local restaurants and caterers. We also sell at local Farmers\' Markets and several local garden shows and special events. Farmers\' Markets we take part in are listed below.   We are members of the North Carolina Herb Association, NC AgriTourism Networking Association, Hobby Greenhouse Club, Cape Fear Audubon, North Carolina Native Plant Society. We do an email newsletter with information about the farm, cultivation practices, our classes, local events and more. You can find Shelton Herb Farm on Facebook. ','910-253-5964 ','herbnflora@atmc.net ','Margaret & Chuck Shelton','','Open year-round. 8am to 5pm, Monday - Saturday. Closed Sundays and Holidays ','','','','340 Goodman Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28451 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:25','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7c535fac-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Shelton Herb Farm  ','Shelton Herb Farm is located on an 200 year old family farm. The business was started in 1986. We are open year-round and sell herbs appropriate for all the seasons. We have greenhouses, outside display areas under shade, and working gardens full of herbs, vegetables and cut flowers.  We have hundreds of varieties. we sell herbs, vegetables, butterfly plants, native and heirloom plants. Plants range from bedding plants to landscape-ready pots. We specialize in varieties that do well in our southern climate. We grow what we sell.   We are a certified Birder Friendly Business. Our farm is surrounded by a pristine natural setting which includes, Long Leaf/ Wire Grass savannahs, several Carolina Bays, two beaver ponds, and numerous dark water branches that meander through hardwood forest and thick low-land bay underbrush on the way to Town Creek. These woods are teeming with birds and wildlife. A diversity of carniverous plants abide here too. ','910-253-5964 ','herbnflora@atmc.net ','Margaret Goodman Shelton','','Monday - Saturday; 8am - 5pm','','','','340 Goodman Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28451 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:25','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7c54517f-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Ashevilla Wines  ','Ashevilla Wines are made with 100% North Carolina grown grapes! From the recognized appellation Haw River Valley, Ashevilla Wines seeks to promote NC agriculture and awareness. Eat local, drink local! Ashevilla Wines !   Did you know that prior to prohibition NC \"grew\" more wine than any other state, even more than CA and NY! With prohibition in place we switched to tobacco. When the tobacco subsidies went away, we switched right back to our roots: growing grapes and making wine!   With nearly 100 wineries now, NC is quickly making a name for itself in the wine business. As the vines are getting to be around a decade old, the complexity and richness of our soil and climate is allowing growers to create wines that rival that of any other state. Drink Ashevilla Wines ! ','828-285-8957 ','george@ashevillawines.com ','George Ibrahim','','','','www.ashevillawines.com ','','197 Kimberly Ave ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28804 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:25','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7c55922b-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Cloud 9 Farm','Vacation on 200 agricultural & wooded acres just 15 minutes SE of Asheville in the Blue Ridge Mountains. Explore Cloud 9 Farm where WE work and YOU relax. Where you can find...(now sing this jingle)\"Beds, Berries, Trees...Beef and Honey Bees!\"   *Beds: Two Vacation Rentals, Cloud 9 Relaxation Home, a upgraded 4 Bdrm ranch house with mountain views, easy driveway, hot tub on open deck for families AND Heavenly Hideaway Cabin for couples; secluded with open deck hot tub. Hiking, biking, fishing, farm tours of this conservation farm. Your continued support saves this farm from being sold to developers. *Berries: U-Pick Blueberries in late June - July on an acre site, free for those who stay on the farm *Trees: Portable sawmilling, lumber, posts, beams, rhododendron accents. Watch sustainable forestry at work as we maintain the health of the forests. *Beef: Hormone and anti-biotic beef is raised naturally with a small herd of Black Angus *Honey Bees: Needed for pollination on the farm, Products from the Hive are sold seasonally. Education in beesuits!   And don\'t forget the Chickens! When you stay on the farm you are always supplied with fresh eggs! You can even gather them yourself. So, Come, Experience the Simple Life on Cloud 9 Farm Vacations, Tours, Conferences, Picnics, Weddings 828-628-1758 ','828-628-1758 ','info@cloud9relaxation.com ','Janet Peterson','','Vacation Rentals open year round. Tours by appointment, small charge. ','','www.cloud9relaxation.com ','','137 Bob Barnwell Rd. ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28732 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:25','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7c5727e5-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Looking Glass Creamery','Looking Glass Creamery is the home of fine handcrafted, small batch, artisanal cheeses. We are a small, family owned and operated creamery located in the mountains of Western North Carolina. We start with fresh raw milk that we buy weekly from several local farms and process it in small batches to make a limited variety of goat and cow milk cheeses. We strive to produce an excellent product made with no artificial preservatives, stabilizers, or additives and free of added growth hormones or other unnatural ingredients. Our cheeses contain only milk, cultures, seasalt, and rennet along with the occasional herbs and spices from the best sources.   Looking Glass Creamery is a very small family farm and licensed cheesemaking facility located in Fairview which is just outside of Asheville, North Carolina. The business was started by Jennifer & Andy Perkins to produce exceptional, small batch, handmade cheese from goat and cows milk. The Perkins settled permanently in Western North Carolina in 2001 after falling in love with the area on their honeymoon hike of the Appalachian Trail in 1994.After a year of construction, the creamery was licensed by the North Carolina Department of Agriculture early in 2009. In the first year they focused on developing several varieties of fresh and aged goat milk cheeses and specialized in the production of bloomy rind, semi-soft cheeses. Cow milk production began in late 2009.   The very small farm where Looking Glass Creamery is located also maintains a flock of laying hens in a mobile coop, two Saanen family milkers (Vivian & Tess), a large and ever-expanding garden, a blueberry patch, grape vines, and a number of fruit trees including apple, pear, quince, peach, and cherry and a beautiful Great Pyrenees named Moses to watch over it all. The establishment of Looking Glass Creamery was the fruition of a decade of work, research, and passion for artisan cheeses that capture the character of a place, reflect the quality of the milk, the farm it came from, and the hand of the cheesemaker. ','828-458-0088 ','jen@ashevillecheese.com ','Jen Perkins','','','','www.ashevillecheese.com ','','P.O. Box 2157 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28730 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:25','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7c58076e-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Sandy Hollar Farms','We have Christmas trees growing in all stages - at Christmastime we offer a \"choose & cut\" operation with hayrides fresh wreaths unique Christmas shop with hot chocolate and apple cider. ','828-683-3645 ','sandyholfm@aol.com ','Curtis or June Hawkins','','Please call for operation hours','','','','63 Sandy Hollar Lane ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28748','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:25','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7c5964af-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Scuttergilly Meadows Farm and Rabbitry','We\'re a tiny family owned and operated farm located in the beautiful western North Carolina mountains. On our farm we selectively breed and raise French Angora rabbits for their luxurious fiber, to sell as show or breeding stock to other Angora fanciers or handspinners/ fiber artists and as family pets. Some of the fiber is used in our line of felted wearables and other fiber art, which is created by Andrea (me, the wife and Mama) and by our daughter, while the rest is offered for sale to other artists and crafters. Angora comes only from rabbits and is warmer than most wools and softer than silk...it is like grasping a cloud on a hot summer day...! It\'s a common misconception that Angora goats produce angora fiber, their fiber is actually known as mohair and is simply gorgeous as well...:).  In addition to our angora fiber and fiber art,we sell produce at our local tailgate market from mid April to October. In 2009 we plan to add cut flowers and plants as well as increase the variety of produce we offer. All our produce is grown organically though we choose to not go through the lengthy and expensive process of becoming certified organic. For the 2008 season we used all horse or human powered equipment to grow our produce! Unfortunately we are not able to continue in that wonderful way and have had to part with our horses. Our horse powered operation was several miles from our home on leased land. We\'ve chosen to move our gardens to our home and concentrate on low and no till growing methods. All our horses have been rehomed with most staying with extended family or friends so we get to visit often!   We\'d love to have folks visit the rabbitry and garden. In the future we hope to be able to teach others about the methods we are trying right now which include permaculture, raised beds, intensive composting and vermaculture (earth worms). We do have an informational booklet available for prospective bunny owners on the care and housing of Angora rabbits and will demonstrate grooming and harvesting fiber to visitors. ','828-626-2140 ','peterbilt94mb@peoplepc.com ','Andrea Meadows','','Contact us!','','','','1396 Dillingham Rd.','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28709 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:25','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7c5ab132-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Smoking Js Hot Sauce Company  ','Smoking Js Hot Sauce Company is family owned and operated and is located in Western North Carolinas beautiful Blue Ridge Mountain town of Candler which is just a few short miles west of Asheville. Asheville is a city rich with naturally grown, artfully produced and lovingly prepared cuisine and so much more. Inspired by our regions local food movement and a passion for gardening and cooking Smoking Js Hot Sauce Company has set out to create original hand crafted specialty food products with great emphasis being placed on quality ingredients and unique combinations.   Our commitment to fiery foods is only matched by our commitment to flavor, so when we begin experimenting with new product ideas we are after the perfect balance, hot & spicy but full of flavor. Currently our product line includes natural and preservative free hot sauces, bbq sauces, salsas, blended dry rubs, pepper purees, seasonally fresh peppers and whole dried peppers. We grow many of the fruits and vegetables that make up our products on our 10 acre farm and we are dedicated to natural and environmentally conscious production practices. Our products are prepared in small batches and closely monitored to insure a high level of taste consistency and character.   In addition to our specialty food products we are also wholesale growers and sellsers of quality pepper transplants. ','','store@firiehotsauce.com ','Joel Mowrey','','By appointment only ','','www.smokingjshotsauce.com ','','36 Rootstock Rd.','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28715 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:25','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7c5b845a-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Yiayia Foods/GG&T Corporation  ','','828 258 0202 ','ggtcorp@aol.com ','Nick G. Tsiros','','','','www.yiayiafoods.com ','','143 Westwood Rd ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28804 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:25','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7c5c9a0b-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Elk Mountain Nursery  ','Elk Mountain Nursery specializes in plants native to the Eastern United States. We are one of the pioneer nurseries on the Web. Our Catalog has been online since 1996.   Our nursery is located in the mountains of Western North Carolina. The long, cool growing season; coupled with a short, but intense winter; makes Asheville an ideal site for a nursery serving the Eastern United States. The nursery is in USDA Zone 6b, allowing us to grow a wide variety of species adapted to both cooler and warmer areas.   We take great pride in providing vigorous, healthy plants. Our shipping methods are the finest in the business. And we do our best to make every customer a repeat customer! ','828 683 9330 ','craig@elk-mountain.com ','Craig Mailloux','','By appointment only 828.683.9330 ','','elk-mountain.com ','','PO Box 599 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28802','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:25','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7c5d7125-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Highlander Farm  ','We\'re nestled in the mountains of Fairview, N.C. and raise lamb\'s and chickens. We\'ve got a 104 acre farm that serves our needs, and we pride ourselves on not using chemicals.','828-628-3780 ','highlanderfarm@gmail.com','Nick Nichols','','','','www.highlanderfarm.net ','','35 Kirkpatrick Lane ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28730','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:25','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7c5eae41-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Biltmore Estate Winery','At the Biltmore Estate Winery, rich tradition meets state-of-the-art technology under the masterful direction of our French winemaker, Bernard Delille. Vineyards on the estate\'s west side grow several varieties of vinifera grapes while the estate\'s former dairy complex now houses the winery. It produces 120,000 cases of wine each year in about 15 varieties. Biltmore wines have been awarded gold and double-gold medals in prestigious national and international competitions.   You can easily spend several hours in the winery on your self-guided visit as you observe the unique combination of art and science that goes into great winemaking. After touring the winery, sample complimentary Biltmore wines in our Tasting Room. In this expansive, light-filled area (originally the dairy milking parlor), our friendly hosts guide you through the tasting process. Even children can participate by tasting grape juice.   There\'s always something special going on at the winery. Our year-round activities include barrel tastings, food and wine pairing, and cooking demonstrations. On special event weekends, jazz and blues bands perform, and children of all ages can try stomping grapes.','800.624.1575 ','','Heather Jordan','','11:00 –7:00 p.m. (8:00 p.m. Friday and Saturday) 12:00 noon–7:00 p.m. Sunday ','','www.biltmorewine.com ','','1 North Pack Square ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28801','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:25','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7c5fcd22-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Blue Mountain Trading Company  ','Blue Mountain Trading Co. specializes in All Natural & Organic, Body Care & Supplements, Textiles & Jewelry that are Grown & Made in Small, Cottage Industry Businesses, in North Carolina & Appalachia.   We mostly sell wholesale to other North Carolina Small Businesses. We also sell retail at festivals throughout the warm season. ','828-280-0726 ','bluemountaintrading@charter.net','Clare Schwartz','','all day everyday ','','www.bluemtntrading.com ','','15 Wills Lane ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28715 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:25','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7c60ab40-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Brooks Bakery ','Brooks Bakery is a home-based bake shop specializing in breads, cookies and cakes. We believe in using whole ingredients to create traditional baked goods--letting the flour and sugar, butter and eggs shine with fresh fruits, vegetables and nuts to highlight.   Independently owned and operated by 21-year-old Emily Brooks--Homeschool alumni and graduate of AB-Tech\'s Baking and Pastry Arts program.   We look forward to working with you to make every day special...whether for a holiday or special occasion, or just as a day to celebrate because we\'re alive and well! ','828-230-2667 ','emily.brooksbakery@yahoo.com','Emily Brooks','','8am-5pm, Monday-Friday, 8am-1pm Saturday. ','','','','55 Locust Meadow Lane ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28787 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:25','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7c61db19-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Cane Creek Asparagus & Company','Cane Creek Asparagus & Company is a family owned and operated sustainable farm serving our community with over nine continuous years of CSA Farming experience. We have about six acres under cultivation. CSA Members say it\'s like having a garden in your backyard without all of the work!   We are water conscious on our farm using only drip irrigation methods. We employ Integrated Pest Management (or IPM) in our gardens. IPM is a natural, systematic approach to approach to controlling pests. Insects and bug bites on the produce are a part of the natural garden experience. You should expect to find slugs and bugs in your CSA box!    The long-term benefits of eating healthy food outweigh the short-term cost of fresh food preparation. If you want to eat healthier, we will supply a continuously changing array of local vegetables along with recipe suggestions and even a vegetable identification photo album to help get you started! ','','canecreekcsa@bellsouth.net ','Glenda Ploeger','','Vegetable boxes offered to CSA Members six days a week for the entire local harvest season. We do not have a roadside stand or sell at tailgate markets. We grow exclusively for our CSA Family Members! ','','www.CaneCreekCSA.com ','','POB 2012 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28730'