sible upon the earth.    Located in the mountains of North Carolina, our handmade soap, fair trade shea butter products, hemp lip balm, body care products, and products for skin care are made from natural ingredients in small batches. ','828-251-5291 ','info@faeriemadesoaps.com ','Tina Glenn ','','','','www.faeriemadesoaps.com ','','PO Box 17181 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28816','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:25','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7c65622d-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Fairview General Store  ','','828-628-2332 ','dhg47k9801@aol.com ','Mike Sellers','','Monday thru Friday 6:30am til 9:00pm Saturday 7:30am til 9:00pm Sunday 8:30am til 7:00pm ','','www.fairviewgeneralstore.com ','','1512 Charlotte Hwy ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28730','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:25','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7c66307d-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','FarmAsheville','','','sponsorfarm@gmail.com ','Adam Nikulicz','','','','farmasheville.org ','','','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28801','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:25','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7c675139-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','FarmLink Carolina','So what exactly is FarmLinkCarolina.com? We\'re not selling food online. What we do is provide a comprehensive, up-to-date database of local food where producers can post their products, a powerful search capability that buyers can use to locate ingredients, and an ordering capability, an online means for chefs to place orders and communicate directly with local producers. Chefs, the search engine will wow you! For a look, go to farmlinkcarolina.com and take the Quick Tour. Restaurants can find out what\'s in season, who\'s got it, who\'ll deliver it, and who has the best price. ','828.318.3138 ','folks@farmlinkcarolina.com ','Rita Livezey','','On the web 24/7 ','','www.farmlinkcarolina.com ','','','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28805','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:25','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7c684017-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Fordbrook Stables','Scenic mountain horse back riding at its best! Great views of the Biltmore House, Grove Park Inn and surrounding Asheville area.   We would love to host your birthday party, family reunion, company picnic or group gathering! We make your event complete with our campfire cookout. Contact Rhonda_Fordbrook@yahoo.com for additional information.   Full boarding available daily, weekly & monthly. Contact Linda Ford for additional information','828-667-1021 ','Rhonda_fordbrook@yahoo.com','Ford Family','','Open year around. Please contact the reservation desk at (828) 667-1021 to book your ride or event.','','www.fordbrookstables.com ','','120 Fordbrook Rd. ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28806','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:25','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7c69519f-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Gaining Ground Farm ','We grow a wide variety of seasonal vegetables, flowers, and herbs using ecologically responsible growing methods. We offer CSA shares and grass fed Devon beef as well as all produce at local tailgate markets ','828-545-2362 ','sluderbranch@yahoo.com ','Anne Grier','','','','www.gaininggroundfarm-nc.com ','','298 Sluder Branch Rd ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28748 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:25','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7c6a899f-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Gladheart Farms, LLC','Gladheart Farms is a 7.5 acre Certified Organic Farm located just minutes from the cultural mecca of downtown Asheville, NC. At its purchase, Gladheart Farms was a prime development property, but was bought and turned back into agricultural use. With a growing trend away from small farms coupled with unstable energy prices, Gladheart Farms felt it was important to preserve one of the most basic foundation stones in our society - local food. Because of this belief, this small urban farm is growing in a sustainable direction. All equipment and greenhouses are powered by bio- diesel which is made from waste vegetable oil and all produce is sold local, providing the consumer with the freshest quality without the unnecessary high transportation costs.  Gladheart Farms welcomes visitors. We are a full scale certified organic farm and are happy to stop and talk with people who come by. We sell direct from our farm as well as wholesale to various markets in the area. We have alpine goats and also welcome volunteers to come work on the farm. We hope you will stop by if you are in the area. ','828-280-7595 ','info@gladheartfarms.com','Michael Porterfield','','We are open from 9am to 5pm Sunday through Friday. We are closed Saturday. ','','www.gladheartfarms.com ','','29 Lora Lane ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28803','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:25','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7c6b7079-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Green Jade Herbal  ','Here in the beautiful blue ridge mountains we handmake all of our products using only pure, natural ingredients. Our goal is to provide our customers with the highest quality herbal and aromatherapy products.','828-280-9058 ','greenjadeherbal@aol.com','Elizabeth Bloomquist','','Monday-Friday: 9AM-5PM','','www.greenjadeherbal.com ','','9 Homeway Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28806','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:25','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7c6cd04c-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','HeatherLane Farms  ','As of April 29, 2008, we became a licensed Grade B goat dairy producing fluid milk to local licensed cheesemakers. We strive for a high quality milk, rich in butterfat and protein. Great cheese comes from great milk! May 2009 saw us begin production of our Mountain Made Goat Milk Fudge in three wonderful flavors. Our Chocolate fudge is a tradional fudge made with semi sweet chocolate. Peanutty Butty has sea salted chopped peanuts thoughout the candy, with the saltiness of the peanuts offsetting the sweetness of the fudge. Our Coconut fudge is a white chocolate fudge with sweet coconut thoughout the fudge, given texture to the candy. All of our fudge is made the old fashion way, on the stovetop with careful attention to time and temperture. Mountain Made Goat Milk Fudge Truffles are a great addition to any party. We start by rolling our Mountain Made Goat Milk Fudge into bite size balls. Then they take a turn into either sweeten cocoa, sea salted chopped peanuts or sweet coconut.Party trays available in three sizes with free delivery in the Asheville area. All the trays are decorted to fit the occassion, including our signature GOAT.   Jennifer Perkins owner and cheesemaker of Looking Glass Creamery is turning our excess milk into a wonderful lightly aged cheese called \"Ellington.\" Ellington has a smooth creamery inner texture. This has to be the best cheese ever produced with our milk! Our Goat Milk Soaps contain fresh milk, never powder or canned milk. Our soaps contain no chemicals or colorants, and are safe enough for people for sensitve skin. We also offer soaps with all natural essence oils and just plain old fashion lye soap.Our products are only tested on humans, never the animals.   We have goats for sale year round. Please contact us for the current sales list. While we welcome visitors to our farm, we do ask that you call and schedule an appointment, so we can give YOU our valued customers and friends our full attention! ','828-254-7610 ','heatherlanefarms@cs.com ','Ken and Yvonne Cobourn','','Year Round-By Appointment. ','','www.heatherlanefarms.webs.com ','','PO Box 8145 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28814 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:25','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7c6e0a67-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Hickory Nut Gap Farm  ','We are fourth generation farmers on this mountain land. Currently we raise and direct market hormone and antibiotic free meats. Available by the individual cut or in bulk quantities. Email us at office@hickorynutgapfarm.com with questions or visit our website.   Our mission is to connect sustainable agriculture practices, our family history, and our customers by sharing the family farm experience and serving as an example of healthy land stewardship while providing high quality ethically raised meats. At Hickory Nut Gap Farm you will find animals raised in their natural environment. Pigs outdoors, cows on pasture eating grass and clover, multiple species grazing together, drinking fresh spring water and living the good life.    Added activities include school tours, pony rides, a corn maze, Upick pumpkins, barnyard animals and the farm store,complete with all local products. Don\'t forget your cooler. Soon we will be offering U-pick blueberries! ','828-628-1027 ','office@hickorynutgapfarm.com','Amy Ager','','Farm Store Hours: Wed-Saturday 1-5pm. During the Fall (September and October) we are open Monday-Sunday 9-6pm. ','','www.hickorynutgapfarm.com ','','57 Sugar Hollow Rd ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28730','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:25','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7c6f3ccb-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Hobbyknob Farm  ','I have been raising llamas, sheep and chickens since 2001. The sheep I raise are dual purpose (fiber and meat) and on the ALBC conservation list. My primary sheep breed is the Jacob sheep. My llamas are mostly for fun and fiber. I do not currently breed llamas. Llamas are good grazers and browsers, highly intelligent and trainable. I raise laying chickens traditionally found on old farms that are known to be hardy and good foragers.  Last year I fell in love with dairy goats so I added a pair of Nigerian Dwarf dairy goats from HeatherLane Farms. These small goats are perfect for someone with small space that wants to enjoy their own milk and homemade cheese.   I am constantly learning about these animals and would love to help you learn also. ','828-645-5869 ','hobbyknobfarm@main.nc.us','Elizabeth Strub','','By appointment only','','www.hobbyknobfarm.com','','14 white Bridge Rd ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28787 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:25','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7c70555f-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Hop\'n Blueberry Farm  ','We are a member of North Carolina Century Farms and have recently converted our small cattle farm to raising sustainable crops. Our goal is to experiment and establish new and exciting crops for small farms in North Carolina.  Currently we are experimenting with hops. Much research is being devoted with the crop this year and the next two years to determine if hops can survive here in North Carolina.   Next year, we are planning to expand our experimentation with another native plant that many consider a weed. More to come on this in the months to come ','828-664-1166 ','hopnblue@yahoo.com ','Van Burnette','','9-5 everyday. Open only by calling first. ','','','','24 Middle Mountain Rd. ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28711 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:25','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7c71496b-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Imladris Farm','Shhh???hear that? Songbirds courting in the raspberry canes? Or the heavy silence of snowflakes slowly blanketing the blueberry bushes? Perhaps the early morning songs of berry pickers, harvesting before the mid-day heat? At any time of year, a visit to Imladris Farm is an adventure of flavor and a chance to rejoin the age-old cycle of seasons. ','828 628 9377 ','info@imladrisfarm.com ','Walter Harrill','','All hours, by appointment ','','www.imladrisfarm.com ','','45 Little Pond Rd. ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28730','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:25','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7c729d4d-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Jake\'s Farm','You can find us at the Black Mountain Tailgate Market, Asheville City Market, and Carolina Organic Growers at the Western North Carolina Farmers Market. We offer tours by appointment. We do have an intern program. Our two heated greenhouses produce product for our customers year round. ','828-665-4472 ','jakesfarm@msn.com ','Chris Sawyer/ Missy Huger','','By appointment only ','','www.jakesfarm.com ','','99 Brown Lynch Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28715 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:25','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7c73643b-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4