sa, Carolina Culinary\'s, Faerie Made skin care, Savoir essences, Red Moon Herbs, Mountain Well Being Colloidals, Sunset Valley farms jams & relishes, Springhouse Meats & More!   We also offer some of our products for sale through our website. If you can\'t find what you are looking for, please let us know. Maybe we can assist you. ','828 645 0403 ','naturesnectar@verizon.net ','Gloria Coppola','','Summer Hours: M-W,F 8:30-6 Thurs 8:30-7 Sat 10-6 Sun 11-4','','www.naturesnectar.net ','','235 Weaverville Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28804 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:25','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7c791322-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Pisgah View Ranch  ','Welcome to Pisgah View Ranch, NC ... the best guest ranch east of the Mississippi. Come and experience your next Ranch Family Vacation at the Pisgah View Ranch. For more than half a century, spending time at Pisgah View Ranch has been a tradition for visitors from all over the world who are looking for that perfect Blue Ridge Mountain getaway to unwind, relax and put the stress of every day life on hold. Capture the spirit of the old west while riding across miles of trails on over 2,000 breathtaking acres. ','(828) 667-9100 ','info@pisgahviewranch.net','Hanna Libecap or Mark McMullen','','May 1st to October 31st. ','','www.pisgahviewranch.net ','','70 Pisgah View Ranch Rd ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28715 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:25','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7c7ab7ba-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Randall Glen Resort  ','Randall Glen is a luxury resort located just outside Asheville, North Carolina in the historic farming community of Big Sandy Mush. Completely isolated by mountains, this picture postcard valley is still farmed by original settler families and has no commercial development at all. Wea€?re at the very end of the valley, on 80 acres of mountainside, wildflowers, creeks, and forest. Wea€?re surrounded by thousands of acres of conservancy land, and wildlife flourishes here. Our Home Farm is at an elevation of 3100 feet and our Randall Glen mountaintop is at 3600 feet, giving us wonderfully cool summer air and great snow in the winter.   For our guests we offer seven luxury log cabins on the wooded mountainside, each with magnificent mountain views and well separated from the others. Four cabins comfortably sleep 2 to 6 persons and three accommodate 4 to 8. Each cabin has a cathedral ceiling living room with a woodburning fireplace; a fully equipped chefa€?s kitchen; a spacious dining area; a rocking chair front porch; and a huge screened porch with a stereo hot tub and outdoor dining table. Amenities include central heat and air, washer and dryer, dishwasher, telephone, satellite TV/DVD/VCR with an extra bedroom TV, and highspeed internet. Some of the luxuries include featherbeds, heated towels, and leather sofas. Kids and pets are welcome, and we provide accessible and low-allergin accommodations as well. Wea€?re open year round.   Activities at Randall Glen include horseback riding and hayrides; trout fishing; extensive hiking and mountain biking trails; gem mining; bonfires and cookouts; a big games lawn with outdoor games and winter sledding; a full game room including billiards, ping pong, Foosball, and air hockey; a comprehensive Fitness Center; gift shop and general store with basic groceries; lending library of videos, books, and games; espresso bar; and living history at our historic settlera€?s log cabin. Our home farm provides fresh vegetables, fruits, and eggs. Guests are welcome to participate in everyday farm life and to help feed our Highland sheep, goats, chickens, ducks, geese, and llamas. According to season, you might experience horsedrawn plowing, sheep shearing, horseshoeing, or bottle feeding lambs and baby goats. There are simple pleasures, too, like blackberrying, creek wading, picking armloads of wildflowers, chasing fireflies, and gazing at more stars than youa€?ve ever seen. We want you to feel at home here, and to feel as if youa€?re part of these mountains. Come to the Southern Highlands. Come home to Randall Glen. ','828-683-5758 ','lkkg@aol.com ','Linda Goodin','','We are open for mountain trail rides (horseback) 7 days a week and reservatons must be made at least a day in advance. The gem mine is open from 10am to 5pm every day except Monday. A farm tour is given any day at 3pm upon request. ','','www.randallglen.com ','','96 Randall Cove Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28748','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:25','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7c7c1a8e-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Reems Creek Nursery','Reems Creek Nursery is just 10 minutes north of downtown Asheville / I-240 in the lovely town of Weaverville, NC. One of Buncombe County\'s oldest and most experienced retail garden centers, the staff at Reems Creek Nursery has been helping people beautify their surroundings with gorgeous plants, gardening supplies, and knowledgeable advice since 1980.  Create your own oasis with our enticing selection ~ from unique conifers and elegant japanese maples to landscaping staples and vegetable plants. Whether your style is formal, English Country, native habitat or farm, our plant specialists can advise you on which species fit your particular needs, and how to keep them thriving. In-depth consultations, design, and installation are available through our Landscape Department.   We have a beautiful and unique selection of trees & shrubs, roses, perennials, annuals, bedding plants, vegetable plants, native plants, fruits, houseplants and hanging baskets, seeds, heirloom and organic seeds, water plants, fish, & pond supplies, organic gardening supplies, potting soils and soil amendments, gardening supplies, garden gifts, gift certificates & more. ','828-645-3937 ','reemscreek3937@verizon.net ','Wilma and Bill Penland','','Spring Hours until July 4: Mon. thru Fri. 8-6, Saturday 9-6, Summer/Early Fall hours: Mon. thru Fri. 8-5:30, Saturday 9-5, Late Fall/Winter Hours: Mon. thru Fri. 8-5, Saturday 9-4, Hours usually change along with the Time Change.','','www.reemscreek.com ','','70 Monticello Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28787 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:26','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7c7d6009-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Round Mountain Creamery  ','Our Round Mountain Creamery is the first and only combined Dairy Goat Farm and Grade A Goat Milk Processing Plant in the state of North Carolina. Seligman E.G.G. Farm, Inc.: Seligman Eggs, Goats, and Garden Farm is located in the Blue Ridge Mountains on a 28 acre strip of land surrounded by streams on all sides. Our farmstead is nestled just below Round Mountain, about 25 miles south of Ashville, North Carolina. Our pampered Alpine, LaMancha and Nubian goat herd provide an excellent quality goat milk for our Farmstead Grade A vat pasteurized Goat Milk and Goat Cheeses. The method we use to produce our milk is regulated by North Carolina Department of Environment and Natural Resources. Our vat pasteurized Goat Milk is tested regularly under strict PMO (Pasteurized Milk Ordnance) guidelines. We are confident that vat pasteurization and bottling in glass bottles will protect the integrity of our fresh Whole Goat Milk. We are able to provide 50 to 100 bottles in any combination of quart and half gallon sizes. Our cheeses are made from the same grade A Goat Milk that is produced and bottled on our farm and is regulated by the North Carolina Department of Agriculture and Consumer Services Food and Drug Protection Division. Our Goat Cheese is a mild and creamy canvas for a culinary pallet of certified dehydrated organic herbs, spices and naturally grown fruits and nuts. Fresh Whole Goat Milk and twelve flavors of Goat Cheese is available daily. Our Herbed and/or Spiced Goat Cheeses, freezes well for up to six months. We milk year round and always have fresh Goat Milk and Fresh cheeses. A Farm, Dairy and Cheese Tasting Tours ($5 per person) are available by appointment. Please call 828-669-0718 if you are interested in visiting the farm. ','828-669-0718 ','las@rmcreamery.com ','Linda Seligman','','9 AM - 5 PM Monday - Friday ','','www.roundmountaincreamery.com ','','2203 Old Fort Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28711','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:26','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7c7e7963-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Southern Charm Horses  ','Now Standing AQHA Incentive Fund Bay stallion, Grandslam Zippo. Foals are just starting to enter the showring and are flat kneed, lovely movers with gorgeous conformation and quiet dispositions. See him and some of his get on our new improved website.','828-670-5502 ','vadaq@hotmail.com ','Vada & Randy Campbell','','','','www.southerncharmhorses.com ','','337 Billy Cove Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28715 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:26','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7c7f7f02-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Sow True Seed ','Sow True Seed is an open-pollinated/non-hybrid vegetable, herb and flower seed company in Asheville, NC specializing in heirloom, certified organic, and traditional Southern Appalachia varieties. We serves home gardeners, market growers and the seed saving community at large.   The company seeks to promote and foster community sustainability by helping to preserve our shared botanical heritage and seed a new era of sustainable culture and ecological wisdom. We are amassing a unique offering of widely adapted heirloom varieties along with traditional favorites of southern Appalachia and the greater south.   Sow True Seed is committed to the expansion of vibrant, local economies with regional food and seed production as their foundation.','828-254-0708 ','info@sowtrue.com ','Peter Waskiewicz','','Our retail store is open 10-4pm daily. During the spring we maintain Saturday hours from 10-4pm. ','','www.sowtrueseed.com ','','146 Church Street ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28801','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:26','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7c809ffd-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Suzanne\'s Farm and Gardens B&B','Located just minutes from downtown Asheville, our bed and breakfast offers a spacious, quiet, and friendly place to come home to. Relax on the wraparound porch, dip your feet in the creek, or wander the 7 acres where we grow cut flowers and herbs for local markets.  When the weather chills down, come inside and sit by the fire — our 1920s, Arts and Crafts-style house features seven working fireplaces, as well as the beautiful woodwork and high ceilings found in the grand homes of that era.   Our historic farmhouse was once the hub of a large dairy farm just west of Asheville. Later, the house served as a waystation for the railroad depot. Over the years, much of the farm\'s rich creekside bottom land was sold off for commercial, industrial, and residential developments. Our goal is to preserve the remaining farmland as a testament to the area\'s rich agricultural heritage, as well as to provide an oasis for guests, friends, and neighbors, where healthful food and abundant flower gardens nourish body and soul. ','828-670-5248 ','info@suzannesfarm.com ','Suzanne DeJohn','','Please call ahead for B&B reservations and flower and herb availability.','','www.suzannesfarm.com ','','31 Toms Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28715 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:26','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7c81b626-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','The Hop ','Serving Asheville\'s Finest Homemade ice cream for over 30 years! Now serving Asheville\'s first homemade Doggie Ice Cream- The Hop\'s \"Happy Tails\" ice cream for dogs!','828-254-2224 ','hopicecreamcafe@yahoo.com','Ashley Garrison','','','','www.thehopicecreamcafe.com ','','640 Merrimon Ave. Ste. 103 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28804','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:26','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7c829df8-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','The Sunflower Gourmet','We are a mother and daughter home business. I have a consumer sales & marketing background and have always loved to cook. My daughter is very creative and also loves to bake. She created our original citrus vanilla cheesecake and we top it with lemon curd and blueberries. Ashley made the original vanilla citrus cheesecake for friends and business associates and they all said we could make a business by selling this specialty recipe. So we did!  We have started selling to the local tailgate markets and we hope to expand to wholesalers and commercial accounts. We are having a great deal of fun perfecting different cheesecake receipes. We are also famous because our cheesecakes are made with the finest, freshest North Carolina ingredients and are ORGANIC! Each cheesecake is made with love, in small individual batches, a