lture from CCC&TI. He can design a beautiful yard for your home or business.    Starting in October our Pumpkin Patch opens. We offer school or group fild trips during the week and are open to the public on weekends.Our Pumpkin Patch includes a 3 acer corn maze and corral maze, animals,jumper,and hayride. Starting Thanksgiving Day we sale Christmas trees at the farm house. During the summer we have a produce stand opened to the public. We sale anything from watermelons to tomatoes to homemade jelly. ','8282171874','jwfarm.olivia@gmail.com ','Olivia','','Pumpkin Patch: mon-fri: call for reservations Sat: 8am-6pm Sun: 1pm-6pm Christmas Trees: . Monday-Saturday: 8am-8pm Sunday: 1pm-8pm Summer (produce & landscape supplies) Mon-Sat:8am-6pm Closed on Sundays ','','www.johnnywilsonfarm.com ','','2675 Dry Ponds RD ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28630 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:26','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7cb5bebb-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','LuckyEwe Farm','We are a beginning hobby farm that grew out of a tiny dream. Someday we would like to blossom into a place of many dreams,providing the community with food, wool, recreation and education. We are members of the Jacob breders association and have studied extensively to insure healthy, happy sheep live on our little farm.    Our Jacobs are registered breeding stock purchased from a knowledgable breeder with a great reputation. These sheep make great show stock, meat and fiber and are wonderful little self propelled mowers.    We chose Jacob sheep because they are so unique. These sheep are considered endangered and we would like to help preserve this breed. They have a great nature. Jacob sheep are stunning to see. They can have anywhere from 2 to 6 horns. They sport a spotted fleece that is low in lanolin and great for spinners and crafters. The meat is lean and tasty. They are small and easy to care for. And very hardy creatures. It is believed that the jacob sheep is the same breed that Jacob was raising in the Bible. (Gen. 30) Because they are a heritage breed they have a high resistance to parasites and illness. ','','luckyewefarm@gmail.com ','Renee & Mark Clark','','email for directions and to arrange visits: luckyewefarm@gmail.com ','','','','1349 Garden Lane ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','',' 28645 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:26','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7cb6f56e-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Snyder Family Farm  ','We have been eating free range, farm raised meats for over 10 years. We had friends who asked about our meats and we would give them samples. They raved about the differences in quality, smell and especially taste. Our animals are fed only hay and grass. We strive to provide a healthy lifestyle for our children and it starts with your core ingredients in your meal, meat. We believe in living off the land as much as we possibly can to become self sufficient. Call or come by the farm and we will be happy to educate you on the benefits of eating healthier.    We are fully licensed with the state as certified NC state meat handlers. And we use a facility that is USDA inspected. We are braching out to serve local restaurants and businesses interested in offering customers a healthier option. Our strongest partner, Bistro 1-2-7 in Hickory currently features our Filet Mignon, hamburger and italian sausage. Please stop by and taste the difference or visit their website. Our products are also available at The Health Hut in Hickory off of Hwy 127 near Planet Fitness.    We are a small family run operation with our children invloved in the process. They go on egg hunts to find our free range chicken eggs, milk our goats and help with relocating our animals for pasture rota