 45 beautiful acres of rolling hills, farmland and forest with a large creek flowing through. Our farm was the site for the Jenny Lind Iron Forge that operated from 1804 to around 1890. Remnants of the dam, and large pieces of iron slag from the forging process can still be found in the creek. In June 2009, Josh and Dr. Grant quit their day jobs to focus full time on opening their farm to the public, as Catawba County\'s first ever Educational Farm Experience. It had been their goal for many years, but they thought they would have to wait till retirement age to do it full time. The opportunity arose, and they went full steam ahead with their project. Dr. Grant was raised eating homegrown beef and vegetables from her family\'s farm. She realized most children have never tasted \"real\" food that she knew was so wonderful. Being a doctor, she also saw many negative effects that children\'s diets had on their health, and she wanted to do something about it. Dr. Grant has extensive education in health and nutrition, and loves teaching people about the benefits of eating food that comes straight from the local, all-natural farms, and avoiding factory raised, artificial food. Dr. Grant also holds a degree in zoology. She not only teaches children about the animals on the farm, but also the animals that live in the creek and woods that adjoin the farm. Red Wolf Farm is a well-rounded educational experience that you will get nowhere else.    We are not a large \"production\" farm that mass produces one or two main products. Rather, we are trying to live as sustainably as we can by producing as much of our food on our farm as we can. We do not use chemical herbicides or fertilizers. Our animals are hormone and antibiotic free, and do not eat medicated feed. Our goal is to educate kids on how to live sustainably, the science of farming, and how what they eat affects their health. Red Wolf Farm supports the Local Food Movement. We are a Got To Be NC Farm!   We are offering various educational school tours in Fall and Spring.   We are also offering a week-end pumpkin patch.   HE PUMPKIN PATCH INCLUDES:  a pumpkin from the pumpkin patch, hayride, 1 acre corn maze, tractor train rides, hands-on farm animal interactions, playground, giant corn \"swim\" tubs, hay mountain, giant crawl tube, slides, pirate ship, airplane, helicopter, pedal tractors, nature trails to creek, and a picnic barn. Bring your picnic basket.  A Summer Day Camp is being held in June.  We will also host your wedding. ','828-428-1445 ','redwolffarm@att.net ','Josh Grant','','Pumpkin Patch Season: Sept. 26- Nov. 4, Weekdays by Appointment for groups of 20 or more, Open to the Public: Sat. 10am - 5pm, Sun. 11pm - 5pm, Spring School Tours: See Website, Summer Camp: See Website ','','www.redwolffarm.com ','','1797 Water Plant Rd. ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28650 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:26','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7cf8c601-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','River Run Farm ','River Run Farm is a 40 acre operation located in Catawba, N.C. Here we have made a home with our cows, dogs, donkeys and Boer goats. We are a husband and wife team that believes that raising goats is supposed to be fun. We began with a mixed breed 20 years ago and changed to Boers in 2002. We have worked hard and invested lots of money to make sure the quality of our herd improves with each generation of kids. We are really excited about this years group. Our recent reference sires are Royals Top Brass Ennobled and Gateridge Striker Ennobled.   We welcome visitors to our farm and we thank you for visiting our web site. ','','mcauley6784@aol.com ','John Mc Auley','','Call','','www.riverrunfarm.zoomshare.com/ ','','2909 joe johnson rd ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28609 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17: