arch lead no where, so he decided that he could make his own recipe.The result is what we know today as Bama Boy Beef Jerky.    Family and friends have told him for years that he should take his recipe and turn it into a business. In late 2008, both Keith and Annette lost their corporate jobs. The job market search was bleak, so we decided to take that advice and turn Keith\'s hobby into a business to support our family. In 2009, we started that adventure. ','800-384-4816 ','bamaboybeefjerky@gmail.com ','Annette Adair','','Mon - Fri: 6AM - 6PM Eastern Time Sat: 9AM - 5PM Eastern Time Sun: Closed ','','www.bamaboybeefjerky.com ','','5691 Beaver Creek Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27562 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:26','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7d0617fb-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Dunlap Farms L.L.C.  ','Our cattle are home raised with no added hormones given to cattle or added to feed.We make our own feed.Cattle are on grass until one and half years old then grain fed in one acre grasslots.   Our beef is aged 3 weeks, then cut and wrapped in butchers wax paper and finished in brown paper. ','336-301-0253 ','bendunlap@dunlapbeef.com','Ben Dunlap','','Saturday at farmers market,everyday at our farm just call before you come down','','www.dunlapbeef.com ','','4926 Bonlee-Bennett Rd. ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27207 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:26','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7d071432-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Grandview Farms  ','Our beef is raised using only the highest quality non-animal byproduct feed and natural grasses. The beef is dry aged after slaughter for 2 weeks. Afterwhich it is packaged in vacuum sealed bags to preserve its freshness. We use Key 