ounter, Green Door Design/Build, Working Films, Roundtable on Sustainable Biofuels, a Biodiversity project, Vermiculture, Bees, and The Abundance Foundationa€?s new off grid a€?office of the future.','919-533-5181 ','wow@theabundancefoundation.org','Tami Schwerin','','','','theabundancefoundation.org/ ','','P O Box 1113 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27312 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:27','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7d46d5c9-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','The Hosta Farm  ','Duck & Greta have been growing plants and running a nursery and online mailorder business for 16 years. Mike\'s a licensed landscape contractor and certified plantsman and Greta is a teacher and social worker.  We have approximately 20,000 sq ft of growing plants in 8 greenhouses and a 10 bay gutter-connect.   At this time we\'re growing approximately 200 varieties of hostas, 34 varieties of hardy ferns, and several other shade perennials','919-542-0360 ','hostafarm@earthlink.net ','Mike Duckwall','','For the 2006 season, we\'re open 10 am to 5 pm Tuesday through Saturday; closed Sunday and Monday, We\'ll open on April 15th and close on June 15th, During the rest of the summer, we\'re open by appointment only, so call before visiting.','','www.hostafarm.com ','','148 Hadley Mill Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27312 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:27','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7d47f46e-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','The Salvage House','We will be carrying a variety of different wood aging from 50 to 150 years old. This wood has been salvaged from the old unusable homes and out buildings here in Chatham County. Please view our product page to see our latest inventory.Come take a look.    The Salvage House is a new company located in Bonlee NC. Our goal is to supply local craftsman with vintage lumber that is not available in most stores. We will also be carrying doors, windows, cabinets, sinks, and more. ','919.837.2376 ','jeff@thesalvagehouse.com ','Jeff Tooley','','Thursday-Friday 8:00am-5pm, Saturday 8:00am-1200pm','','www.thesalvagehouse.com ','','PO Box 105 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27213 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:27','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7d48f40e-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Yknotfarm  ','We are a small diversified farm that raises grass & forage based livestock to produce quality meats from. We currently have beef cows, broiler chickens, laying hens, ducks, goats, pigs, and turkeys.    All of our animals are treated humanely throughout their stay with us. We provide fresh water at all times and access to the great outdoors as much as possible so they can graze peacefully among our many pastures. We are trying to raise our livestock as natural as possible, whenever possible. Antibiotics are only given if necessary to save their life, and then we ensure a more than required withdrawal time is adhered to before processing.    To help handle the animals in a humane fashion, we do sometimes provide them various grains or livestock feeds so they get used to being handled, or when grass or hay is not readily available. During the winter, we purchase and use only locally processed fescue hay. ','919-837-0131 ','yknotfarm@gmail.com ','Kelly Brott','','Please understand that we are a small farm, so we may not be immediately available to answer your email or phone call, However, we try to check our messages often throughout our work hours of 9am - 9pm and will get back with you as soon as possible','','www.yknotfarm.com ','','PO Box 158/381 Wilson Rd ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27252 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:27','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7d4a384d-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Yknotfarm LLC ','We are located in Chatham County, NC on a beautiful 22-acre property in Goldston, where we currently raise beef cows, broiler chickens, laying hens, pigs, and goats. All of our animals are treated humanely throughout their stay with us. We provide fresh water and as much access to the great outdoors so they can graze peacefully among our many pastures. We are trying to raise our livestock as natural as possible, whenever possible. Antibiotics are only given if necessary to save their life, and then we ensure a more than required withdrawal time is adhered to before processing. We do give our animals various grains and livestock feeds, but mostly just as treats, to help the animals get used to being handled. We find it helps establish a more cooperative relationship between the animals and ourselves. During the winter, we purchase and use locally grown fescue hay.   Because our animals are mainly grass and forage fed, their meat is leaner and healthier for you and will taste as it was meant to be, not artificially flavored by being finished with grain. If you purchase our products and are not satisfied, please contact us as soon as possible so we can correct the situation to the best of our ability. We want all of our first time customers to become loyal customers and we aim to do this through providing outstanding products and customer service. ','919-837-0131 ','yknotfarm@gmail.com ','Kelly A. Brott','','On farm sales available by appointment only, please call 919-837-0131.','','www.yknotfarm.com ','','PO Box 158/381 Wilson Rd ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27252 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:27','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7d4b4fd8-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f7