 support the Southern Kitchen, you support the local community. We have private dining rooms available and also offer off- site catering. Visit us on Facebook or online for more information.   Since 1947, the Southern Kitchen has been a landmark in Whiteville, serving as many different types of food through the years as one could imagine, having been in turn a country restaurant, an Italian restaurant, a Greek restaurant and even a Mexican restaurant.    Today, it is a fine-dining European restaurant and lounge that blends French cooking with Southern flair and an Asian twist. Chef Sokun, who was featured in magazines such as Southern Living, is a French-Cambodian, classically trained, national award-winning chef who will delight the discriminating food lover with her amazing creations and exquisite selections. ','910-640-5055 ','chef@newsouthernkitchen.com','Guillaume Slama','','We serve lunch Tuesday through Friday, from 11 to 2, We serve dinner Thursday through Saturday, from 5 to 9.','','newsouthernkitchen.com ','','606 S Madison St ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28472 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:27','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7d7c7f28-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Strickland\'s Corn Maze  ','Our corn maze was started in 2003 when we stopped growing tobacco. In hopes of another income option we came up with idea of a corn maze. With help from family and friends it has been a success for 6 years.   Maze Designs 2003 Cash Cow 2004 Noah\'s Ark 2005 NC State and Carolina 2006 Pirates 2007 Maltease Cross 2008 FFA/Barn 2009 Elmo.   With agritourism in North Carolina growing, it has also added to our success. We try to provide a clean, downhome,fun enviroment for everyone, young and old. ','910-649-7921 ','stricklandproduce@yahoo.com','Allyson Strickland','','Seasonal-September thru November ','','www.stricklandscornmaz