rganic mushrooms, preserves & jellies, plants, cut or dried flowers, we are committed to the best in taste quality & service.   Our products include : *The best jellies & preserves you\'ve ever tasted...all made one small batch at a time--fig, pear, muscadine & scuppernong grape and pepper. *Fresh Shiitake mushrooms...delicious and nutritious! *Mushroom Logs...grow you own Shiitakes. Makes a great gift. *Plants & cut flowers...order ahead for your special event. *Fresh (in season) pears, figs, muscadine & scuppernong grapes, pecans & black walnuts. ','336-853-8834 ','brendasue@sandycreekfarm150.com','Brenda or John','','Flexible hours....call 336-853-8834 for specifics.','','www.sandycreekfarm150.com ','','3160 S Hwy 150 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27295','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:28','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7dcfec28-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','The Barbecue Festival  ','Let\'s Celebrate! Lexington and Davidson County residents can once again look forward to hosting the annual Barbecue Festival. The 27th Annual Barbecue Festival is set for Saturday, October 23, 2010 in Uptown Lexington. The month of October has been declared Barbecue Month,a month full of activities including the Tour de Pig Cycling event, 5K Hawg Run, Pepsi Pig Tale Writing Competition, Golf Tournament, Tennis Tournament, Hawg Shoot Air Rifle Tournament, and many other exciting events.   Six stages of entertainment showcase local and national artist. The festival is for all ages and includes a special section of rides and games for children, the Barbecue Carnival & Family Area. Famous \"Lexington Style\" Barbecue is served out of three main tents, one at the square and the other two on the North & South ends of the festival.    The Barbecue Festival is especially proud to have been named one of the Top Ten Food Festivals in America by Travel & Leisure Magazine. This year the festival was again selected as one of the Southeast Tourism Society???s Top 20 Events for the month of October. The festival was also nominated by Congressman Mel Watt and selected by a committee of the Library of Congress for inclusion in their Local Legacies Program to celebrate the library???s 200th anniversary. The Barbecue Festival has received more than 40 awards from the North Carolina Association of Festivals and Events through their Excellence Awards program. The festival has also received an award from the International Association of Festivals and Events through their Pinnacle Awards program. Most recently the festival received four excellence awards during the North Carolina Association of Festivals & Events Association???s annual conference including the prestigious Festival of the Year award. We invite everyone to come to Uptown Lexington where we provide our visitors with the finest exhibits, the most exciting entertainment, and of course, the best barbecue in the world. Please mark your calendar and join festival sponsors BB&T and The Dispatch for the best day in Lexington as we celebrate the 26th Annual Barbecue Festival, Saturday, October 24, 2009 ','336-956-1880 ','info@barbecuefestival.com ','Stephanie K. Saintsing','','FREE ADMISSION...The hours of the Barbecue Festival are from 8:30AM until 6:00PM.','','www.barbecuefestival.com ','','P.O. Box 1642 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27293','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:28','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7dd1243e-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Three Hat Mountain Strawberry Farm  ','We offer fresh strawberries, either pick your own or we pick. We have a general store for browsing antiques, purchasing local honey (when available), or bird house gourds. ','336-474-0993 ','marie_bruff@ncsu.edu ','Leonard or Marie Bruff','','Late April til Mid June 7 am - 7 pm Monday thru Saturday ','','','','1031 Lopp Drive ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27292 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:28','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7dd2aff7-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','TX Enterprises  ','We are self sufficient Beef Cattle Operation. Our operation is mainly commercial cattle, but with a few Quality Registered Purebred Simmental and Red Angus. The majority of the commercial herd is operated under a two breed rotation of Simmental and Red Angus. However we do have a select group of F1 females that are bred to shorthorn for club calves. Our goal with our entire herd is to produce calm, flashy, productive cattle that will work for a variety of different options. Most of our replacement heifers are raised here on the farm and A.I. bred using any of the three breeds depending on the female. We are continually striving to improve our herd by selecting only quality cattle to stay in our herd.    We grow all of our feed and feed out our steers for freezer beef on corn silage and barley, corn ration. Our calving season is varied to meet demands of customers for beef. None of the steers are implanted with hormones and minimal medications are used. In addition we have now added some heritage breed chickens (free range). The breed we are concentrating on is the Light Brahma. We have a modest supply of eggs. Currently (December) we are getting about 4 dozen a week.    Quality heifers and bulls are for sale at all times. ','336-769-3856 ','cthoma11@bellsouth.net ','Charlie Thomas','','8am-10pm by appointment only ','','www.showsteers.com/TX%20Enterprises/index.htm ','','4728 Gumtree Rd ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','',' 27107 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:28','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7dd57dfe-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Vogler Swiss Heritage Farm','Vogler Swiss Heritage Farm is the home of River Saane Goats, registered with the American Dairy Goat Association, also other Swiss goat breeds. With a Swiss theme, the farm plans to open for agritourism in 2011, and offer educational and historical programming for children and adults with an emphasis on the German/Swiss traditions from the early settlers of the area who immigrated here in the 1700\'s. Also on display is the National Bird of Switzerland, a rare type of poultry, and other animals reminiscent of the period. Danish and European ferrets as were originally used for fur and hunting are on display and available for purchase as well.   Vogler Swiss Heritage Farm also has German angora and Swiss Fox rabbits and guinea pigs, also called cavies. Cavies are used around the raised bed gardens to trim grass, in a fenced area, as they were used in barnyards of yesteryear. Our heritage gardens include heirloom varieties of plants and herbs, and some very old flowering plants collected from old homesteads and cemeteries. Our own herbs and goat milk are used to make our soaps, available for sale. Fur fiber and yarn are also available for purchase, as are feathers for crafts and fly fishing.    School groups are encouraged to come by the farm and visit Tuesday to Friday beginning August 1st. A small fee is charged. The educational program is conducted by a history major, with costumed staff, and takes about two hours. Allow three hours if a photo session and lunch at the picnic area is planned. Children learn about their regional heritage, have fun activities appropriate for the season, and have hands on activities. Listen to the old story of the 3 Billy Goats gruff as the goats walk over the bridge, and watch out for the Troll! Stay and have a fun lunch before departing, and shop at the gift store for that perfect souvenior. Have photos taken of your group to be emailed to the teacher/group leader. Perfect for day care centers, classes K-6, special needs groups, scout and church groups. ','3366443509','kathryn.jordan@ymail.com ','Kathryn Jordan','','10 am to 2 pm Tues-Friday beginning August 1st, Saturday 2-4 pm, closed Sunday and Monday, Other hours by appointment. ','','vshf.9f.com ','','763 Shady Hanes Rd ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27295','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:28','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7dd71cd3-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Calahaln Farms','The farm land has been in the family for generations. We at Calahaln Farms want to be good stewards, and keep the property in good condition for the community today and tomorrow. We operate a produce stand at 510 Calahaln Rd. Also, we will be selling at several of the farmer\'s markets located in Mocksville, Farmington, and possibly Winston-Salem.    During the growing seasons, we have pre-picked and pick your own strawberries, Blueberries, and Blackberries.    There has been a demand for a community supported agriculture program. Therefore, we have complied with the wishes of the community and we began providing produce in May of 2009. ','336-909-2240 ','calahalnfarm@gmail.com ','David Anderson','','We are at the farm Monday through Saturday 8:00 until 5:00.','','','','510 Calahaln Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27028 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:28','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7dd8019f-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','County Line Farms  ','All cattle are raised and fed on our farm, or by neighboring farmers that follow the same practices we do. We do not use antibiotics or growth hormones on our cattle. Cattle are primarily grass fed, supplemented with minerals and g