e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27028 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:28','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7de9e5dc-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Garden Gate Vineyards  ','We produce home-style fruit wines and pottery. We us no pesticides on our grapes. We serve tastings of 13 different kinds of wines in our shop for FREE!! We also have a Sangria made from our Strawberry wine and a Hot Wassail from our Muscadine.   We sale by the gallon in Sep. our Muscadine and Scupperdines. We also give free access to our crusher. We also sell muscadine and blackberry plants. Sonya does all her own hand-made pottery which have fairies, angels, frogs and leaves adorning them.   We now have an Arbor for you to bring a picnic basket and enjoy outside or a party room inside for your enjoyment. ','336-751-3794 ','gardengate@yadtel.net ','sonya & Bob Whitaker','','Wed. thru Sat. 12:00 noon till 5p.m. Sunday 1:00 till 5p.m, All other times by appointment.','','www.GardenGateVineyards.com ','','261 Scenic Drive ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27028 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:28','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7deb1c06-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Half Pint Farm Suffolks','We have been raising show and breeding sheep for the past 15 years with an emphasis on quality, heatlhy and sound sheep, but due to health reasons we are no longer raising lambs.   Many of our sheep have won numerous championships in many different states and we are very proud of them all and wish everyone continued success with our bloodlines. ','336-492-5962 ','halfpintfarm@yadtel.net ','Rick or Judy Wilson','','Anytime by appointment. ','','','','161 Macy Langston Lane ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27028 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:28','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7debf9f9-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Hauser Creek Farm','We are a small, second-generation family farm, growing 6 varieties of lavender on land where beef cattle were once pastured. We also grow native grasses and wildflowers for use in floral arrangements.    In 2006 we placed a conservation easement on 9 acres along Hauser Creek, which we proudly preserve. ','3367063235','alethea@northstate.net ','Alethea Segal','','By appointment only ','','www.hausercreekfarm.com ','','898 Spillman Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27028 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:28','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7ded5585-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Hilltop Orchard  ','We have been growing peaches for over 30 years. My dad planted our first orchard around 1977. It was a beautiful orchard that consisted of 500 trees. About 5 years ago we realized we needed to re-plant and start a new orchard because the old trees were beyond their prime. We re-planted our new orchard and incorporated bare ground strips to aid in frost protection. We also had to build a fence around our new orchard to prevent deer from damaging the trees. We have grown corn now for over 15 years. Many people have become dependent on our corn due to the fact of how hard it is to grow corn in the garden successfully. With the increase in the deer population, this can be a tough task. We grow about 4-5 acres of silver queen corn and begin selling it by the dozen as soon as it matures. All of our corn is picked fresh daily in the mornings. Occasionally we have to go back and pick more throughout the morning if we sell out. We try to pick all of our corn in the mornings because it sustains the fresh quality better. If you pick corn in the afternoon after the temperature has climbed, the corn will not stay fresh very long after it\'s been pulled.    We offer a pick your own operation with peaches. We also have peaches already picked as well. However, during corn harvesting, peaches will mainly be pick your own only due to most of our labor being focused on pulling corn. All of our corn is pre-picked. ','336-492-7246 ','davidkoontz874@yahoo.com','David Koontz','','Monday - Friday 8AM-6PM Saturday 8AM- 7 PM Sunday 12-6 ','','','','555 Ijames Church Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27028 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:28','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7dee6f63-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Ijames Heritage Farm','Our farm has been in the family for over 200 years. We provide educational tours. Also have lots of animals to enjoy. ','336-492-7529 ','toddreba367s@yadtel.net ','Reba McInnis','','Call for appointment. ','','','','367 Sheffield Rd ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27028 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:28','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7def486c-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Janel Hensley / Broker  ','Janel Hensley specializes in Horse Farms, Large Acreage and Luxury Homes. Owner and Breeder of American Warmblood horses. Stays current on most up to date technology in the business of real estate to provide the best professional service to all customers and clients.   Can provide information on farms and financing any where in the world. Call me first to send you on the right path to your real estate investment.   Visit me at www.janelhensley.com or cbtriad.com/janelhensley, or JanelHensley1.homelog.com ','336-998-1153 ','janelhensley ','Janel Hensley','','8:30 to 5 Monday through Friday 9 to 4 Saturday, 2 to 4 Sunday',''