sult is a smooth, well-aerated, surface. The litter saver easily connects to your tractor and is quality-crafted by Priefert to provide years of trouble-free service with minimum maintenance. ','(336) 403-6652 ','johnnyunnecessary@hotmail.com','R.D. Wright','','Flexible Hours by Appointment','','www.littersaver.com ','','PO Box 2073 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27006 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:28','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7df27924-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Providence Farm Ornamentals  ','Providence Farm Ornamentals grafts Japanese Maples, and Dwarf conifers with a focus on many rare or hard to find varieties. We currently have over 120 Japanese maple varieties in production.    Dwarf pines are our primary focus at this time, with many varieties that are suitable for creating Japanese gardens. We also graft small numbers of spruce, and fir. All of our ornamental firs are grafted on to Abies firma, a suitable rootstock for southern climates. ','336-998-9758 ','cw@yadtel.net ','Carl Weston','','We are open by appointment only ','','','','182 Providence Trail ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27028 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:28','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7df3d743-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','RayLen Vineyards & Winery','Until 1998, when Joe and Joyce Neely purchased the land, RayLen Vineyards & Winery functioned as a dairy farm for nearly a century. Today, the rolling hills and winding drive romance our guests as they drive through 35,000 European varietal grape vines. The distinctive cupola roof top of RayLen Vineyards & Winery is a beacon for the southern portion of the Yadkin Valley Appellation. Travelers from the highway and wanderers from the surrounding country roads are drawn to the tasting room to discover a new experience. Loyal customers return for the lush vista and a reliable favorite of RayLen\'s award-winning wines.    When Vintner Steve Shepard first began making wines for RayLen Vineyards & Winery in 2000, only 2500 combined cases of Chardonnay, South Mountain\'s Vineyard Chardonnay, Merlot, Carolinius, and Shiraz were produced. Today, production is over 10,000 cases of 16 different wines, including Pinot Grigio, Viognier, Riesling, Cabernet Franc, Pale Red, and the infamous Category 5 Bordeaux blend. Awarded \"Best in Show\" in the Mid-Atlantic Wine Competition for the 2005 vintage, the Category 5 remains RayLen\'s most popular red wine. Named after the biggest and boldest hurricane, this Cabernet blend is powerful.    The Yadkin Gold, a white wine blend of Riesling, Chardonnay, and Viognier, was the first wine to carry the Yadkin Valley Appellation label. It remains RayLen\'s most underestimated and underappreciated white wine, although USA Today and Southern Living have picked the Yadkin Gold as RayLen\'s best white wine. Among RayLen\'s newest wines are the Eagle\'s Select, Cabernet Sauvignon, and Sparkling Brut. The Eagle\'s Select is a Meritage blend aged for 18 months in new French oak; it\'s a bold wine with longevity. The Cabernet Sauvignon is aromatic with notes of leather, tobacco, and black cherry. A refreshing sparkling wine, the Brut has tiny bubbles, good acidity, and balance. ','336-998-3100 ','noblegrapes@raylenvineyards.com','Steve Shepard, VP/GM','','Monday through Saturday, 11:00 - 6:00 pm ','','www.raylenvineyards.com ','','3577 HWY 158 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27028 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:28','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7df4a3d6-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','ROBIN\'S NEST FARM  ','','336 998-2829 ','lundytrk@statesville.net ','S