00c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','E Industries, Inc.','E Industries, Inc. is a small-scale livestock producer that specializes in meat goats. Our goal here at EII is to produce the highest quality meat goats possible. All of our animals are on a veterinarian directed vaccination and medication program that ensures high quality meat production and the healthiest animals possible.   EII has been investigating new markets for our product over the past years. One such market that showed promise was selling pre-packaged meat directly to restaurants and stores, instead of live animals; however, there are very few slaughter houses in North Carolina that have the willingness or capacity to slaughter goats.    For this reason, EII has decided to investigate the possibility of operating a regional buying station dedicated to goats. This station would pay a premium price for local goats. Animals would be graded based on USDA selections and weights, and a price would be assigned accordingly. The main benefit of selling animals at this station, rather than an auction, is that the price is predetermined. The prices would be available prior to the sale date, so producers will know exactly what price they will receive. ','910-381-0292 ','johndailgarner@gmail.com','John Dail Garner','','We are still a family farming operation, so our hours of operation vary from day to day, The best option is to call or e-mail using the contact information listed above. ','','www.ncagr.com/gl.htm ','','PO Box 1124 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28349 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:28','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7dffefc4-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','First Prize Produce  ','The Best Trees Enterprise is located on a small farm in eastern North Carolina. We specialize in the production of Floriculture, Sorghum, Sugar Cane and vegetables. Three different verities of sweet potatoes are available.    The environmental benefits of trees change carbon dioxide into increased oxygen levels, a natural buffer, reducing high winds, erosion, flood damage, clean pollutants from the air, provide shade, food and shelter for wildlife species and improve water quality. A natural landscape of native plants is low maintenance, beautiful and cost effective. Trees can increase real estate values 5-25%. The greatest value is providing an everlasting benefit for our children and future generations.    The following species are available: Black Locust, Eastern Red Cedars, Loblolly pine, Sycamore, Roughleaf Dogwood, Baldy Cypress, and Water Tupelo. ','910 296-2007 ','bestle413@hotmail.com ','Arthur L. Best','','8:00 AM - 6:00 PM','','www.thebesttrees.net ','','324 Wesley Chapel Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28349 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:28','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7e00f49a-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Old Courthouse Nursery, LLC','Old Courthouse Nursery was founded in May of 2000 to produce liner material for the wholesale nursery trade. Our customers are primarily other nurseries. We produce woody ornamentals (shrubs) and trees in containers. Container sizes range in size from 2\" rooted cutting plugs to 30 gallon pots.    The nursery is owned by Jeffrey Matthews, grandson of O. S Carroll, founder of Carroll\'s Foods. The nursery is on property that was originally the Turkey Research Farm for Carroll\'s Foods.    The name Old Courthouse Nursery was chosen because the site of the Duplin County Courthouse (1754 to 1784) is on the property. In 1784 Sampson County was created from the western portion of Duplin County. The present Sampson/Duplin County line bisects the nursery. ','910-293-9374 ','oldcourthousenursery@embarqmail.com','Bob McLeod','','Mon-Friday