 of some rather heavy agricultural authorities. But the owner, Jack Kroustalis, was not discouraged by the naysayers. He began planting vinifera varieties that are used to produce fine California and French wines. Chardonnay, Cabernet Sauvignon, Riesling, Merlot, and Sauvignon Blanc are now thriving along the banks of the Yadkin.    As the vines flourished, more acreage was planted and, by 1986, Kroustalis found he had a 70-ton grape harvest, which was sold to other wineries. Westbend became a bonded winery in 1988. The first Westbend wines were released in June 1990. Today, Westbend wines are winning national and international awards. Gold medals have been awarded to the Barrel Fermented Chardonnay, the Cabernet Sauvignon, the Merlot, the Chambourcin, the Sauvignon Blanc, the Riesling, and the Seyval Blanc. ','336-945-5032 ','westbendvineyards@att.net','Lillian Kroustalis','','Tasting & Wines Sales: Tuesday - Saturday ~ 11:00 - 6:00 Sunday ~ 1:00 - 6:00 Tours of Winery: Saturday ~ 1:00, 2:30 & 4:00 Sunday ~ 2:00 & 3:30 ','','www.westbendvineyards.com ','','5394 Williams Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27023 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:29','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7e8f85df-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Windmill Acres Farm','','336-970-1655 ','jcarpenter@alphagraphics.com ','Wes Carpenter','','','','','','1522 Jasper Lane ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27127 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:29','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7e90d41f-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Woosley Farm  ','Wayne and Riely Woosley have taught public school in Forsyth and Stokes Counties for 25 years. Between them they have taught all ages, from Kindergarten to seniors in high school. Throughout their teaching careers, class fieldtrips to the farm have been favorite experiences of their students.    With Riely\'s retirement in 2003, this exciting opportunity is offered to all area students. A unique combination of 18th century living history tours combined with a representation of the rapidly vanishing small farm in the Forsyth County countryside becomes a memorable experience for students of all ages.    The Woosley farm began in the latter 1800s when Uria Woosley moved from the Arcadia area of Davidson County and purchased 300 acres along the Yadkin River and Bashavia Creek in western Forsyth County. John, one of Uria\'s three sons, inherited the northern third of the original tract. He and his father, built the house which stands today. Each generation made changes and improvements to the structure. Addiitions include electricity, water, plumbing, weather siding, bathrooms, closets, and central heating; none of which were in the original house. ','(336) 945-2471 ','wayne@woosleyfarm.com ','Wayne or Riely Woosley','','By Appointment','','www.woosleyfarm.com ','','2780 Woosley Rd. ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27040 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:29','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7e91fc39-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','BOBBEES BOTTLING INC  ','WE ARE A USDA APPROVED PLANT THAT WILL TAKE YOU RECIPE AND ORDER INGREDIENTS, CHOP IT, MIX IT, COOK IT, TEST IT, BOTTLE IT, CODE IT, LABEL IT, BOX IT, SHRINK IT, STORE IT AND SHIP IT FOR YOU.   WE BOTTLE SIZES FROM 5 OZ BOTTLES TO 55 GAL DRUMS. GIVE US A CALL AND COME FOR A VISIT, RECEIVE A NEW CUSTOMER PACKET TO HELP GET STARTED IN YOUR SAUCE BUSINESS.   WE DO WET PRODUCTS SUCH AS BBQ SAUCES, SALAD DRESSINGS, HOT SAUCES BLOODY MARY MIXES, STEAK SAUCES ETC. ALSO DRY RUBS IN BOTTLES OR BAGS. ','919-496-4286 ','COPACKER0@CS.COM ','BOBBIE BATCHELOR','','WE ARE OPEN FROM 8:30AM TIL