king family farm, located just east of the Triangle in Franklin County. We grow strawberries in the spring, blueberries and blackberries in the summer, and pumpkins in the fall.   Visitors enjoy hayrides, the Back Forty, our family entertainment area of the farm, pick your own strawberries, blueberries, blackberries,and more! ','919-496-3076 ','fun@vollmerfarm.com ','Mary Vollmer','','The Farm Market and Homemade Ice Cream Shop are open Mon.-Sat. 9am-7pm, Sun. 12pm-7pm, The Back Forty will be open from September 25 - October 31, 2010, Back Forty Weekends Only Sat. 11am-8pm, Sun. 1pm-6pm. ','','www.vollmerfarm.com ','','677 NC Hwy 98E ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27508 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:29','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7e9896c0-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Wendy L. Perry, Inc. ','A native of central North Carolina, Home Economist Wendy Perry\'s professional journey has taken her along many fun and interesting pathways in the culinary world. A Marketing Home Economist, she is a food stylist for Our State Magazine. At every turn in the road, she has found herself dabbling in some sort of food adventure, each one fun and unique... and inspiring! From event planning to training folks to be personal chefs, she has played with food in all sorts of ways, including recipe development. Yet as the granddaughter of farming families and farmland owner, she has always held a special place in her heart for the farmers and their families who till the soil and tend their herd, yet are SO under-appreciated! She is now sowing seed in another direction and offering the skills she has cultivated for over three decades to those growing our dee-lish foods! From marketing plan assistance to web pages and social media, marketing mistress Wendy is your gal! She can also represent your product at expos and coordinate special events.