c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Cheesecakes by Alex  ','First, let me say - I love to cook and especially eat . I grew up in the restaurant business and it has always been my first love. This past year, my mother-in-law, who lives with us, asked me to make a cheesecake. Well, I, being the good son-in-law (ha! ha!), made a recipe out of a book. All during the process, I had a taste in mind for the way this cake should turn out - I couldn’t wait to taste it. When I did, however, I was truly disappointed in both the taste and the texture. The challenge had begun.    Over the next few months, all I could think about was the taste I had in mind. I changed this and changed that and baked and baked until I finally got the taste and texture I wanted. When we finally tasted the final recipe, we knew this was it! Good thing; I think my wife and mother-in-law were ready to run me out if I baked one more cheesecake for them to try! I then began to bake some for friends and family and I always received the same response. Soon, this obsession / hobby grew out of my kitchen and we set up shop.    We now have sixteen flavors and bake all the time. I love to see the reaction of people trying these cakes for the first time; it really brings me a lot of joy. So, take my advice. Try one. Try several! These are some of the best cheesecakes you\'ll ever taste. ','336-273-0970 ','alex@cheesecakesbyalex.com ','Alex Amoroso','','Expanded Hours Monday Closed Tuesday - Wednesday: 7:30am - 8pm Thursday & Friday: 7:30am - 11pm Saturday: 10am - 11pm Sunday: 10am - 6pm Also, see us at the Greensboro Farmers\' Curb Market on Yanceyville Street, Saturday mornings from 6am - 12pm ','','www.cheesecakesbyalex.com ','','315 South Elm St. ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27401 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:30','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7f1aad62-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Circle N Ranch  ','Circle N Ranch was started in 1989 in Climax, NC with only three horses. We still have our original three horses, plus nine more horses, ponies and a paint donkey named Cracker Jack. They are not only our business, but also our pets. Each one has a lifetime home and are never sold or traded. Every year all ponies are vet checked and annually vaccinated including rabies. We provide clean healthy, beautiful ponies with over 20 years combined experience doing pony rides. They are also the same ponies that our grandkids ride. All of our tack and equipment is well maintained. From the truck and trailers that haul the ponies to our final clean-up when we leave, Circle N Ranch takes a great deal of pride and enjoyment in what we do. As owners we are at every event overseeing each detail, we never just send hired help by themselves.     We do not try to be all things to all people; Circle N Ranch specializes in only one area - PONIES! They range in size from small to large. No scale is used to weigh children unlike some of our competitors who have 100 pound weight limits which could embarrass or hurt a child\'s feelings. With our years of experience we try to judge which pony is suitable for each child, and seldom do we have a child too large for one of our ponies. For a memorable and enjoyable experience at a clean, insured, and well maintained facility with a family atmosphere - come to Circle N Ranch. If you ever have the opportunity to watch a child pet or ride a pony, you will see that money can indeed buy happiness!        Circle N Ranch is fully insured. If your event requires additional insurance coverage and/or they request to be added to our insurance that can be done. There is an additional cost for this coverage and must be paid in advance. A minimum of two business days is needed to obtain added coverage from our insurance carrier.       A new 40 ft. x 60 ft. red barn was added recently, complete with a large heated/cooled party room decorated western style. Have your picture taken in our authentic restored stagecoach or 1800 era original Conestoga covered wagon. Ponies can also be brought to your location for events. We offer individual hand lead pony rides and a custom made pony carousel for larger events.       The Circle N Ranch pony carousel is a great way to attract attention and generate crowds of adults and children to your event. While our prices are very competitive with other pony businesses - remember you get what you pay for. Should you find a lower price for the same services, feel free to contact us. Most of the time we will match or beat our competitor\'s prices. Our goal is to make your special day/event a cherished memory for each person in attendance. For birthday parties, school fundraisers, church festivals. Bible Schools, daycares, fairs, corporate picnics, family reunions, etc. think Circle N Ranch ponies. Two large ponds with paddle boats and docks are also on our property   Be sure to ask for Domino our trick pony to perform at your party! He can pick birthday child out of a crowd and also guess child\'s age, plus other tricks.    Have your next party/event with us! You bring the kids and we will provide the ponies, party room and memories for a lifetime. When you think PONIES, think Circle N Ranch.','336.674.3966 ','CircleNRanchNC@aol.com ','Keith & Linda Newman','','Open Year Round ','','CircleNRanch.com ','','6517 Monnett Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27233 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:30','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7f1b8d5a-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Cummings Farm  ','We are a small family farm raising cattle on pastureland , and dry hay produced on the farm. Our cattle are free of growth stimulants, antibiotics, and pestisides. The catttle do receive needed vacinations and vete