ation to further up on Hemphill Road. The white house on the knoll as you come in to the property on Boyd Farm Rd. is the Boyd Homestead, built in the early 1900\'s, where nine children were raised. The youngest daughter, Betty continues to occupy the homeplace now. The Boyd family raised cattle, and had crops of tobacco, corn, and potatoes---David Boyd was known fondly as \"Tater Dave\" ---he lived to be 100 and died in 1970. The eldest son, Dock Boyd now deceased was the father of Dan Boyd who is presently the owner of 130 acres of the family land which includes the Christmas tree farm and the cabin rentals and the log home he shares with his wife Betsy. Dan always had fond memories of his grandparents farm and the reunions held by the pond every summer, and purchased this land in 1972 from two of his uncles and his father who had inherited this part of the farm allowing them to continue the cattle farming on the property if they would permit Dan and Betsy to build a log cabin on the property. Dan and Betsy built their home in 1974, and also a log outbuilding adjacent to their house, used for storage. They found the hand hewn cabins for their home in Spring Creek, Madison County, N.C, Dandridge, Tn near Lake Douglas, Hurricane section of \"Twelve Mile Strip\" and the Hemphill Community of Haywood County,N.C. When Uncle David, and Uncle Bob and his father gave up farming, Dan had a vision for his retirement from dentistry. He would grow Christmas Trees and restore antique log cabins on the property. In 1984 the first Fraser Fir Christmas Tree was planted, and other seedlings were planted each year afterwardsa€|.and seven years later that first crop was harvested. Our Choose N Cut began is 1999. Some of the trees are now 25 yrs. old. In 1989 the first authentic log cabin used previously for storage was restored and became a rental cabin, The Shelton Laurel Cabin, the first of now seven cabins that have been restored as Boyd Mountain Log Cabins. The Shelton Laurel Cabin originally stood in Madison County, NC in the Shelton Laurel Community, the Meadow Fork Cabin restored in 1991 originally stood in the Meadow Fork community of Madison County, NC, the Millstone Cabin restored in 1993 was originally a cantilevered barn from Arden, NC, the Long Branch Cabin restored in 1995 was from Whittier, NC near the Great Smoky Mountains National Park, the Cosby Cabin and the Little Cosby Cabin originally from Cosby, Tn, were connected by a dogtrot and restored in 1997, and the newest old cabin, Clinch Valley was relocated to Boyd Mountain in 2008 from the Clinch River Valley area of northeast Tn, near Ky,and Va . In 1994, Dan retired from his dental practice in Waynesville and devoted his time to growing trees,cabin rentals and restoration and operating two car washes in Waynesville. Dan and Betsy\'s son David, who owns Boyds Landscaping and Hydroseeding lives in the large scribed log home on the top, and now manages the Christmas Tree Farm. Dan and Betsy\'s daughter, Mary Alice lives in Charlotte and works at UNCC and is a partner in the Boyd Mountain Log Cabins and Christmas Tree Farm Family Limited Partnership.   A wonderful family experience walking through the maincured fields & selecting your own trees! Free refreshments & bathrooms available. ','828-926-8888 ','davidhboyd@yahoo.com ','David Boyd','','November 20th - December 20th, Daily 9 AM-5 PM, Cash or Check with vaild ID only. ','','boydmountain.com ','','143 Boyd Farm Rd ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28785 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:31','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7f7a8de4-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Cagles\'s Livestock Exchange  ','We are a Family Owned and Operated Business. The small animal auction was started on April 1st 2000. The Public brings their small livestock to be sold just before sale time on Saturday. Farm related merchadise sells first usally within an hour, then the sheep and goats, the poultry and small animals are the last to sell.    We have over two thousand registered buyers. We are NC licensed and bonded. ','828-454-5501 ','cagles@charter.net ','Mike Cagle','','Saturday at 8 am, We can be reached at any time by phone. ','','','','96 Traders Pl. ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28786','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:31','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('7f7bfc84-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','EMERALD GATE FARM','This 3 bedroom, 3 bath vacation rental is also available as a 2 bedroom B&B. It is located on 13 acres of beautiful rolling mountain property with so much to do you\'ll never want to leave. We have ponds, gardens, creeks, springs and mountain forest hiking trails for exploration. We are \"horse friendly\" with a trail leading right into the Park. Black raspberries and blackberries surround our pasture for picking plus apple, peach, cherry, elderberry and black walnut trees. Our fully equipped kitchen: 2 ovens, 6 gas burner cook top, microwave, trash compactor & ice making fridge make it easy to use our home grown produce. Our 3 trout ponds have resident ducks, geese and trout that our guests are welcome to fish for. Our hearty home cooked breakfast specials will last B&B visitors all day.    This estate is very private and secluded yet we are close to the small towns of Waynesville and Maggie Valley where there is antiquing, river rafting, restaurants and Lake Junuluska. Only 3 miles from route 40 which will take you to Asheville 31 miles to the east. We are close to 3 different entrance points for the Blue Ridge Parkway and very close to the Smokey Mountain National Park, Cataloochie Valley where Elk can be seen every afternoon and the Cherokee Reservation with Harrah’s Casino. At 3600 ft it is usually cool enough to open th