goldenseal.com ','','300 Indigo Bunting Lane ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28753 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:32','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('8080fd55-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Rogue Harbor Farm  ','Since 1978, we\'ve had the pleasure of growing high-quality Fraser Fir Christmas Trees. We have always enjoyed fashioning the fragrant greenery into beautiful decorations made-to-order for our customers. Our farming practices are Certified Organic through Clemson University\'s Department of Plant Industries, farm certification # 11017.     Rogue Harbor Farm Fraser Fir products have always been fresh, natural, even, full, and wonderfully fragrant. This year we\'re offering decorated and undecorated wreaths in two sizes for mail-order, or for pick-up at our farm in Madison County.    We also make centerpieces and other greenery items for mail order or on-farm pick up. We\'ll be happy to email you an order form, or please call with any questions.     For mail order customers we\'ll enclose a gift card with your personalized message, if you wish. We ship our products by USPS priority mail, guaranteeing a 2-3 day shipping time to any destination in the continental U.S. We ship Mondays through Thursdays (except Thanksgiving day) beginning November 27 through December 14. ','(828)689-4586 ','linda@rogueharborfarm.com','Linda or Aubrey Raper','','We begin our greenery season a week before Thanksgiving, and are available through Dec. 14, It\'s best to call or email to place your order and arrange a time to come out, During the Christmas season, we\'re often blessed with snow-covered ground and we\'re ','','www.rogueharborfarm.com ','','701 Peters Cove Rd. ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28753 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:32','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('8081f520-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Zimmerman\'s Berry Farm ','Zimmerman\'s Berry Farm is a family owned and operated u-pick berry farm. We\'re located in the western North Carolina mountains about 45 minutes north of Asheville.     Picking season begins June 15 with black and red raspberries first, then blackberries. Red raspberries are ready to pick beginning in August. Call or e-mail for current availability.     We have clean, mowed, level picking rows. Picking baskets and take home baskets are provided. Children are especially welcome. Homemade jams and jellies are always available as well as craft items. ','8286562056','pam@zimmermansberryfarm.com ','Pamela Zimmerman','','9:00 am til 2:00 pm, seven days a week June 15 until frost. ','','www.zimmermansberryfarm.com ','','2260 Revere Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28753 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:32','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('80835b1c-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Appalachian Vacations and Adventures','We\'re a place like none other, alive with possibilities for your next romantic weekend getaway, family vacation, or trip with the friends! Come to Madison County, North Carolina for a nature lovers paradise, a mecca for outdoor education, perfect for those seeking a change from the ordinary.     Appalachian Vacations and Adventures specializes in preparing area visitors for a wonderful visit to the mountains with a perfect combination of fun and relaxation ~we have cabins, vacation houses, cottages and Inns (small town and farm settings) plus, white water rafting, horseback riding, workshops, farm tours, spa soaks, massage therapy, farmers markets, and wonderful dining choices. Let us help you create a perfect itinerary! Visit us on line for descriptions and reservation information. ','888-404-9622 ','ncvalley@verizon.net ','Deborah DeLisle','','Monday - Friday 10 am - 5 pm *Closed on Weekends','','www.ncvalley.com ','','PO Box 252 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28743 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:32','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('80849ab2-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Bailey Mountain Produce  ','Bailey Mountain Produce is a family owned produce stand.   Come see our selection of fresh produce.    Friendly staff to help with all your produce needs.  Be sure to visit us while here in the mountains of North Carolina!','(828)689-4821 ','kimrobin@madison.main.nc.us','Kim Robinson','','9:00am until 7:00pm Mon-Sat, 1:00pm until 5:00pm Sundays','','','','7174 nc hwy 213 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28754 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:32','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('80860dd4-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Briar Rose Farm','A visit to Briar Rose Farm is more than a place to spend the night. Experience waking up to roosters welcoming the morning sun. Make your breakfast using the farm fresh eggs left in your refrigerator, along with the loaf of homemade bread left by your hosts, Tom and Judie. Greet the cool mountain morning by having breakfast on the wide private front porch. Hike to the firetower 2 miles up the road and take in the 360 degree view. Sample the produce from our organic garden. Perhaps you\'d like to meet the goats, see how we turn trees into lumber on our sawmill, collect eggs, or see how we grow hydroponic lettuce. After an evening campfire, enjoy the hottub and the millions of stars visible in our rural still dark night skies.     Families, Honeymooners intergenerational families on vaction, and couples all seem to find the farm a special place. We enjoy welcoming folks back year after year.     Why not create some memories for your family?     Our new Log Cabin on 80 private acres will be opening soon! Just for two, this log cabin will offer quiet solitude, a warm light uniquely decorated cabin with porches and decks made from the timber of the farm and hand hewn mortise and tendon joinery. It is truly a special place to enjoy the mountains. ','828 622-7329 ','info@briarrosefarm.com ','Tom and Judie','','The Farm Cabins are open year round. ','','www.briarroserosefarm.com ','','91 Duckett Top Tower Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28743 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:32','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('8086f454-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Dancing Sun Cabins NC','We provide two small romantic one bedroom cabins, and a three bedroom vacation home on a 74 acre farm.     We invite you to come and stay in beautiful mountain accomadations to get away and hike, birdwatch, find rare unique plants and tranquility.     A short walk takes you to the AT. Bring your horses. ','828-622-9569 ','tom@dancingsuncabins.com ','Tom Gahagan','','daily ','','www.dancingsuncabins.com ','','2441 roaring fork road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28743 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:32','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('80883ce7-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Eagle Feather Organic Farm  ','Nestled in the Blue Ridge Mountains bordering the Pisgah National Forest in Marshall, NC, lays a haven for herbalist, naturalist, and seekers of agri-tourism excellence.     Eagle Feather Organic Farm, owned and operated by Robert Eidus, is home to the North Carolina Ginseng and Goldenseal Co - www.NCGoldseal.com     This land has been designated as a Native Botanical Sancturay by the United Plant Savers. Eagle Feather Farm is a haven for rare, threatened and endangered plant species and a showplace for the conservation and cultivation of medicinal plants. ','(828) 649-3536 ','robert@ncgoldenseal.com ','Robert Eidus','','Call us for seasonal hours of operation 828.649.3536 ','','www.ncgoldenseal.com ','','300 Indigo Bunting Lane ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28753 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:32','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('8089387c-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Fowler Farms Sporting Clays and Game Preserve ','Fowler Farms Sporting Clays, \"Golf with a Shotgun\", and Game Preserve is located on the old family tobacco and cattle farm in the beautiful valley of the Spring Creek Community, Madison County.     Sporting Clays is for teaching shooting skills, but also as a tournament sport and one of the major recreational target shooting sports.     Quail and pheasant hunts are available by appointment ','(828)622-0177 ','mrfowler54@msn.com ','Mary Ruth Fowler','','Sporting Clays are open year round from 9 AM until dusk, Thursday, Friday and Saturday and may be open other days except Sunday by appointment, The hunting preserve is open October 1 until March 31, Monday thru Saturday by appointment only.','','www.fowlerfarmssportingclays.com ','','490 Fowler Farm Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28743 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:32','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('808aa02d-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Geowild Farm ','We believe that the diversity of plant life in Western North Carolina must be preserved. We help landowners to identify, protect, and install native plants on their property.     We grow organically, to encourage high pollination rates in both our native plants and our seasonal starts. Our fresh vegetables and herbs are chosen for their heirloom qualities and flavor.     Look for Geowild plants at the Marshall Tailgate Market on the Island-Sundays 12-4 starting in Mid-April. Also look for our booth at the Asheville Herb Festival at WNC Farmers Market-first weekend in May. ','828-658-3904 ','redclay_7777@yahoo.com ','Nancy Odell','','Call for appointment ','','','','228 White Oak Rdg ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28787 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:32','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('808bfb8a-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Sweet Betty Bee\'s Honey and Hive ','We are proud to offer you Sweet Betty Bee\'s Honey and Hive products. Naturally produced in western North Carolina without pesticides or antibiotics, our honey is unheated and unfiltered, leaving intact its amazing nutritional composition.     We see our apiaries as a partnership with the bees and with the whole of Mother Nature. While proximity to conventional farming methods prevents us from claiming our honey is organic (bees will forage miles from home), we practice organic principles to the greatest extent possible by finding alternatives to pesticides and antibiotics. Additionally, we do not feed corn syrup or sugar to our bees. Honey and pollen are beesa€? natural diet. Why give them anything else?     Lyne is a practicing Nurse and offers Apitherapy services including bee venom therapy. ','','ed@sweetbettybees.com ','Ed Vendely','','Please contact us through our website, www.sweetbettybees.com, We can arrange to meet with you by appointment. ','','www.sweetbettybees.com ','','640 North Fork Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28753 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:32','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('808ceb5c-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Carolina Country Fresh Market  ','Scattered Acres Inc. is a family run business. The company has three areas of focus: Row crop farming being primary, Carolina Country Fresh Market, and the \"Berry Patch\". Our farm is run by Kenneth H. Roberson, Sr. and operated by two of his sons, Ken and Henry, and two of his grandsons, Josh and Kip. The Farm raises cotton, peanuts, wheat, soybeans, and tobacco and has done so for over 30 years. We also bale wheat straw and peanut hay for sale. Ken is responsible for the Berry Patch.','252-795-2926 ','info@carolinacountryfresh.com','Josh Roberson','','Carolina Country Fresh: M-Sat 8:30am-7pm and Sun 10am-6pm(April thru December) Berry Patch: 7-5 Mon-Sat. (In season) ','','www.carolinacountryfresh.com ','','P.O. Box 477 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27871 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:32','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('808e427f-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Mackey\'s Ferry Peanuts','We entreat each one of you to visit our store in Jamesville and to try our delicious samples. For those of you with a penchant for sweets, we offer the most delicate hand-stretched Peanut Brittle, Grandma\'s homemade Molasses Cookies, a variety of chocolate confections, and our new Peanut Butter Cookies, made with our very own homemade Peanut Butter. Avid peanut snackers will enjoy our Blister-Fried peanuts, French-Fried Redskin peanuts, spicy hot \'Flame-Thrower\' peanuts, old-fashioned Parched peanuts, unsalted Dry-Roasted peanuts, or our classic Sugar-Coated peanuts. For a distinctive gift from rural North Carolina, consider our rustic wooden gift boxes, featuring an assortment of our products and a decorative printed lid.','888.637.6887 ','support@mfpnuts.com ','Sharon Smith','','Mon - Sat, 9am to 6pm. Sun, 10:30am to 5:00 pm.','','www.mfpnuts.com ','','30871 US Hwy 64 E ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27846 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:32','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('808faba4-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Mackey\'s Ferry Peanuts and Gifts ','Since 1983, Mackey\'s Ferry Peanuts has used the best peanuts grown in Eastern North Carolina to create premiun peanut products for peanut lovers everywhere. We entreat each one of you to visit our store in Jamesville and to try our delicious samples. For those of you with a penchant for sweets, we offer the most delicate hand-stretched Peanut Brittle, homemade Molasses Cookies (my Grandma\'s recipe), a variety of chocolate confections (Butternut Crunch being a favorite), and Peanut Butter Cookies, made with our very own fresh ground special recipe Peanut Butters.    Avid peanut snackers will enjoy our Blister-Fried peanuts, French Fried Redskin peanuts, spicy hot Flame-Thrower peanuts, unsalted all natural Plain roasted peanuts,or our classic Sugar-Coated peanuts.    For a distinctive gift from rural North Carolina, consider our unique rustic gift boxes, featuring and assortment of our products and decorative printed lid with a NC theme. We offer custom designed lids for your corporate needs as well as a variety of cardstock giftboxes to suit any price range. Your visits are always welcome and appreciated in our store. Sharon and Chris Smith, Owners of Mackey\'s Ferry Peanuts and Gifts. ','252 793 2993 ','sharon@mfpnuts.com ','Sharon Smith','','M-Sat 9:00 to 6:00 and Sunday 11:00 to 6:00 ','','www.mfpnuts.com ','','30871 US Hwy 64 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27846 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:32','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('809112ae-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Big Mill Bed and Breakfast','Located in the tranquil North Carolina countryside Big Mill Bed & Breakfast sits amid acres of landscaped grounds overlooking a three-acre lake. Halfway between Raleigh and North Carolinaa€?s Outer Banks, Big Mill is just minutes from major highways. The main house has seen several renovations; original farm buildings from days past are still in residence and have been given new life as part of the Bed and Breakfast.    My folks moved to this farm in 1922 and I was born in this house. After 20 years away, including roaming the world in a sailboat, I returned. This is still a working farm, and all original buildings are here. The Packhouse has been renovated into suites: the Corn Crib, The Pack House Suite and the Mule Shed. We also have two rooms in the main house.\r\n','2527928787','info@bigmill.com ','Chloe G. Tuttle','','9 a.m. to 9 p.m every day','','http://www.BigMill.com ','','1607 Big Mill Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27892 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:32','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('80921aca-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Griffin\'s A-MAZE-ing Corn Maze  ','We are entering into a brand new adventure. This 7-acre corn maze is guaranteed to keep you moving for at least at hour.    This year\'s design is the Fireman\'s Maltese Cross, which is the fireman\'s badge.    The Maltese Cross is your symbol of protection. It means that the fireman who wears this cross is willing to lay down his life for you just as the crusaders sacrificed their lives for their fellow man so many years ago. The Maltese Cross is a fireman\'s badge of honor, signifying that he works in courage - a ladder rung away from death. ','252-792-4811 ','tourism@visitmartincounty.com','Kim Griffin','','Opening August 25th. Tours Thursday - Sunday through Halloween 4:00pm - 8:00pm, Last group at 8:00 pm so bring your flashlight. School and other groups by appointment, Call 252-792-4811 or 252-809-2034.','','www.visitmartincounty.com ','','4975 Fire Dept. Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27892 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:32','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('80937add-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Kingsway Farms','We are a small 60 acre farm in upper Martin County that specializes in Grass fed, rotational grazed beef, chicken, geese, meat goat and lamb. In addition, we sell fresh brown farm eggs collected daily and refrigerated. We never spray our pastures with insecticides or use hormones on any of our livestock. We pride ourselves in the healthy and humane care of our livestock. Our goal is to produce natural, healthy quality meats and vegetables that we would be proud to serve our own families.     We raise pastured poultry through a rotational grazing system with portable roosting houses and collect our fresh eggs daily from our portable hen houses. We also have pasture raised goose for sale as well as occasional 4H wethers and does. We also raise Boer meat goats for breeding stock, 4H projects and meat. We are currently adding Dorper sheep, and Hereford Grass Fed beef to our rotational grazing pastures. In the spring we have fresh, naturally grown strawberries, herbs, and fresh vegetables.     In season we have a small plot of totally natural strawberries that we sell picked to order. We also have seasonal vegetables, herbs and will be adding additional products in 2010. ','252-798-4118 ','kingswayfarms@yahoo.com ','Deborah D. Smith','','Please call for winter hours and information, Eggs are for sale daily. ','','','','3201 Bennett Rd. ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27857 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:32','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('8094f8df-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','RHIANNON FARM ','Family owned & operated. Animals come first! We want to remain small. Animals handled daily by owner. Farm visits by appointment please. Veterinarian references if needed.    We have Arabian & Standardbred horses,chickens,geese,cats,dogs,& alpacas (both breeding & non- breeding). Our animals are mostly pets for both adult & children\'s enjoyment!    I have had, and still do have, wonderful mentors soooo I plan to \"PASS IT ON\". ','(252) 792-7192 ','horse1@wildblue.net ','CARROLL ETHERIDGE','','Please call (252)792-7192 to schedule a time to visit. ','','horsenutrition101.com/index_farm2.htm ','','3705 JOE MOBLEY ROAD ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27892 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:32','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('80985ca3-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','HIDDEN COVE CHOOSE & CUT CHRISTMAS TREES  ','We have Fraser Fir Christmas Trees up to fourteen (14) feet tall. You may tag a tree for later pickup or we will cut your tree and you may take it when you visit our farm. We have cross and candy cane wreaths along with 10, 12, 14, 16, 20, and 24 inch circle wreaths. Larger circle wreaths are available if ordered at least one week in advance.      Our trees are priced at $4.00 per foot for trees to seven (7) feet tall. Taller trees are on an ascending scale that reaches $6.00 per foot for trees ten (10) feet or taller. Wreaths with bows are priced at $1.00 per inch or without bow, subtract $2.00 per wreath.     We also deliver trees in the Marion area for a fee of $3.00 per tree for trees less than eight (8) feet and $5.00 per tree for trees eight (8) feet or larger. ','828-776-0913 ','hiddencove@charter.net ','William Chapman','','We will be open from Friday, November 18th through Monday, December 19th, Hours on Saturdays, Sundays, and the Friday after Thanksgiving will be from 9:00 AM until 5:30 PM, All other weekday hours will be from 10:00 AM until 5:30 PM. ','','','','Hwy. 221 North ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28752 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:32','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('8099ec1a-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Historic Orchard at Altapass','Nearly 100 years old, the Historic Orchard at Altapass is the last operating apple orchard on the Blue Ridge Parkway.     A family operation since 1995, the Orchard was purchased as a preservation project to assure that this breathtaking spot would be here for generations to come. Much to our surprise, we found we had purchased an historical treasure as well.     Admission is free and worth every penny! Enjoy free live music, saving monarch butterflies, choosing ice cream flavors, sampling Orchard-made fudge, swapping tall tales or just relaxing in our spectacular scenery. ','828 765-9531 ','carsonw@bellsouth.net ','Bill Carson','','From May 19-October, Mon, Wed-Sat, 10-6. Sundays 12-6, Closed Tuesdays until October when The Orchard is open every day, 10-6.','','altapassorchard.com ','','PO Box 245 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28749','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:32','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('809b3d7a-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Hollifield Farm  ','Hollifield Farm is a small farm operated by Kip and Dawn Hollifield, McDowell county natives, who inherited their love of gardening from their long-standing North Carolina mountain family heritage.     Our farm is in northern McDowell County in the Woodlawn/Turkey Cove Community. We are situated just below the Blue Ridge escarpment about 5 minutes from the Parkway, with views of Mt. Mitchell to the west and Linville Mountain to the east.    We specialize in Mirai sweet corn. Other vegetables are sometimes available. Fresh Cut Flowers are also grown. ','828-756-4992 ','kipholl@charter.net ','Kip & Dawn Hollifield','','We are mainly a harvest-to-order farm, Please call ahead for harvest availability and to place orders, schedule pick-ups or learn about u-pick opportunities. ','','http://hollifieldfarm.blogspot.com/ ','','35 NC 226A ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28752 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:32','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('809d25ed-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Listening Eagle Farm  ','We began our adventure with goats six years ago. Since that time we have shown our girls with great success. Most of the LaMancha kids win a dry leg their first season out and both the Nubians and LaManchas are consistent winners as they mature. Our bucks have also held their own in the show ring with our little Dante\' taking GCH over his sire and grandsire.    The girls will start competing in one day milk tests for their stars in June 2005. We are confident they will all succeed as average production for the LaManchas is 12 pounds daily. The Nubians are close behind at an average of 10 pounds of milk produced daily.     The kids will begin arriving in mid-January 2005. I experimented with breeding my young does to a Nigerian Dwarf buck so there will be mini-Munchies available also. Prices range from $50 for the mini\'s to $250 for kids from our most successful breedings. Discounts to those who take kids early so I don\'t have to bottle feed them. Special consideration will be given to 4-H members. All kids are raised CAE prevention. ','828-756-7187 ','jubaltwo@yahoo.com ','Sherry Williams','','','','','','1211 Hicks Chapel Loop ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28752 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:32','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('809f4632-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','South Creek Vineyards & Winery  ','Come & taste our award winning Bordeaux Style Wines at our 100 year old Italian Renaissance Farmhouse. As you enter the grounds, take in the surrounding nature complimented by our grazing horses. Meander through the vineyards. Tour the winery where the barrels rest. Shop our unique artisan retail room. Unwind and enjoy the serenity while you sip wine at our large outdoor living area. We believe you will enjoy our world class wines and be charmed by the uncompromising beauty of our estate and vineyards.     We are a boutique winery combining meticulous winemaking practices with a genuine love of the land and support for the North Carolina Wine Community. Our Bordeaux style wines include Chardonnay, Cabernet Sauvignon, Merlot, Cabernet Franc and our Signature Blend, Maestro.     We welcome you to visit our winery where southern hospitality exists, and taking time to relax while enjoying an excellent wine is what we all imagine it should be. ','828-652-5729 ','mary.rowley@southcreekwinery.com ','Jim or Mary Rowley','','South Creek has seasonal hours, Please call 828-652-5729 or go to our website www,southcreekwinery.com for details. ','','www.southcreekwinery.com ','','2240 S. Creek Rd.','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28761 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:32','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('80a0570b-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','The Colonial Organic Gardens & Polo Estate ','','8283018244','the-colonial@luxurydossier.com','Lynn Morris Khan','','','','','','PO Box 1860 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28762 ','','','','2012-