ident. The state historic site commemorates significant events in the Polk administration: the Mexican-American War, settlement of the Oregon boundary dispute, and the annexation of California. Reconstructions of typical homestead buildings—a log house, separate kitchen, and barn—are authentically furnished. The visitor center features a film on Polk\'s life and exhibits on his family and tumultous presidency. ','704-889-7145 ','polk@ncmail.net ','Scott Warren','','April 1 - October 31: Tuesday-Saturday 9:00am-5:00pm, November 1-March 31: Tuesday-Saturday 10:00am - 4:00pm','','www.polk.nchistoricsites.org ','','12031 Lancaster Highway ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28134 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:33','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('80c74e7f-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Ratcliffe on The Green  ','Critically aclaimed Fine Dining Restaurant That soupports Local Farmers by buying 80% to 90% of all of its products from North Carolina Farmers','704-358-9898 ','chefmark_hibbs@yahoo.com','Mark Hibbs','','Lunch Monday - Friday 11:30 - 2:00 Dinner Monday - Saturday 5:00 - 10:00, Closed on Sunday','','www.ratcliffeonthegreen.com ','','435 South Tryon Street #100 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28202 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:33','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('80c83aff-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Ross Farms','Ross Farms is a nursery that specializes in growing perennials. We have a large selection of perennials such as hosta, dicentra, phlox, fern, iris, dianthus and much more.     Ross Farms also grows steppable groundcovers and some blooming deciduous shrubs and ornamental grasses. Here at Ross Farms you will find some very old fashion and very new perennials varieties and some natives.     We invite you to come shop at our nursery. The best perennial selection can be found from March thru November. Our perennials can help you add color to your landscape and attract bees, hummingbirds and butterflies. ','704-543-6388 ','rossfarms@bellsouth.net ','Claudia Ross','','We are open Monday thru Friday from 8 am to 4 pm, We do not accept credit cards, Cash or checks are accepted.','','','','9424 Community House Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28277 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:33','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('80c9c041-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Rural Hill  ','Rural Hill is the historic homestead of Major John Davidson, signer of the Mecklenburg Declaration of Independence and a patriot in the American Revolution. John was a cousin of General William Lee Davidson, who encamped with his men at Rural Hill before the Battle of Cowan\'s Ford (February 1, 1781). Lord Cornwallis, with his 1500 men, began to cross the Catawba River at Cowan\'s Ford on the morning of February 1st only to find General Davidson and 150 men waiting. In the ensuing firefight, 100 British troops lost their lives; three Americans fell, including General Davidson.     Rural Hill is a restoration in progress. It is a designated historic landmark and is on the North Carolina study list for listing in the National Register of Historic Places. The volunteers of the Catawba Valley Scottish Society have undertaken to preserve the Davidson homesite and the lands (265 acres) and buildings surrounding it. Also on the property are a circa 1890 one room schoolhouse, plantation house ruins, smoke house, ash house, granary, a 20th century farm house and the Rural Hill Burying Ground.     Rural Hill is also a working farm, with a herd of Scottish Highland cattle. Characterized by their picturesque horns and shaggy long hair, the Highland breed are noted for being disease resistant and able to adapt to extremes in temperature and climate. ','704-875-3113 ','edmclean@ruralhill.net ','Ed McLean','','Hours: 10:00 - 4:00 Monday through Saturday and by appointment, We are open for special events on weekends ','','www.ruralhill.net ','','POBox 1009 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28070 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:33','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('80cbb27d-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','The Butter Bean Village Market, LLC  ','At The Butter Bean Village Market, we are local and we sell local food and products. Our mission is to support local folks and promote healthy food. Come in and visit our little eclectic market. We have the staples for your everyday needs along with one-of-a-kind pottery and fresh-baked bread from a local bakery. We have everything from local ice cream and honey to fresh fruits and vegetables. Come in and enjoy our storea€|brimming with old time country charm.     Local Treats a€￠Tonya€?s Famous Ice Cream a€￠Larrya€?s Organic Coffee a€￠Renn Bee Honey, Salisbury, NC a€￠Goat Milk Soap a€￠Local Poultry a€￠Eggs a€￠Pasta a€￠Hoop Cheese a€￠Sausage and Liver Mush a€￠N.C. Wines a€￠Savory Moments a€￠Conrad & Hinkle Pimento Cheese, Lexington, NC      Our History After purchasing the property from the estate of a Mr. Pigg in the 1990s, our current owner, Mrs. Joni Wellman, and her husband decided that the location would be a great place to start an a€?Old Time General Storea€? and thus The Butter Bean Village Market was born. The building itself has quite a colorful history. Originally built by Mr. Pigg as a gas station in the 1950s that closed in 1972 after an unsuccessful robbery attempt, it has since been leased to several entrepreneurs. The store has been a pool hall, a bar, and a gril ','704-992-1851 ','butterbeanmarket@yahoo.com','Joni Wellman','','M