,'7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28749 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:33','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('80d4740a-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Blue Ridge Soap Shed  ','Now offering 130 varieties, The Blue Ridge Soap Shed makes the largest variety of handmade soap in the United States, and its soapmaking operation is open to the public. Come see soap made and select your favorite soaps in the retail shop.     Visitors are welcome to view whatever aspect of the soapmaking process is being conducted at the time of their visit, from the mixing of oils and lye, to the molds used to make each batch and the cutters used to prepare each bar they take home. Photos, antique soap-making equipment and sample raw materials to see, smell and touch are on display to entertain and educate. Anyone who specifically wants to see a batch of soap made from start to finish at the time of their visit should check the soapmaking schedule or call ahead. Demonstrations are led by Dr. Tim Tyndall, a retired Science professor, who also provides historical information and an overview of different soap varieties while making a batch of soap. There is no admission fee for our regularly scheduled demonstrations. Your purchase of soap in our shop following the demonstrations is always appreciated, but never required.    Home school and public school groups, 4-H and scout groups, tour buses and other large groups are asked to schedule their attendance at on-site soapmaking demonstrations in advance so that special arrangements can be made ??? including scheduling ???Dr. T??? to provide the demonstration and instruction, with an emphasis on the math and science of soapmaking. Soapmaking Demonstrations are often provided on Saturdays and Sundays, begin at 2:00 pm. Demonstrations last approximately 15-20 minutes. First time visitors should keep in mind that our soapmaking demonstrations are conducted in a covered outdoor pavilion that is not enclosed on the sides, so please dress accordingly. Full demonstrations are not held in the event of bad weather. If no demonstration is held, an overview of soapmaking steps and equipment is provided inside the store. ','(828)765-6001 ','info@soapshed.com ','Dr. Tim Tyndall','','We are a seasonal business open daily 10-5 from early May through October 31st, and weekends in November and December','','www.soapshed.com ','','179 Meadow View Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28777','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:33','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('80d55ab5-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Byrd Charolais','We try to raise top quality Charolais genetics that will work for you on grass.We have used several well established, proven blood lines from top cattle producers throughout the USA.     Cattle are sold by the pound. We believe our bulls and females put more weight on quicker with less feed than most other breeds. ','828-688-2068 ','mark.byrd2@verizon.net ','Mark Byrd','','6:00 a.m.- 11:00 p.m.','','','','6081 hwy. 226n. ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28705 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:33','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('80d6e044-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Falls Creek Farms','We are a family operated Bio-secure farm, raising trout, livestock, vegetables, herbs, and more, using low impact, conservative methods to bring our customers great tasting, farm fresh products, often at great savings over grocery store prices.     We pride ourselves in growing custom ordered produce, livestock, and trout. We offer both organic and conventional vegetables, grass fed hormone free cattle, and chemical free live trout