, and restaurant with banquet room facilities. We host weddings, family reunions, birthday parties, Christmas parties, as well as bus tour groups.     Hayrides are a big part of our farming operation. In the Fall there are weekend hayrides for pumpkin picking, a haunted Halloween hayride(sponsored by our local fire department) and a Christmas Light Show (lighted night time hayride) beginning Thanksgiving night. ','(910) 324-3422 ','mikesfarm@always-online.com ','Theresa','','Our farm is open year round with extended holiday hours, The gift shop/bakery is open Thursday-Saturday 10:00 am - 8:00 pm, Sunday 12:00 - 3:00 pm. Restaurant hours are Thursday - Saturday 4:30 pm - 8:00 pm and Sunday 12:00 - 3:00 pm, Call for more inform','','www.mikesfarm.com ','','1600 Haw Branch Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28518 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:34','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('815e4cd5-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Royall Commercial Contractors  ','Royall Commercial Contractors is a full-service contractor specializing in metal building packages and turn-key erected projects. Serving North and South Carolina, Georgia, and Virginia. Call Today! Royall Commercial Contractors For All your Building Needs! Our Portfolio Creswell Trenton Wilmington Hampstead Wake Forest Cape Cartaret Wilson Knightdale Faison Carports, Garages, Boat Covers, Farm Equipment On your level land.     Royall Commercial Contractors, Inc. PO Box 715 Swansboro, NC 28584 ','(910) 326-5700 ','jroyall@ec.rr.com ','John Royall','','','','www.royallcommercialcontractors.com ','','PO Box 715 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28584','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:34','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('815fd7a6-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','The Wyatt Ranch ~ Saddle Horses & Mini Cattle  ','We are proud to announce that the Wyatt Ranch has relocated to a larger 30 acre farm nestled in the fields of Maple Hill NC, conveniently close to Jacksonville, Wilmington, MCAS New River, MCB Camp LeJeune and all of eastern NC! We offer gaited horse evaluations, transport, leasing, short term board, and many flashy, smooth and colorful gaited horses for sale! On occasion we have non-gaited horses for sale as well. Check in to see whats at the farm! We are VERY excited and hope to get you GOING GAITED soon!      We are a small, family run operation that takes pride in quality over quantity. Horses are our passion, NOT our livelyhood. Our sale horses are ridden, handled daily and evaluated by us, and we expose them to as many environments as possible to give you a realistic idea of the horses you are considering. Great disposition and NATURAL gaiting ability are our main objectives, and we specialize in selling you your next partner, not JUST a horse!      About the owner: Liz has been a horse lover since birth, and has been riding since age 5, most of that being self- taught in the school of hard knocks with some great practical and natural teachers along the way. Over the years she has tried her hand at hunters, jumpers, gaming, barrels and gaited horse showing and despite great success, she has always found the most enjoyment while trail riding on her gaited horses. Liz loves to show traditional trotting horse lovers how versatile and pleasurable gaited horses can be, as well as re-mount her fellow gaited horse lovers with new partners. She continues to push the envelope and shows her gaited horses in events ranging from a rated gaited shows to barrels, extreme trail challenges, team penning and trick training, usually with the same horses doing them all! She beleives that you CAN have a truly versatile horse with a cadillac ride! ','(910) 389-4027 ','Ponygirl1978@hotmail.com ','Liz & Will Wyatt','','Call For Appointment ','','www.wyattranchhorses.com ','','Angola Area ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28454 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:34','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('816135bd-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Avillion Farm  ','Avillion Farm was established in 1995 in the beautiful piedmont area of North Carolina. In the heart of the rapidly growing Research Triangle, we raise shetland sheep, angora goats, and angora rabbits for their fiber - wool, mohair and angora, respectively. We are pleased to offer sound healthy sheep, goats and rabbits for sale as breeding stock or fiber pets.      I have found few activities as satisfying as spinning the wool from my own animals into yarns that I can then sell directly or make into unique accessories and gift items. I learned to felt in 1999 and this has offered yet another creative use for our fibers. Felting is the process by which protein animal fibers are made into a non-woven fabric, unlike other fabrics which are made from spun yarns. When wool fibers are subjected to heat, pressure, agitation, moisture and soap, they bond together. The felt produced can be made into toys, accessories, clothing and rugs. ','(919) 563-0439 ','avillionfarm@avillionfarm.com','Elaina M. Kenyon','','By Appointment ','','www.avillionfarm.com ','','4737 Shanklins Dead End Rd ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27243 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:34','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('81620831-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Bart\'s Old North State','Bart\'s Old North State has been providing people all over the state of North Carolina with \"Traditional North Carolina Barbecue\" since 2001. We are now commercially bottling our original sauce that is designed to be a perfect blend of both Eastern and Western style N.C. Sauces. ','307-272-7935 ','bartsbarbecue@gmail.com ','Michael Hernandez','','','','www.bartsoldnorthstate.com ','','PO BOX 9163 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28515 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:34','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('81635a8d-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Busy Bee Apiaries','We became a commercial operation in 1996 and have 600 plus hives of bees used to pollinate crops throughout North Carolina      The honey is produced from many nectar sorces in North Carolina. These include: tulip popular, blueberry, gallberry, tupelo, sourwood, clover, and a mixture labled wildflower.     Our honey is considered a raw honey due to minimal filtration and low heat used during extraction and bottling. ','(919)942-2006 ','busybeeofnc@bellsouth.net ','Jack Tapp','','Monday - Friday 9:00 am to 5:00 pm Saturday - 9:00 am to 2:00 pm','','','','1201 New Hope Ch. Rd. ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28516','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:34','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('8164b450-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Cackalacky, Inc.','CACAKALACKY! As featured on Food Network\'s Rachael Ray Special, The Washington Post, The History Channel\'s \"Ameraican Eats,\" Public Radio International\'s \"MarketPlace,\" ABC\'s \"The Tony Danza Show\" - and beyond!      CACKALACKY FUN FACT: Made with sweet potatoes and red wine, every bottle of Cackalacky is packed with more all-natural ingredients than the leading national hot sauce, ketchup, and mustard brands combined. It\'s true! Tell your friends! ','','','Cackalacky Jack','','24/7/365 Cackalacky never sleeps! ','','www.CACKALACKY.com ','','P.O. Box 4901 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-