fied crop and livestock farm in North Carolina and Beverly was on a dairy farm in Florida. After spending the first couple years of married life in the foothills of NC, they decided to move back to Ritchiea€?s home farm. With the plan to raise their own family with the traditions and values which were instilled in them, they began farming. Along with their children, they now make the fourth and fifth generations to work the soil on their Northern Orange County farm.      Five and a half years after the move home, they are ready to provide farm fresh products direct to the consumer. Beginning with berries and beef, the possibilities are endless. Watch for new products as they continue on their journey. ','919-949-8157 ','info@doublercattleservices.com ','Ritchie & Beverly Roberts','','8 a.m. - 7 p.m. Monday thru Saturday of Strawberry season, CLOSED SUNDAY Hours for grass-fed beef sales will be posted on our website when meat is available, Cattle sales by appointment. ','','doublercattleservices.com ','','701 Ollie\'s Lane ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27278 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:34','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('816bcab0-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Garland Truffles  ','In business since 1979, Garland Truffles is the oldest and first successful grower of truffles in the Western Hemisphere. It is the only nursery in the United States that has grown and sold trees that are in production. Elusive for centuries, cultivating truffles, the gourmet delicacy of France, Italy and Spain, can now be achieved in selected areas around the United States. Large profits can be made on relatively few acres. Mushroom growing experience is not required to grow this crop, however, intensive gardening or farm experience is recommended. We welcome you to our web site, with its valuable truffle cultivation information. Contact us for additional information and questions regarding the suitability of your site.     We are not a retail facility. Tours are $300 for up to two people and last about four hours. Other fees for consultation can be found on our website. ','919-732-3041 ','betty@garlandtruffles.com','Betty Garland','','Tuesday through Friday, 9 AM to 5 PM Tours are usually on Saturdays ','','www.garlandtruffles.com ','','3020 Ode Turner Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27278 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:34','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('816d3131-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Long Haven Corriedales  ','We have raised Certified Corriedale Lamb naturally for almost 20 years, using sustainable farming practices with no growth hormones or animal byproducts. We carry 7 cuts of vacuum packed frozen lamb, boxed for your freezer or for gifts.    Our lambs are certified to be Corriedale lambs to insure you are going to get that Corriedale texture and taste in every purchase of Long Haven Premium Corriedale Lamb.    We also carry wool filled bedding items, yarns, Lamb Skin Pelts, and Pet Food and Treats. All created from the Corriedales raised on our farm. ',' (919)967-5496 ','Donna@longhaven.com ','Donna Long','','Farmer\'s Market: 0700AM-Noon Saturdays, At the Farm: By Appointment Only','','www.longhaven.com ','','2911 Meacham Rd. ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28516','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:34','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('816ec92d-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Maple View Agricultural Center','Welcome! Maple View Agricultural Center is an Agritourism facility, designed to encourage both children and adults to learn about agricultural life through hands on experience. MVAC strives to educate visitors about the benefits of sustainable agriculture and farm life. Strong agricultural philosophies are the foundation for our educational programs. The 6,000 sq. ft. facility offers a gathering area capable of accommodating up to 120 individuals. MVAC features four interactive learning labs, providing the perfect opportunity for students to use all of their senses through hands-on education.     Maple View Agricultural Center is an Agritourism facility designed by educators to teach children about agriculture in relation to the North Carolina Standard Course of Study in Science. Our center opened its doors in April of 2009. Since our opening we have served public schools, private, homeschoolers, and preschool groups. The groups are offered Maple View Milk and Maple View Ice Cream as an option on their tour. Our facility can accommodate up to 120 students by grade level at once.      Weekends at MVAC are a fun retreat for the whole family. Come visit our barnyard, enjoy the hayride, relax in our picnic area, explore the working garden, and play on our brand new playground. The MVAC barnyard is chock full of animal friends to meet. See Sassy our miniature donkey and her foal. From our Nubian and Dwarf Nigerian goats to Guapo, our handsome llama, you can experience the fun of watching the animals play and interact. Watch as our Animal Superintendent feeds our hungry animals. ',' 919-942-6122 ','nussin@bellsouth.net ','Allison Nichols','','Our hours are seasonal, We will be open weekends September and October, Please check the website for hours, Groups are scheduled weekdays, Call to schedule a group tour 919-942-6122 ','','mapleviewagcenter.com ','','3501 Dairyland Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27278 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:34','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('81704c87-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Maple View Farm Milk  ','Imagine fresh, locally produced milk available to you in returnable glass bottles. Our milk is produced by cows at Maple View Farm and bottled at our processing plant on the farm. We never have and never will use artifical growth hormones on our cows. Only the milk produced by the Maple View Herd is processed by Maple View Farm Milk Co. The plant manager, Roger Nutter pledges to you fresh, wholesome, deliciously refreshing milk.     Maple View Farm Milk Company is located in Orange County, North Carolina, just northwest of Chapel Hill. We raise our own crops for our cows. During the various seasons of the year, our cows eat hay, corn, silage, grass, or a combination of them all. We also grind our own grain to make sure the combiation of grains, minerals, and vitamins is a perfect complement to the grass or silage our cows are currently eating. We do this so that our cows will produce milk to their maximum potential naturally without the use of any synthetic hormone.     Maple View Farm, a grade \"A\" milk producer since 1922, moved to Orange County in 1963 after selling a five generation dairy farm in Corinna, Maine. Maple View Farm Milk Company is committed to having the freshest milk available to you at all times. ','919-933-3600 ','muffin@mapleviewfarm.com','Muffin Brosig','','Ice Cream Store hours are seasonal, Call for current hours 919-960-5535 ','','www.mapleviewfarm.com ','','3109 Dairyland Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27278 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:34','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('8171de22-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Maple View Ice Cream','Maple View Ice Cream was built overlooking Maple View Farm. A long front porch with 25 rocking chairs faces west. A great place to sit, eat ice cream and watch the sun set. Up on the hill we have 10 picnic tables and a large field. Several times a year we put a round bale there for children to play on. We have opened 2 other locations-1 in Hillsborough at Hampton Pointe and 1 in Carrboro on Weaver Street.     Maple View Ice Cream opened January 1, 2001. We opened with 1 5 gallon batch freezer and soon purchased a 10 gallon batch freezer. All of our ice cream is made in these 2 freezers so we can guarentee the quality of homemade ice cream. We offer a full service ice cream facility, serving scoops, shakes, floats, malts, sundaes and banana splits made with a whole banana. To go, we offer cakes in three sizes, pints - several flavors, 1/2 gallons in Vanilla, Chocolate, Butter Pecan, Cookies & Cream and Chocolate Chip Cookie Dough.     We make our ice cream on site buying our mix from Maple View Farm Milk Company. Our cows have never been given artifical homones and never will. It is fun and easy to create flavors. We currently have about 50. We have seasonal flavors and 12 flavors we offer all the time, plus 4 flavors we feature every month. Maple View Ice Cream offers a $5.00 Gift Certificate that is a great way to show appreciation to that special friend, relative or professional. ','919-960-5535 ','muffin@mapleviewfarm.com ','Muffin Brosig','','Hours are seasonal, Call for current hours 919-960-5535 ','','www.mapleviewfarm.com ','','6900 Rocky Ridge Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27278 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:34','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('8173506e-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','McAdams Farm','McAdams Farm is located in Efland, North Carolina in northern Orange County. We have approximately five acres of produce, including almost 2 acres of pre-picked and pick-your-own strawberries. The farm has been in operation since 1885. We grew tobacco until the year 2000, and have since diversified into the other products listed. The farm is also home to a 125 pair commercial cow-calf operation.      Three generations currently work at the farm. Howard Sr., Howard Jr. and Karen, and Callie and Elizabeth are all important to the operation. There is always work to be done with the vegetables, strawberries, and cattle.      Call or stop by for more information. We look forward to seeing you! ','(919)732-7701 ','','Howard McAdams and family','','At the Farm: Strawberry Season (May): Monday thru Saturday, 8 AM to 7 PM, Vegetables (June thru October): Monday, Wednesday, and Friday from 3 to 6 PM, At the Carrboro Farmers\' Market: Saturday Mornings from 7 AM to 12 noon, Early May thru late November, ','','www.mcadamsfarm.com ','','1100 Efland-Cedar Grove Rd. ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27243 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:34','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('8174b595-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Minka Farm, LLC  ','Minka Farm wants to be your farmer! We are a young and growing family farm that uses sustainable practices to raise fruit & vegetables, hen & duck eggs, and pastured beef.     All of the animal products we produce come from animals that are raised on pastures that are maintained without the use of synthetic pesticides or herbicides. Animal feeds are vegetarian and do not contain hormones or antibiotics. Our beef cattle, ducks and chickens are Animal Welfare Approved. Visit www.animalwelfareapproved.org to learn more about this rigorous certification which ensures happy, healthy lives for farm animals.    We do not use synthetic fertilizers, herbicides or pesticides on our market garden and offer a CSA through the spring, summer & fall. The orchard is young, but look forward to a huge range of tree fruits and berries including blueberries, blackberries, apples, peaches, plums, grapes, pawpaws, pears, figs and persimmons. ','919.304.4999 ','farmer@minkafarm.com ','Kimberly Harry','','By 