T.P. area of North Carolina. I had several friends who desired farm websites so they asked me to build and host their agribusiness website. It launched my company Orphan Systems.com I raise sheep for the enjoyment of having animals, because I have a biology background, and it keeps me humble. I have been programming professionally since 1997 and design and build webbased healthcare information delivery systems. Most of my sites are database driven and have versatilities and capabilities that free pages and template-driven sites cannot offer, including online form processing, custom actions and transactions.     If you are curious about what I can offer please visit, OrphanSystems or NC Farm Swap ','919 357 8126 ','sheep@orphansystems.com ','Gary Fay','','','','www.orphansystems.com/fcsfarm/ ','','Shanklins Dead End Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27243 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:34','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('817d288a-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Arrowhead Beef  ','Arrowhead Beef is located in northern Orange County in Cedar Grove, North Carolina. We have always enjoyed the excellent quality and taste of our home-grown beef. The cattle grazed on grass and are finished on grain. Our cattle never leave the farm until they are ready to be processed. Our processing is done by Chaudhry Halal Meat in Siler City, NC. After being slaughtered, the meat is dry-aged for 28 days in a temperature controlled room. This process helps improve the taste and tenderness. Next the meat is cut to order, vacuum sealed and frozen. This process is completed under the inspection of a state USDA Inspector. We transport the product back to our farm in freezers where it remains until purchased. Because our meat is vacuum sealed, it will always taste fresh, even after being frozen for months. From our farm, for your family\'s table-we offer for sale this quality beef that we hope you will enjoy. ','919-732-4854 ','arrowheadbeef@aol.com ','Adam Huskins','','We are open on Saturdays 2-5 and by appointment on other days. ','','','','3230 Hwy 86 North ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27278 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:34','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('817e1f72-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Breezy Oaks Farm  ','We have a small farm of 24 acres in Mebane, NC where we raise our Red Wattle Hogs, a few cattle and pastured poultry. Our 200 acre farm located near Callands, VA is where our main herd of cattle and a few other critters live.     We proudly produce 100% grass-fed & finished dry aged beef, gourmet pastured pork and free-range chicken & eggs. Customers say our pork chops, chicken breasts, and ground beef are exceptional. Our animals are never treated with hormones or antibiotics, so our meats and eggs are hormone, antibiotic and chemical free. Our feed is custom blended for us.     If you would like to place an order please call or email with your inquiries. 919-617-6115 mwynne17@gmail.com ','9196176115','mat.breezyoaks@gmail.com','Matthew Wynne','','Open by special appointment only. ','','www.breezyoaksfarm.com ','','3242 Mt Zion Ch Rd ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27302 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:34','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('817f9882-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Fickle Creek Farm','','919-304-6287 ','ficklecreek@mebtel.net ','Ben Bergmann','','','','home.mebtel.net/~ficklecreek ','','4122 Buckhorn Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27243 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:34','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('81812235-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Genesis Farm  ','Genesis Farm is a micro-eco farm located about five miles west of Chapel Hill. We sell fresh, seasonal produce and cut flowers during the growing season. We also sell fresh eggs from our sassy hens.     Due to the increase in urban life and reliance on technology, we believe that many children suffer from a \"nature deficit\". To counter this deficit, we have created The FARM SCHOOL, which opens May-October. It is a field-trip destination designed for school grades K-5th, but we accomodate all age groups (even adults!) who want to learn about small farm life, how to grow plants for food and care for animals. Learn about cows, chickens, meet our miniature donkey and horse; plant a seed, turn the compost pile, \"milk\" Bessie. Bring your lunch and enjoy free play in the pasture. We invite you to come out and get your knees dirty! Also, we offer a nook on the farm, focused around an old potting shed, that we call Our Pasture Place. It is available for small weddings and parties (outdoor venue only, noon to dusk) and includes a picnic area under old maple trees, volleyball and large bandstand.      New this year: The Barnhouse at Genesis Farm. We offer our guest quarters as a farm stay where you can come and meet the barnyard critters, enjoy a breakfast of fresh eggs from our hens and sit on the deck and marvel at amazing sunsets. The cottage is spacious and will sleep five: it has a bedroom with queen-sized bed; futon and small couch/bed in the large living room. All new and very comfortable. Come and relax on the farm! ','919-968-4759 ','theny2003@yahoo.com ','TD Matheny','','Please call or email for hours and product availability. ','','www.genesisfarmnc.com ','','1841 Jo Mac Rd ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28516','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:34','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('818292ab-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Genesis Farm\'s Pasture Place  ','Nestled in a corner of our farm, this natural retreat offers four acres of open space and rolling pastures focused around the old potter\'s shed. Enjoy a private setting bordered by tree-lined fences and a fish pond, complete with farm animals and wildlife. There is a picnic area shaded by two majestic maple trees, a large deck/bandstand, volleyball and lots of room for playing. This is a non-smoking, outdoor venue only, open from noon until dusk.     Make yours a memorable event: rent space for parties, reunions, small weddings, receptions, festivals, fund-raisers -- whatever your needs. Great place for kid\'s birthday parties. Genesis Farm is a twenty-acre working farm located in Orange County, approximately six miles west of Chapel Hill. Easily accessible, family friendly and plenty of parking.     Opportunities: **For open venues, festivals, small weddings: $500. **Great place for kids\' birthday parties -- best suited for ages 4-10, party length of two hours: $100 minimum ($7 per child after 8 children). **For private events, space may be rented for entire day: $300 for first 100 people; or space may be rented in two-hour blocks: $150 for first 15 people (additional folks: $3.50/head). ','919-968-4759 ','tdtheny@earthlink.net ','TD Matheny','','Noon until dusk, Seasonal -- closed for winter unless there is a special request.','','','','1841 Jo Mac Rd ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28516','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:34','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('818382d8-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','High Rock Farms','High Rock Farms is a 67-acre farm in northern Orange County located in central North Carolina Three generations of family members work together to grow fresh fruits and vegetables, harvesting right before you buy. High Rock Herbs delivers extracts from locally-grown, naturally-fertilized medicinal herbs. We take pride in growing herbs without chemicals, pesticides or herbicides. ','336-562-5569 ','highrockherbs@gmail.com ','Jeannie or Rose Dunn','','Please call for an appointment, We are happy to serve you.','','www.highrockfarms.com ','','7500 High Rock Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27243 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:34','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('8184f077-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Hogan\'s Magnolia View Farm','Hogan\'s Magnolia View Farm is a small family farm, providing grass-fed beef to the Chapel Hill/Durham community. Grass fed beef is not only lower in fat than grain-fed beef, but has higher levels of healthy fats including Omega-3 fatty acids and CLA.     Our cattle are pure Herford beef cattle. They eat either fresh pasture growth or stored grasses such as hay or hay silage. They are allowed to grow at a natural rate; calves stay with their mothers. We have recently introduced a new Red Devon bull, Gilbert. The Red Devon is an old breed from New Zealand, superbly suited to grass feeding. Their meat is flavorful and moist and they gain weight efficiently on grass. Our herd lead stress-free lives on about 40 acres of pasture, with free access to water and shade. We do not use any hormones or antibiotics. The herd stays healthy due to the lack of crowding, free-range pasture, and careful management by Rob. ','919-942-6090 ','grassfedbeef@nc.rr.com ','Rob Hogan','','We are open all year round and sell the meat from a meat house on our farm, E-mail us to arrange a time to come.','','www.hogansbeef.com ','','9118 Old NC 86 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28516','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:34','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('81865526-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Humphries Nursery  ','We\'re a family-owned and operated container nursery in Orange County. This is our 18th year of growing the best perennials for the Triangle area!     We specialize in flowering and foliage plants for a wide range of conditions: sun/shade, damp/dry, and in between.    Our plants are consistently rated the best-performing; because we test them and grow them in natural conditions. ','919-489-5502 ','humphries.nursery@verizon.net ','Kathy Humphries','','Open Weekends March 19 through July. Sat. 9 to 4 Sun. 12-4 Also by appointment any other time. ','','mysite.verizon.net/humphries.nursery/index.html ','','605 Erwin Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27707 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:34','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('8187d8d6-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Laslo\'s Garden ','Laslo\'s Garden, established in 2008, is located in the beautiful countryside of Efland. The garden is tended by husband-and-wife team Tim and Joanne Laslo with the help of their children Robert and Mackenzie. \"We want our children to realize the rewards of good hard work and to enjoy the wonderful freshness of foods from our garden,\" says Tim. \"We use natural gardening techniques and try to nurture the earth at the same time it rewards us with its bounty.\" The Laslo\'s Garden table at the HFM is a kaleidoscope of colors that change with the seasons. This spring, it is greens in every imaginable hue punctuated by the pinks and reds of the Laslos\' gorgeous \"bright lights\" Swiss chard, a customer favorite. As summer comes on, it will be the bright yellows, reds, and oranges of tomatoes and peppers. The Laslos have a reputation among HFM vendors and customers for being the \"go-to\" place for peppers. Green or yel