0306701b527',1),('81f013f3-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Poplar Grove Plantation  ','Historic Poplar Grove Plantation is a museum complex with costumed guided tours of the 1850 Manor House, live informative demonstrations by the blacksmith, basket maker or weaver. This southern plantation was known for being one of the oldest and largest peanut plantations in the south, formerly consisting of over 600 acres, now situated just north of downtown Wilmington. Poplar Grove Plantation has been featured in a number of films about the civil war era.     The history of Poplar Grove Plantation and the Foy family date back to the late 1700\'s. You\'ll learn about farm life, farm animals, crops, slavery, the civil war and much more. The picnic and playground area, agricultural and historic artifact exhibits, garden and gazebo add to this great place for group or individual tours. School programs are tailored to grade level and may include a hayride through the 16 acre plantation (by advance reservation.) Children love to visit Toby the shetland pony, Rowdy one of the resident goats and the unusual chickens in the coop.     The Cultural Arts Center is home to the Cape Fear Woodcarvers, Cape Fear Rug Hookers, Quilters-by-the-Sea and other community groups that meet here regularly to work on their crafts and enjoy friendly conversation. The center is also available for weddings, parties and meetings and will hold up to 175 guests. The manor house may be rented for small wedding ceremonies after 5PM. ','910-686-9518 ','pgp@poplargrove.com ','Jeanne Walker','','Monday - Saturday 9:00AM to 5:00PM Sunday Noon to 5:00PM, Closed: Easter Sunday, Thanksgiving and from the week before Christmas until the first Monday in February.','','www.poplargrove.com ','','10200 US Highway 17 North ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28411 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:35','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('81f16f7b-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','The Farm Market','Since 1969 The Farm Market and Sweet Carolina Farms LLC has been providing farm fresh produce to New Hanover, Bladen and Pender County families. We carry locally grown produce (seasonal) with several items coming straight off the fields behind our market.     A local favorite of beach goers for 35+ years The Farm Market has supplied travellers from Raleigh, Greensboro and other areas west as they travel to Wilmingt and it local beaches.    We are a local favorite as well as many come from the Wilmington area, just minutes away, to sample the local fare.     It all started in 1969 as our father Sonny Rowe had blueberry fields that sat adjacent to HWY 421 in Currie. Travelers would stop on the side of the road jump the ditch and ask if we would sell them blueberries as they headed toward Wilmington on vacation. Soon daddy decided to put in a \"stand\" to get the folks off the busy highway and provide a store front for them to purchase our farm fresh products. The rest is history! ','910-675-9971 ','johrow@carolina.rr.com ','David Rowe','','9-6pm 7 days a week ','','','','13538 NC Highway 210 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28457 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:35','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('81f2da9c-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','The Jelly Hut ','I created The Jelly Hut to do something that I love and I watched my mother do as I was growing up. I learned how to make bread and jellies by watching my mother and she did it to preserve all of the delicious seasonal foods that came out of our garden. Now I want to do the same while making a living for my family. I put much care into my breads and jellies and hope that you will enjoy them as much as my family does.     Most of my jellies are made from locally grown fruit. I believe the fresh fruit used in the jelly makes all of the difference in the world! My breads and muffins are of course homemade with my most popular seller being my pumpkin muffins. I get requests for them as soon as I sell out. I do make many different varieties of jellies and breads and try to fill special requests. If there is something you would like to see just request it and if I don\'t already have it I will do my best to make it! ','910-231-5260 ','thejellyhut@yahoo.com ','Susan Navas','','24 hours a day 7 days a week for online orders, 8 a.m. to 8 p.m. for phone orders ','','www.ncagr.gov/thejellyhut.htm ','','199 Brewington Drive ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28425 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:35','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('81f4322f-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','The Nifty Place','We are a specialty retail antiques & gifts shop featuring many handmade and all natural products. Most are from NC and many are from independent local crafters and therefore unique.     Our \"Mom and Pop\" business is reminiscent of the days before Wal-Mart and other giant retailers. Our customers are friends, not numbers. We will soon relocate to our renovated historic building at 102 W. Fremont St. here in Burgaw and will add a bakery!!! ','910-259-4552 ','info@theniftyplace.com ','Chris Walker','','Monday through Saturday 10AM to 6PM Wednesdays we may close at 2PM (and by appoinment) ','','www.theniftyplace.com ','','103 W. Fremont St. (Mail to: PO Box 746) ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28425 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:35','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('81f507a5-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Haven Acres Farm','We have peaches grown right here on the farm, along with other produce from right up the road. We have fresh veggies and friendly people! ','','tara@havenacresfarm.com ','William and Tara Fowler','','Saturdays from 9am until 2pm, Tuesdays from 5pm-9pm- also available by appointment by calling 252-209-1954. ','','','','1027 Beech Springs Rd ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27944 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:35','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('81f689e1-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Luna\'s Market ','Our Grandmother\'s name was Luna. In 1973 Ben & Jackie bought her farm and moved on the property, keeping the farm in the Hobbs family. Throughout Grandmama\'s life she prepared for \"Party Time\" on Saturday mornings assuring her family had a special cake, candy, or pie for Sunday gatherings. Luna was a wonderful cook, a gracious host and a true southern lady. She always had a vegetable garden with beautiful flowers about the edges. As we are concentrating on Special Events, \"Party Time,\" fresh classic Southern dishes, and locally grown flower presentations; we could not think of a more perfect name than \"Luna\'s Market\".     Luna\'s Market is an fully restored and furnished house with country gardens. Our facility is the perfect place for gatherings of family, business, and/or friends. We can accommodate up to 65 guest in the restaurant (35 guest downstairs with an additional 30 guest upstairs) Our venue is set back off a country road leaving us an expansive lawn that can accommodate tents for larger parties. We are historically charming yet up to date with all our amenities.     We are currently hosting mini farmer\'s markets on 1st and 3rd Saturdays with the dining area serving the featured market items for brunch. ','252-426-7815 ','sybil@lunasmarket.com ','Sybil Skinner','','1st and 3rd Saturdays for morning markets and brunch 9am to 1pm - Special Events ','','www.lunasmarket.com ','','960 Pender Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27944 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:35','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('81f773e3-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Snow Hill Farms Show Cattle  ','','252-312-3660 ','snowhillfarms@gmail.com','Jared Harrell','','','','www.snowhillfarms.com ','','384 Woodland Church Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27944 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:35','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('81f8d179-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Hot Times Firewood Company','We sell to convenience stores, restaurants, parks, and marinas.','336-597-2584 ','hob@person.net ','Joe Berryhill','','Contact any time','','','','705 Berryhill Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27574 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:35','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('81fa2355-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','ABCwoolcrafts  ','Our Colored English angora rabbits have won at the ARBA conventions, but mostly sit here in SE NC giving us beautiful fibers. Bloodlines like \"wooley Boogers\" and \"chu\" grace our pedigrees, but names like \"pretty baby\" and \"butterscotch\" make them pets. We offer horse boarding and riding lessons. In 07 hope to stand a very nice black percheron stallion at stud to limited mares. We show at the NC state fair with our lambs and hand spin and work with yarns and wool every day.     We show lambs and spin, but make an excellent sheep treat to help train and \"drench\" your sheep. called Baa bars all lambs love them and you gain from knowing they are getting all they need.     As we grow we may eventually offer lambs for sale but do not at this time.We will be happy to discuss market lambs for next spring ','910-324-7665 ','grayjoe@charter.net ','Melissa Gray','','','','abcwoolcrafts.mralter.com/ ','','176 Dail lane ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28574 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:35','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('81fb13b5-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Blalock Farm1','This farm has been in our family for over 100yrs. We pride ourselves on our products. We handle the very best. And you know it is fresh because you can see where it growes. We offer pick your own but we have a roadside stand too.     Due to rising fuel cost we have had to get alittle creative so we are offering new items at our roadside stand. We now have antiques and collectible porcelain dolls. Also we have indian items and mule drawn equipment.     Come join us for a wonderful time. The children can learn so much here.Coming soon is a walk through museum that dates back a hundred years.! Thanks for your time and I hope to see you soon. ','336-599-5188 ','browncattle1232004@yahoo.com','Wesley Blalock','','We are open 10am to 5pm Wensday thru Friday year round, Produce offered seasonal.','','goodness grows in NC store ','','6420 Burlington Rd ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27541 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:35','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('81fc53ed-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Blalock Produce','Our farm has been in our family since before the civil war and honesty and integrity have always come first.    We value our customers and hope to keep them coming back hopefully with their friends.We also have a roadside stand for those who wish to have already picked items.     We offer pick your own vegtables .Also we will qladly deliver to shut-in\'s on Tuesdays and Thrusdays when seasonal. ','336-599-0098 ','blalockproduce@wmconnect.com','Wesley Blalock','','Mon. thr Sat. 8am to 7pm Opening in July ','','','','6420 Burlington Rd ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27541 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:35','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('81fd3096-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Blalock Produce','We are a family farm that has been in our family for over 100yrs. We offer the best in vegtables without harsh chemicals.     We have had to get creative due to rising fuel cost so we have also started offering other items at our on farm produce market. We offer Antiques and indian items. Along with collectible porcelain dolls and mule drawn equipment.     Our on farm produce stand is open year round. Wensday thru Friday 10:00 until 5:00. We have an outside yardsale year round too and many other farms join us from time to time. Come join us or just stop in and say hi! We\'d love to see ya. ','336-364-1965 ','wesleyblalock@yahoo.com ','Wesley Blalock','','Year round Wensday thru Friday 10:00 till 5:00','','','','6420 Burlington Rd ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27541 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:35','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('81fe692c-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Elevenses Llamas and Miniature Donkeys  ','We are located in rural Person County, about 20 miles north of Durham.   We have been raising quality llamas and miniature donkeys since 1991. ','336-364-7100 ','elevenses@mindspring.com','Miniature Donkeys','','By appointment (our property is secured for the health and safety of our animals).','','www.elevensesllamas.com ','','195 Valley Dr. ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27572 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:35','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('81ffd23c-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Irena Farm  ','Irena Farm is located about 40 minutes north of Durham, near Roxboro, NC. We are developing a system to produce high quality lamb grown entirely on native grasses. We are adapting the UK \"three-tier\" system using maternal breeds which thrive in southeastern heat and dry summer spells.     We offer very mild lamb that finishes at a light weight suitable for barbeques and roasts for the family. We frequently also offer older animals - our breeds provide some of the best mutton on the planet! Very mild and tender with almost gamey taste.     We presently only offer whole animals, although we have no problem with splitting orders for customers who order together. We deliver to the processor of your choice, or we can have the processing done and we\'ll deliver to a mutually convenient location. A 65 pound lamb yields about 35 pounds of meat, which usually fits in a medium sized cooler. We would love to talk to you about buying lamb straight from the farm! ','(336) 234-0389 ','shouse@mebtel.net ','Rebecca Shouse','','','','www.goosedogs.com/irena ','','54 Scott Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27343 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:35','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('82017025-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Rogers Cattle Company, LLC  ','Rogers Cattle Company, LLC (RCC) is located in Roxboro, North Carolina. RCC is owned and operated by Johnny and Sharon Rogers. As a young couple wanting to be involved in agriculture we began RCC in 2000 and have continued to grow and develop our livestock and beef enterprises.     Our all natural Angus beef is produced from both Red Angus and Black Angus cattle. All steers are feed a specially formulated diet developed by Johnny who has a MS Degree in Nutrition from NCSU. The steers also have access to lots of green pasture and open spaces. In addition to our cattle, sheep have recently been added as companion graziers on our farm. Grass fed lamb is also available for purchase in the fall and winter. In 2011, we added chicken and turkey to our offering. Give us a call for more details.     Our goal is to supply outstanding farm fresh pasture raised meats for you and your family. We hope you will be able to taste the pride we have for our superior quality beef in every bite! ','336-598-5835 ','rccbeef@gmail.com ','Johnny and Sharon Rogers','','Call to schedule an appointment 336-598-5835, Monday - Saturday 9:00am to 5:00pm. ','','www.rogerscattleco.com ','','945 Woodsdale Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27574 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:35','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('820273b2-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Thane\'s Neck Farm  ','We are a small family farm that specializes in breeding high quality alpacas. We love to show off our beautiful alpacas and welcome you to visit and see these wonderful creatures for yourself.     Alpacas are beautiful animals that are raised for their extremely soft, exquisite fleece that grows in 22 natural colors. Alpaca is a Cashmere-like fleece that is one of the worlds finest and most luxurious natural fibers. Alpaca fiber is stronger, lighter, warmer and softer than sheep\'s wool. Our farm goal is to breed huacaya alpacas to produce healthy, easy to handle animals recognized for their outstanding fleece. We strive to produce fiber with low micron count, high density, with good crimp, and preferably with color. We include Peruvian, Bolivian, and Chilean bloodlines in our herd to produce our all-American huacaya alpacas.     We also raise many other animals on our farm. These include our two mini donkeys, two Irish Dexter milk cows, Nigerian Dwarf goats, a mixed flock of colored egg laying chickens, Naragansett turkeys, Muscovy ducks and American Chinchilla rabbits. At times we have a selection of these other livestock for sale as well. ','336-939-1301 ','diana@thanesneckfarm.com ','Diana Moxcey','','Family and group farm tours by appointment only, Please call to schedule your tour today! ','','www.thanesneckfarm.com ','','9516 Virgilina Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27574 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:35','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('820415ab-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Winstead\'s Pumpkin Patch/ Taylor Farming','The Winstead farm is located in the scenic rolling hills of Leasburg, NC. Growing up we primarily grew tobacco, hay, and raised livestock. My stepfather, Samuel Winstead started up the farm shortly after returning from serving in the pacific during World War 2. We were known in the community especially during the holidays due to our old fashioned country hams. When people weren\'t tending to the agri-business, we were working on curing hams. Sam\'s Country Hams had a loyal patrionage. People would travel all the way from upstate New York after having one of our hindquarters at a family affair. We only sold to the public, never advertised, and managed to sell out every year. The old ham house still stands as a testament to time and reflection. It no longer operates in its origonal purpose, but is quite beautiful in its turn of the century rustic architecture. A log cabin style structure with creasote stained walls, its rustic assemblage fulfilled the function.     When I was about ten years of age, I managed to learn about the effects of tobacco, and convinced my stepfather to quit the tobacco business. Years later, he quit farming, and concentrated on his contracting company.     Over a decade later, and after recognizing the need for sustainable agriculture, we look forward to seeing what the soil will allow us to harvest naturally and efficiently. Last year we marketed the first crop grown on the land in over fifteen years. This year we expanded to two test crops. Specialty watermelons and Italian pear tomatoes grew amazingly well in a wild organic enviroment. Due to our success in cultivating these crops, we will be offering them as specialty crops next year. Pumpkins will always be our base product, as we are quite fond of them. Possible agritourism concepts may follow in the future. We look forward to bringing our best to you. Contact us for any reason, we would like to hear from you! ','919-234-9301 ','jtaylor794@nc.rr.com ','Jonathan Taylor','','All inquiries can be addressed through the information at the top of our page.','','','','101 Sams Ham Rd. ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27291','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:35','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('8205907c-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Bailey\'s Sauces, Inc ','After years of listening to friends say, \"Dale, you need to bottle this marinade and barbecue sauce\", my wife and I prayed about what he would have us do. The door was opened and we pursued God\'s plan.     After contemplating on what to name our sauces, we wanted the name to reflect God in our lives. We were directed to a verse in the bible that says, \"Taste and See that the Lord is Good; blessed is the man who takes refuge in him. Psalm 34:8      We new that Taste and See was the perfect name for our sauces. One, if people could taste our products, they would see how great they really are, and secondly, but most importantly, if only people would taste God, they would see how good he really is. S ','252-756-7179 ','nblovespe@netzero.net ','Dale Bailey','','Monday-Friday 9:00-5:00, Please call for an appointment.','','www.tasteandseelig.com ','','3765 Mills Rd ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27858 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:35','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('82066633-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Bear Foot Farm  ','','252-524-3714 ','Bearfootfarmnc@aol.com','Michael Boggs','','E mail us at BearfootfarmNC@aol.com ','','','','2922 NC 118 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28530 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:35','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('82074595-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Bear Foot Farm  ','We are located on 44 acres in Southern Pitt County. Our goal is to provide quality Pasture Raised Registered Dorpers for breeding stock, as well as high quality meat lambs.     We also raise Registered Maremma Livestock Guardian Dogs. This rare breed was developed over 2000 years ago to protect other animals, and is one of the best there is. You can view them here: http://hometown.aol.com/bearfootfarmnc/page1.html And here: http://www.dogbreedinfo.com/maremmasheepdog.htm ','252-524-3714 ','Bearfootfarmnc@aol.com','Michael and Ellen Boggs','','Call or come by most any time, or E mail us at BearfootfarmNC@aol.com ','','hometown.aol.com/bearfootfarmnc/index.html ','','2922 NC 118 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28530 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:35','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('8208d88e-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Boss Hog\'s Backyard BBQ ','Charles Baker, Mr. Boss Hog himself, has chased golf balls throughout his career as a golf pro before becoming a restaurantuer in 1999. His love of cooking for others and cooking for many golf \"greats\" and big events led him from the shimmering of the emerald greens after retirement into a new concept of cooking barbeque, ribs and chicken he called \"Boss Hog\'s Backyard BBQ\". From his start in 1999, this barbeque iron chef is now on his third Boss Hog\'s Restaurant and continuing to open new doors with his products while business grows at an extremely fast pace. Retirement looked favorably on the boss as his decision to open his own restaurant took him straight from retirement into an instant successful business that involves family members to maintain and control growth. His daughter Kim, helps with all three restaurants as does his son, Bobby, who manages the 14th street location. The birth of his sauces came about by working with many different ingredients throughout his years of cooking and experimenting only to end up with the best. Billy Tripp, the pitt master at Boss Hog\'s ensures every rib, chiken and chopped barbeque is so fittin\' it\'ll make your tongue jump out and slap at ya for more! We do have plenty of napkins inside, cuz your gonna need it after gettin\' hold of his lip smacking ribs, lusciously covered in the boss\'s Sweet Southern BBQ Sauce. As of today and no sooner than I just left the restaurant, customers gobble the stuff up faster than we can fix it, so we knew there had to be a bigger trail out the door of people who would like the taste of Boss Hog\'s BBQ sauce and rubs straight from Greenville, North Carolina. The sauces and rubs will soon be on North Carolina shelves for folks to have a taste of as well as purchasing it at the restaurants. Just look for the grinn\'n Hollywood pig on the orange label wearing the \"Boss Hog\" t-shirt and his enterage of back seat drivers! See ya there! Yours truly, Boss Hog (aka Mr. Charlie Baker).','252-758-8880 ','dsm0313@mail.ecu.edu ','Charlie Baker','','Monday through Sunday, 10:30am to 8:00pm ','','','',