,'a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('821ab104-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Swift Creek Fish Farm Inc.','Indepentent grower of grain fed catfish, Established in 1995, Located: on Gum Swamp Rd. Ayden, NC ','252-746-8080 ','swift@nowait.net ','Merlin Nichols','','Thursday - Saturday 7:00 AM - Sundown','','','','6231 Gum Swamp Rd. ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28513 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:35','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('821c3c09-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Apple Mill ® ','Apple Mill? was established in 1927 by the English horticulturist William Scrope Viner. He selected Saluda because of its reputation for growing flavorsome apples and berries. Saluda, home of the original North Carolina Apple Festival and the North Carolina Horticultural Society was the first commercial apple growing region in North Carolina. Fine quality fresh fruit, fruit butters, jams, preserves, and mulled cider have been produced for decades at Apple Mill?. These foods have been sold to the public at the Apple Mill? kitchen and store at Exit 28, I-26 Saluda, NC.     Apple Mill? orchards grow premium apples for cooking apple butter. Our spices are imported directly and ground fresh immediately as they are added to the slowly cooked butter. We call our product Whole Apple Butter, because the washed raw apples are cored, not peeled. This process removes the stem, seeds, and blossom end. The cored apples are cooked in pure apple cider. The removed core \"plugs\" are pressed in a juice extractor and the juice is added back to the apple butter in the cooking kettle. As the kettle contains no stems, seeds, or blossom ends, no off flavors are produced during cooking. When the finishing point is reached the entire mixture is pureed into a creamy butter containing all the nutrients of the peeling and the core juice, which alone account for 90% of the nutrition in an apple.     In addition to producing premium Whole Apple Butter, Apple Mill? also produces a variety of fine food products. Carolyn Atkins, owner of Apple Mill?, cooks with all varieties of fresh fruit and vegetables. ','828-749-9136 ','applemill@tds.net ','Carolyn Atkins','','Apple Mill® is open 364 days a year from 9:00 to 6:00. ','','www.ncapplemill.com ','','1345 Ozone Drive ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28773 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:35','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('821d3b1c-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Slater Turf Farm','We are producers and wholesale suppliers of turfgrass sod. In addition to turfgrass sod we are offering other agricultural products such as pumpkins in October and cool and warm season ornamental grasses.     We are located in the western part of North Carolina in Polk County where I-26 intersects with the NC/SC state line.     We are open Monday through Friday and most Saturday mornings. We recommend calling for availability. ','828-894-5113 ','slaterturf@msn.com ','Dave Slater','','We are open Monday through Friday and most Saturday mornings, Call to place orders.','','www.slaterturf.com ','','5554 Hunting Country Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28782 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:35','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('821e8fd3-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','The Old Mule Co.  ','The Old Mule Company is located in the North Carolina Mountain Foothills. We are a small family owned business specializing in our gourmet bbq, marinade, dipping sauce. Old Mule\'s unique blend of spices and flavors makes this an ideal gift for anyone. It\'s not too hot