 in Polk County. They have been so well received; I\'ve developed more variations of unique flavors and other candies containing nuts. Each package of nuts contains pecan halves, walnuts and whole almonds. My nut flavors at the moment are: Cinn-fully Cinnamon, the original cinnamon flavor; Orbital Orange, a unique flavor with an orange citrus tang; and Spicy Afterlife, a sweet and salty flavor with a hint of heat at the end. Keep checking for new flavors as I develop them.      My Blissful Pecan Brittle is loaded with pecans in a light buttery crunch. Terrific Toffee is loaded with oven roasted almonds in a bed of toffee and coated with dark chocolate. The Goata€?s Milk Fudge is smooth and creamy dark chocolate with loads of walnuts. It\'s the goat\'s milk that makes the difference!      Cinn-ful nuts and candies are handmade locally with local ingredients when available. Our products contain local farm fresh eggs, goata€?s milk and pecans. Our nuts are oven roasted in small batches to insure quality. My candies are also prepared by hand in small batches to guarantee the same delicious flavor each time. Cinn-ful Nut products are gluten free. Products can be ordered in 4 oz., 8 oz, or pound quantities and shipped to order. Think of Cinn-ful Nuts for weddings, events or gifts. ','828-817-9161 ','rbnjulian@yahoo.com ','Robin Julian','','Cinn-ful Nut products are available anytime by special order, Call 828-817-9161 to place your order today! ','','www.cinnfulnuts.com ','','50 Hidden Hill Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28782 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:35','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('82232b9c-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','DeerHaven Hills Farm, LLC  ','DeerHaven Hills Farm is a family operated Certified Organic Blueberry and Muscadine Grape farm near Tryon in the foothills of the Blue Ridge Mountains. Before moving to North Carolina with our daughter and her family in 1998, my husband and I owned a small, organic, wholesale tropical fruit farm (papaya, mango, pineapple, lichee, & macadamia trees) and Podocarpus nursery in Davie, Florida. We purchased our property in Polk County in 1996, moved here in 1998. We began planting produce that could be grown organically, was more native to this area and was more weather, disease and pest resistant--namely blueberries and muscadine grapes. It was our plan, not only to make our property sustainable (financially as well as food-wise) for our family, but to help keep family farms alive in our larger, county and state communities.     My husband passed away in late 2007 and I have taken his place running the farm. We became Certified Organic by NCCIA in 2009 and recertified in 2010 by Clemson University. We are the only Certified Organic farm in Polk County at this time. We drilled a new irrigation well in 2009 and installed a drip irrigation system for the 700 rabbit-eye blueberry bushes in 2010. We had a great blueberry season this summer with over 3000 pounds and the 700 Summit and Triumph Muscadine vines are lush and full of fruit. Both crops have outdone themselves this year.','828-863-4660 ','deerhavenhills@skyrunner.net','Gail Blate','','By appointment','','','','PO Box 1460 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28722 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:35','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('8224a20d-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Giardini Gardens  ','Come visit our restuarant and farm where we grow a wide variety of fresh produce that is incorporated into all the delicious meals we serve in our rustic Italian restaurant. We feature amazing rustic pizzas fresh from our wood burning ovens along with a wonderful variety of seasonal lunches and dinners focused on our garden fresh produce. We also have a retail market with fresh made lunches and dinners available for take-out along with garden fresh produce in season.     Throughout the year there are garden tours, workshops in organic growing, kids programs and informal cooking classes. Call for information or check out our website at www.giardinigardens.com. ','828-894-0234 ','MDLyth@aol.com ','Mary Lyth','','The Retail Market and Take-Out is open Tuesday - Saturday from 11 am - 7 pm The restaurant is open for lunch and dinner Wednesday - Saturday from 11:30 - 8:30','','www.giardinigardens.com ','','2411 Hwy 108E ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28722 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:35','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('82258dee-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Green Creek Winery  ','Green Creek Winery is a new winery located in Western North Carolina about 35 miles south of Asheville. We have 9 acres of vineyards, a tasting room and lawn area. We are open Thursday through Sunday from 1 -5 PM and other times by appointment. Our tasting is free and we have a few gifts for purchase. We are tour bus friendly with plenty of parking.','828-863-2182 ','greencreekwinery@alltel.net','Alvin Pack','','Tursday through Sunday from 1 - 5 PM','','www.greencreekwinery.com ','','413 Gilbert Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28722 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:35','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('82270072-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Green Creek Winery  ','Green Creek Winery was opened in 2005. We have A tasting room, patio and lawn area. We currently have 8 wines, all are estate wines. 07 Chardonnay, 06 Winemaker\'s Reserve Chardonnay, 07 Cab. Sau, 07 Merlot, 07 Cab. Franc, Chambourcin Rose and Cab. Franc Rose. And, our most well know wine is Chardonnay Rosso, the world\'s 1st Red Chadonnay','828-863-2182 ','greencreekwinery@alltel.net','Alvin Pack','','October thru March, Thursday thru Sunday 1 -5 PM, April thru September, Wed & Thur 1- 5 PM / Fri & Sat 11-6 and Sunday 1 - 6 PM','','www.greencreekwinery.com ','','413 Gilbert Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28722 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:35','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('8227fd50-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Green River Vineyard and Bed & Breakfast Accommoda  ','Country Bed & Breakfast located on 30 acreas surrounded by our vineyards, picturesque mountain vistas and the Green River.     Luxury accommodations decorated in unique wine themes. All rooms located on the main floor with their own private entrances through French doors leading out to a courtyard with water fountain, and therapeutic spa.     Includes: freshly made cookies, evening social with simple hors\'deurves, refrigerator stocked with complimentary beverages, game room, comfortable common room, full country \"Gourmet\" breakfast, central air conditioned bedrooms with ceiling fans, own private bathrooms, hiking trails along the Green River, country gardens and \"Southern Hospitality\" ','','greenrivergal@alltel.net ','Peggy Turner','','Check in: 3 pm to 6 pm or by arrangement, Check out 11 am, Special rates for midwk., and off season.','','www.greenriverbb.com ','','3043 John Watson Rd. ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28139 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:35','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('82297de9-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Mt. McLaney\'s Highland Harvest  ','After a lifetime of wondering what the heck was in our foods, we started Highland Harvest to end the wondering! We KNOW there are NEVER any chemicals, pesticides or ever fertilizers in our hens or gardens! We are very very small frye....miniscule, in fact, so we CAN keep track of everything that enters our food chain and make sure everything is safe at all times!     We deliver. That\'s the only method we use to get our goods to you. There is no store, no place you can go to get our products. We thought about it but it made more sense for ONE vehicle to travel to 50 sites in the county in one trip than for 50 cars to make 50 trips from all points on the map. We love the environment. This is our contribution. One phone call will bring what you need right to your door on delivery day. We keep you informed of what is available with a weekly newsletter listing everything we have available.     Our hens are true free range hens. They have our 35 acres to roam as they please, sometimes on the porch, usually in the woods, finding bugs and all the things nature intended them to eat. Luckily, they are all trained to return to the henhouse to lay so we dont have to search the woods for the eggs! We have chickens of all sorts, brown and white egg layers but we call our dozens \"rainbow\" because we also have hens that lay green and light blue eggs, sometimes a pink or an olive drag thrown in! The eggs are nest direct, dozens have varying sizes from the new hen\'s first efforts to the macho hens that lay \"oooh, that musta hurt\" sized eggs. I hand wash each and every egg, inspecting it for cracks and problems. ','828-288-0774 ','HighlandHarvest@msn.com ','Katherine Anderson McLaney','','We deliver weekdays all year round, WE take your calls 24/7 ','','www.highlandharvest.net ','','13 Mt. McLaney Trail ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28139 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:35','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('822a5a3d-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Sunrise Farm  ','Registered Dairy Goats.   