reenhouses on our 120 acre farm. Committed to an environmentally friendly agriculture and safe food supply, our family has operated the farm since 1987.      We take food quality and stewardship of the land seriously. Preservation of farmland, food quality, air quality and our environment are critical to all of us. With this in mind we are happy to share information that may help others preserve the environment and promote sustainable agriculture.      Our greenhouse tomatoes are available in the spring and fall. We have been told that our tomatoes are the best at the farmer\'s market. We credit this to our use of organic growing methods. ','336-857-2775 ','uwharriefarm@rtmc.net ','Judy or Larry McPherson','','Sorry, we do not have a farm store, Please call 336-857-2775 to place orders or to arrange a pick-up at the farm. ','','www.uwharriefarm.com ','','4658 Waynick Meadow Rd. ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27205 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:35','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('823c3b11-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','\"The Bakery\"on Ladybug Lane  ','The magic at The Bakery on Ladybug Lane lies in the use of local seasonal fruits and vegetables. Although, the adorable little polka dotted critters crawling through the gardens also might have something to do with it. Our cupcakes are created with only the freshest ingredients, and these sweet treats\' delicate flavors dance on the palate like the strawberry plant dances in the wind throughout spring. We strive to produce the most delectable creations inspired by nature, and being nestled between two gardens, we don\'t have to look far for inspiration. ','336-824-8088 ','shari.hardin@gmail.com ','Shari Hardin','','Daily pre-order only ','','www.TheBakeryOnLadybugLane.com ','','1 Ladybug Lane ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27298 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:35','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('823d8e54-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Acorn Ridge Farm','Acorn Ridge Farm contains 168 acres with farmlands, pastures, animals, farm structures, modern and antique farm equipment, rolling hills and 3 lakes.     Our goal is to educate and entertain children and adults with the knowledge of farm life as it was years ago and also reflect today\'s methods of farming. We will always have numerous farm animals and various crops in season to show how food is grown and harvested.     We offer one of the Triad\'s best educational and fun-filled adventures for school field trips, church and family outings, picnics, birthday parties and more. ','336-302-4107 ','gsbrown7@yahoo.com ','Donald R. Smith','','To be determined.','','www.acornridgefarm.com ','','1245 Mt. Tabor Church Rd. ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27203 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:35','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('823e7331-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Big Bear Candy Co','','336-498-2581 ','bigbearcandyco@gmail.com ','Paula Hightower','','','','http://bigbearcandyco.etsy.com ','','PO Box 397 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27350 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:35','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('823fd090-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Caraway Alpacas, Inc.','We have been loving and caring for alpacas since 1997. We normally have 20-30 alpacas on the primises. We raise both huacaya and suri alpacas.    We also do our own shearing and send our fiber to the fiber mill to be processed and returned to us in several ways. We get some back in the form of roving to be handspund into yarn; we get some back in a variety of yarns; and we get some back in finished products like sweaters, vests, scarves, etc.     We have a resource and learning center on our farm for those interested in raising alpacas or learning about alpaca fiber. We also have many different alpaca products on hand but we do not operate a \"store\", so visitors must make an appointment. ','336-629-6767 ','carawayalpacas@embarqmail.com','Teresa Johnson','','Visits to our farm are by appointment only. ','','www.carawayalpaca.com ','','1079 Jarvis Miller Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27205 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:35','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('8240ad53-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','E.D. Snider  ','Retired but do a little farming still.     I also have hay (Cow and Horse Quality) Fescue/Burmuda Mixture 2.75 a bale ','336-622-2942 ','agweb@ncmail.net ','E.D. Snider','','','','','','3319 Brower Meadow ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27355 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:35','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('824226e8-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Goat Lady Dairy','Located in the lovely rolling hills of northeast Randolph County, our working farm is rich in the diversity of pastures, ponds, meadows, gardens, woodlands, wildlife and livestock. Using sustainable agriculture, we work with nature to enrich rather than deplete our environment. We intentionally limit the size of our farm operation in order to maintain the personal quality of our products and continue to enjoy what we do everyday. We make approx. 250lbs. of handmade farmstead cheese per week and offer our monthly Dinner At The Dairy.     All our cheeses have a special flavor with subtle qualities found only in local dairies. Goats from our milking herd are chosen based on the flavor and qualities their milk contributes to our cheese. We make several styles of cheese including fresh, spreadable Fromage (in 9 flavors), hand-molded Logs, tangy Feta, Smokey Mountain Round, Marinated Chevre, Chevre Camembert, Crottin, Chevre Taleggio and a raw milk, semi-hard cheese called Gray\'s Chapel. At Holiday times we make Chocolate Goat Cheese Truffles. We continue to develop new styles.     You can visit Goat Lady Dairy during our twice a year Open House. We offer Dinner At The Dairy monthly. We also offer group tours by advance reservation. You can get details about all these opportunities and directions to the farm from our web site www.goatladydairy.com Sorry we are not open to the public for individual tours. Call ahead if you would like to come buy cheese at the farm. ','336-824-2163 ','goatladydairy@mindspring.com ','Steve Tate','','Sorry we are not open to the public, Call ahead for cheese sales at the farm or to arrange group tours, Visit www.goatladydairy.com for details about Dinner At The Dairy and our twice a year Open House. ','','www.goatladydairy.com ','','3515 Jess Hackett Rd. ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27233 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:35','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('8243cfe0-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Goat Lady Dairy','Located in the lovely rolling hills of northeast Randolph county, Goat Lady Dairy farm and its log buildings are more than 200 years old. Our family began restoring 60 acres of the original homestead in 1983. Today our working farm is rich in the diversity of pastures, ponds, meadows, gardens, woodlands, wildlife and livestock. Using sustainable agriculture, we work with nature to enrich rather than deplete our environment. We intentionally limit the size of our farm operation in order to maintain the personal quality of our products and continue to enjoy what we do everyday. In addition to our handmade farmstead cheeses, we offer Dining Adventures via Dinner at the Dairy along with hosting Private Events and an organic vegetable Community Supported Agriculture program. Our mission is to nurture the land, our family, and our guests through creative work and quality products.     Dinner at the Dairy - This is why you have tastebuds. Fresh, local, naturally delicious foods. Such colors and textures, amazing aromas, and delectable flavors-suddenly your senses become fully awake. When you dine with us at Goat Lady Dairy, you\'ll actually \"experience\" your food. As you arrive, enjoy appetizers while relaxing on our porch. Then, you\'ll get a behind-the-scenes look at a working farm on our signature farm tour. Finally, you\'ll move leisurely into a \"guided\" multi-course dinner, which includes a tasting of our nationally famous cheeses. This is genuine farm-to-fork slow-food eating. And once you get a taste of it, you\'ll have a whole new appreciation of where your food comes from. Visit www.dinnersatgld.blogspot.com for more information.     Weddings at Goat Lady Dairy - We host and cater wedding ceremonies & receptions on our farm, which is located about thirty minutes outside of Greensboro, NC. We can accommodate up to 150 guests on our property. We provide the following for our wedding clients: 1. A simple planning process for the bride & groom. We believe a wedding should be fun and exciting to plan, not stressful. 2. A beautiful, natural environment. Our decorations are gardens, goats, and chickens! 3. Delicious, farm-fresh food at your reception. All of our food is made from ingredients sourced from our farms or other local farms. 4. A comfortable atmosphere in which you (and your guests!) can relax and truly enjoy your wedding. Visit www.weddingsatgld.blogspot.com for more information. ','336-202-4674 ','millsbtate@gmail.com ','Mills Tate','','We have an Open Farm Day