ours: Mon-Fri 7 to 5 (or by appointment) Sat 8 to 12 (or by appointment) ','','','','333 Summit Rd. ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27288 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:36','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('8293055e-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Norton\'s Honey Farm  ','PLEASE NOTICE: We updated this site on the second of September 2010: I am a commercial North Carolina beekeeper and my honeybees produce the wonderful natural aromatic and flavorful HONEY that we produce, pack and sell. We currently produce and sell two types of SPRING WILDFLOWER HONEY, and a wonderfully robust FALL WILDFLOWER HONEY. With hives in over 10 North Carolina counties from the Blue Ridge mountains to the Central Piedmont we provide our North Carolina customers honey through selected Stores, and Mail Order via the World Wide Web with QUALITY RAW HONEY that is never heated nor filtered. We use only stainless steel and food grade plastics in our de-capping, extracting, clarifying, straining, and storage processes. We have a dedicated sanitary facility for packing and processing our honey.      Our honey is bottled to order , which brings you the freshest quality, flavor and aroma possible.      I am an engineer and have worked for such high tech companies as Hughes Aircraft and Ford Aerospace. While there I learned the values of quality control and responsibility to the customer. These same concepts of quality are built into all our operations from hive assembly and management to bottling and packaging our quality products. We truly strive to produce the finest honey possible for our customers.     All of our Wildflower is processed in the same manner with the same amount of attention and care. This year our STANDARD SPRING WILDFLOWER HONEY consists mostly of tulip poplar, black locust, black gum, wild blackberry, persimmon, and clover honey all randomly collected by our honeybees from most of our apiaries. It is a fine tasting honey that is medium amber in color.    This year we also have a very special Berry Fruity Spring Wildflower Honey that has been collected entirely from our yards that are used to pollinate blackberries, strawberries, and raspberries with large acreages. This has resulted in a wonderful delicate, light and very fruity honey that also has some of the spring varietals listed above.     Our 2009 FALL WILDFLOWER HONEY when available consists mainly of goldenrod, and aster honey; it is a medium to dark amber honey rich and heavy in flavor and high in antidoxants. It is what you may want for help with your fall allergies. The reason that we only sell last yeara€?s crop is that the 2010 fall crop is still being collected by our honeybees.     All Shipping & Handling information is located on the right column of this website under the honey prices. If you have any questions, please email or call and ask.     Our gentle method of processing HONEY is preferred by honey purists; it is often called RAW HONEY because it is never heated and only strained. It is the best most flavorful honey that you can buy! It is absolutely wonderful! When you read about the health benefits of local honey, raw honey, and honey high in antioxidants consider purchasing our HONEY, honey that is produced here in North Carolina.     Our honey prices are listed on the right side of your screen.    We also sell 100% BEESWAX, POLLEN, PROPOLIS, CANDLES, ITALIAN HONEY BEES & QUEENS, BEEKEEPING SUPPLIES, and we rent our honey bees to North Carolina fruit, vegetable and berry farms for POLLINATION SERVICES.','336 342 4490 ','Carolinabeeman@hotmail.com','Chuck Norton','','If you are uncomfortable in ordering through the mail I would be glad to speak with you over the phone in order to answer any questions, Contact me at 336 342 4490 after 7:30 pm EDT, or even better by my e-mail: Carolinabeeman@bellsouth.net,     I am a on','','www.Carolinahoney.com ','','330 Irvin Street ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27320 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:36','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('82948063-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Papa Lonnie\'s Inc.  ','Papa Lonnie\'s Inc. was founded in August 2002 with its headquarters in Stoneville, NC. We are a small family business dedicated to preserving the recipes which have been in our family for genrations. Our sauces have such a distinct flavor, whether you like our regular or hot style, we believe they will be the best basting barbeque sauces you have ever tasted.     Our inspiration and namesake comes from Lonnie Bragdon, who was born and raised in western Kentucky. During WWII he was stationed in North Carolina before being shipped out to Europe. While stationed in NC he met his future wife and decided to settle here after the war. Lonnie then brought his recipes and cooking skills to the Shiloh Community near Stoneville, NC where he made his home and raised his family. Over the years he became affectionately known as \"Papa\" and during this time Papa Lonnie\'s BBQ Sauce was perfected. Sadly, Papa Lonnie passed away in 1989 but his memory and his sauces live on in our hearts and company.     Our Shiloh style sauce has a unique taste and is neither Eastern style or Lexington style and can be used directly as a table sauce. It is great on pork, beef, chicken, seafood and wild game. Remember this is the sauce you\'ve been searching for! ','336-573-9313 ','info@papalonnies.com ','Mike Bragdon','','','','www.papalonnies.com ','','154 Dogwood Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27048 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:36','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('8295700f-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c',