e late 1800\'s as a homeplace and its early tenants enjoyed the fruits the land both for sustenance and financial support. A true working farm, Oakhaven has seen its share of changes over the years too. Like any working farm, Oakhaven has had to change and modernize itself throughout the years to not only survive, but thrive!     The farm\'s main source of revenue through the 1950\'s was tobacco... there are still numerous tobacco barns located on the property that were used to hang and dry the tobacco leaves for market. Visitors to Oakhaven can still find tobacco being air dried the traditional way in some of these barns during the fall of the year and the pungeant aroma of freshly hung tobacco leaves is not to be missed. In the late 1950\'s and early 1960\'s the farm began developing a dairy operation that quickly became its\' main source of revenue. Evidence of the old dairy operation can still be seen along the main road where the old milking facility and silos nestle against a backdrop of rolling hills and forest. In 1971, a decision was made to take the knowledge and experience gained in raising dairy cows and shift that into a beef cattle operation that is still operating to date. Visitors to Oakhaven today can experience a working 150 head cow/calf operation. ','336-939-9125 ','gary@experienceoakhaven.com','Gary Barrett','','Varies... please check website for more information! ','','www.experienceoakhaven.com ','','1434 Dibrell Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27311 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:36','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('82a8b7e5-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Peace of Eden Farms','Peace of Eden Farms is located 20 miles north of Greensboro near Highway 220. With a beautiful view of Hanging Rock, Sauertown Mountain and Pilot Mountain it is our piece of heaven on earth.     We started raising llamas in 19