ack And Gigi Enterprises LLC ','We began making this sauce over 25 years ago as a basting sauce for country-style ribs cut off of a bone-in pork loin. Within an hour of completing the grilling process, we baste the ribs with our special sauce, allowing the sauce to caramelize. Remove the ribs, pack them in a foil-lined cooler, pour extra sauce over them, seal the foil and cooler, and allow the meat to steam for at least an hour ( we′ve actually left them untouched for up to 8 hours, and they′re still piping hot!).     Following a trip to a college baseball tournament at Mississippi State University in 2003, we were inspired to expand our grilling efforts to a larger scale. An oil-tank smoker gave us more grill capacity, and we began to experiment with our barbeque sauce on more varieties of meat, including chicken halves, baby back ribs, shrimp, and Boston butts. Our family, friends, and neighbors also enjoyed cooking with our sauce, and we started to produce batches for private sale in an eight quart pot. We received a lot of encouragement to manufacture the sauce commercially, but two full-time careers were all that we could manage at the time.     In April 2008, I retired from full-time employment and started the process of marketing and producing “Blowin′ Smoke” BBQ sauce. The name originates from our two new daughters-in-law who suggested the name “Blowin′ Smoke”. I disagreed with the name because while the sauce is sweet and spicy; it is not hot. They explained that they believed that I was just “blowin′ smoke” with my talk of manufacturing the sauce. I tried to find a better name, but I was outvoted 5-1, so “Blowin′ Smoke” it is. A customized logo by a local Rowan County artist, Betty Sedberry, completed the packaging. Now “Blowin′ Smoke” has become a fixture in many unique stores in Piedmont North Carolina. Why don′t you try it in your home? We have friends in California, Colorado, New York, Washington State, Virginia, Florida, and South Carolina who are fans of our versatile sauce. We hope that you will use it in your favorite recipes and experiment on your grill. We hope that your family enjoys “Blowin′ Smoke” BBQ sauce as much as we enjoy providing it for you. ','704-637-9351 ','blowinsmoke@bellsouth.net ','Jack Moore','','','','www.blowinsmokebbqsauce.com ','','P O Box 4072 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28145 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:36','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('82bc27ab-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Mr. Tommy\'s Firewood  ','Mr. Tommy\'s Firewood is a family owned and operated business that believes in providing quality products and personalized service. As a family, we have been supplying customers with quality wood products for over 30 years and in the past 3 years have expanded to serve the North Carolina\'s firewood needs. We work hard to serve our customers with integrity and provide them with quality that they can depend on.     We currently split, wrap and ship all of our own bundles as well as offer additional fire-starter products, such as Lighter-Knot Kindling and EZ Fire Fire-starter.     We also offer heat treating options and are currently certified under the NC Pest Compliance Agreement #2483, meeting Fla. 5B-65 Regulation. ','336-284-6358 ','mrtommysfirewood@gmail.com ','Nicole Grissom','','Monday-Thursday 7:00-5:30 ','','www.mrtommysfirewood.com ','','PO Box 538 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27054 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:36','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('82bd9abc-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Patterson Farm Inc. ','Patterson Farm Inc. is a third generation produce and plant farm specializing in tomatoes and strawberries. We offer school tours by appointment in April, May, September October an