1e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Lazy 5 Ranch  ','The Lazy 5, located between interstates 85 and 77 in Piedmont, North Carolina, features over 700 animals from around the world. On your 3 1/2 mile safari through the gently sloping pasturelands, you will experience animals from six continents.     Take plenty of time to study their behavior from the safety of your own car or make reservations for one of our horse drawn wagon rides. This is a drive-through experience unique in North Carolina. There is no other collection of animals like this in the Southeast. ','704-663-5100 ','lazy5ranch@aol.com ','Wendy Wilson','','Monday thru Saturday we open at 9am and Sundays we open at 1pm, Everyday we close one hour before sunset.','','www.lazy5ranch.com ','','15100 Hwy 150 East ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28115 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:36','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('82cd0dc9-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','NEW MOON FARM  ','New Moon Farm is dedicated to the principle of sustainable agriculture and to the standards of the non-chemical method of growing produce for the market at large. Our goal is to maintain the highest standard of all-natural production and to provide information and assistance to anyone interested in the philosophy non-chemical farming practices.      Here at the Farm, we mainly grow heirloom and open-pollinated varieties, never GMO. We also practice the art of saving our own seeds year to year, whenever possible. We use organic seed sources for the varieties that we grow. Our varieties are chosen for taste, production, natural hardiness and disease/pest resistance. We do not use chemical or synthetic fertilizers, pesticides, soil additives or any other polymerized medium for growing any of our produce. You may be assured that we adhere not only to the USDA regulated standards for the production of our crops, but in many cases attempt to exceed those standards, based on our own personal philosophies about permaculture and sustainable agriculture. We are USDA CERTIFIED ORGANIC!     New Moon Farm offers the finest in fresh, locally grown CERTIFIED ORGANIC produce. ','704-799-0185 ','newmoonfarm@alltel.net ','Suzanne Ballard','','The Farm is open to visits by apointment only, April thru October.','','www.newmoonfarmorganic.com ','','1420 Belk Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28125 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:36','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('82ce78eb-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','New Moon Farm ','Located in western Rowan county, New Moon Farm grows a wide assortment of certified organic produce, specializing in heirloom, ethnic and gourmet varieties, in addition to tried and true Southern staples. Since most of our veggies are picked less than a day before they are delivered to our customers, you will not find fresher, more delicious produce, unless you grow it yourself!     At the Farm, we strive to promote the concepts of biodiversity, sustainable farming practices and a healthful, natural lifestyle for all. We believe that eating local organically grown produce, in season, is one of the best ways to provide optimum nutrition for yourself and your family.     New Moon Farm uses a unique system of distribution for our products. Through our CSA program, customers are able to take advantage of our wonderful selection of fresh, hand picked produce from April through November. ','','newmoonfarm@alltel.net ','Suzanne Ballard','','Farmer\'s market hours are 8am until noon','','www.newmoonfarmorganic.com ','','1420 Belk Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28125 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:36','a1c3e20e-