J Ranch  ','Jake got started showing sheep in 2003 at the Rowan County Fair. Our neighbor, Carlyle Sherrill asked Jake if he wanted to show some of his Gert\'s, and here we are.    After showing at many county fairs, NCJBRU, National Santa Gertrudis Heifer Show in Texas, Clemson & NC State Fair, Jake has made many new friends throughout the past year or so.     In October 2004, Jake purchased his first Gert from our friends in Asheboro at Ingold Farms. Terry & Debbie and all the Ingolds have been great friends, and have been very helpful with any questions we have had about our first heifer. ','704-663-5725 ','sawdust65@alltel.net ','Jake or Jeff Smith','','Most every evening after 4:30pm, and most every weekend','','','','515 Jones Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28125 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:36','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('82d32f07-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Yoder\'s Amish Market  ','Yoder\'s Amish Market is a locally owned, family-run Amish style country store. Come let our old fashioned quality products, aromas of spices and seasonings, even the smoky mountain hymns playing in the background transport you to a bygone era where shopping was fun and personal, quality was just something you expected, and you could leave the store feeling good about life and looking forward to savoring that homemade apple fried pie in your bag. So come on out, shop a while, sip some Kutztown Birch Beer and enjoy the peaceful country atmosphere. ','704.636.5660 ','liz@yodersamishmarket.com','Liz Smith','','Monday-Saturday 9am-5:30pm ','','www.yodersamishmarket.com ','','4077 Statesville Blvd. ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28147 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:36','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('82d48930-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Golden Valley Honey','Golden Valley Honey is owned by Master Beekeeper Jeanne Price and is operated by her and her three grandchildren, Zach, Lauren and Grace Moore. ','828-247-1640 ','carolinabeelady@gmail.com ','Jeanne Price','','','','goldenvalleyhoney.org ','','182 Elizabeth Ave ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28043 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:36','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('82d6298e-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','K.W.Gettys Farm','THE FARM: The K.W. Gettys Farm in Rutherford County, NC is located on the side of Cherry Mountain in the heart of the most rural section of the county. This has been a family-owned and operated working farm for well over 100 years. We use about 180 acres to feed and raise our cattle. They are pasture and hay-fed, with grain added to finish the calves we harvest. We grow our calves naturally without feeding antibiotics or adding hormones to increase weight gain. Our cattle receive recommended vaccinations and routine treatment for parasites.     THE BEEF: The beef we offer are healthy, young (under 24 months) and are born and raised in our pastures. We sell beef by the quarter, half or whole. Finished quarters will be 100-130 lbs. (although there will be variations either up or down). The USDA inspects your beef at a Taylorsville butcher\'s shop. Quarters hang for as long as possible to age (aging improves flavor) before being trimmed closely, cut, wrapped and frozen.     PURCHASE THE BEEF: Each quarter will include steaks, roasts, stew beef and ground beef. Steaks will be sliced 3/4\" thick and packaged 1-2 per package. Roasts will be 1 to a package. Stew beef and ground beef will be packaged 1 lb. to a package. The beef is $5.00/lb with a required $50.00 to hold each quarter. The $50 deposit will be credited toward the final bill. Beef will be packaged (vacuum packed in clear package) and ready for customer pickup at the butcher in Taylorsville on a specified date. ','828-453-7485 ','','Polly Gettys','','If you miss us, please leave a message, We are in and out of the house, but we will return your call, Please do not call after 9pm. ','','','','1126 Gettys Rd ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28040 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:36','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('82d7a91a-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','LAKESIDE MILLS, INC. ','Lakeside Mills has been producing stone ground corn meal products in North Carolina since 1736. Our history is long and rich. The mill was used to supply the Continental troops in the fields as well as Lenoir County during the Revolutionary war. During the Civil War, much fighting took place near the original mill site, which still stands on US Highway 70 east of Kinston. The mill is situated on Kelly\'s pond, which is over 300 acres and was once a major recreation area with its fishing, picnicking, swimming and boating facilities. Lakeside Mills was owned by several different families before it was purchased in 1929 by the King family, where it has remained for four generations. Incorporated in 1968, Lakeside has seen many changes, from the direct delivery of our products within a 30 mile radius to a complete modern distribution of Lakeside brands to grocery and foodservice warehouses in ten southeastern states.    We take pride in providing to our customers the old southern style of corn meal and flour products that they have used for generations. Lakeside Mills has corn meal, flour, grits, hushpuppy mixes, biscuit mix, seafood breaders, chicken breader, frying breaders, and pancake mix. Corn meal products are available as roller ground or stone ground with the exception of grits, which are roller ground. All of our products are available in southeastern United States grocery stores and restaurants.    The fifth generation of King\'s is now starting out, as did their fathers. The treat of going to the mill, the excitement of the big trucks coming and going, the grain trucks as they unload their grain for daddy, and of course the food shows where they can ','828-286-4866 ','sales@LakesideMills.com ','BRYAN KING','','','','www.LakesideMills.com ','','PO BOX 230 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28139 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:36','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('82d8b232-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Spring Hill Merchant','Spring Hill Merchant offers unique and wonderful items exclusively from Western North Carolina. We offer a wide selection of food and hand crafted items made from the wonderful farmers, artisians and crafters in this region.      Browse our products. Create a personalized gift basket for a family member, friend or business associate. Our products make thoughtful corporate gifts that showcase the best this region has to offer. When you buy from us, you are buying products made in America. ','(877)891-6389 ','terri.watts@springhillmerchant.com','Terri Watts','','24 hours','','www.SpringHillMerchant.com ','','PO Box 533 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28018 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:36','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('82da1c87-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Babbling Brook Farm  ','Babbling Brook Farms is a small animal farm raising pygmy meat goats, ducks, turkys and peacocks. We keep a few guinea hens also to keep down the bug population though the ducks, turkeys and peacocks help a lot also. We feed our animals grains, scratch but also allow the animals to range feed. Because of this we seldom have an insect problem.      This year we are also starting into organic farming techniques. We have been preparing ground according to organic methods using organic materials. We are aiming for a fall harvest of carrots, beets, radishes and onions ','828-248-1739 ','babblingbrookfarm@gmail.com','Lauretta Huffman','','We are open between 9am and 5pm Monday thru Friday but will be available if called for special pick up times.','','www.babblingbrookfarm.com ','','360 Hermitage Trail ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28040 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:36','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('82db80e1-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','behelerfarm ','the farm is located in western north carolina. our produce is figs and vegetables which we are trying to sell this year.we are located in hopewell,just out of ellenboro,n.c.','8284472580','behelerfarm@gmail.com ','carolcooper','','by appointment only.','','','','539 glover road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28040 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:36','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('82dc5f65-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','brantley farms1 ','we use pure bred angus or balancer bulls','828 245 5548 ','jerrybrantley2@Qyahoo.com','jerry brantley','','9am to 5pm mondy thru Saturday','','www. brantley farms .com ','','509 griffin road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28043 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:36','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('82dd2ca3-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Cabin Creek Farm ','Cabin Creek Farm is a work in progress. We are committed to sustainable, year round farming practices which are designed to yield health and nutritious products for the family table. ','828-212-4727 ','mabrooks28@gmail.com ','Marshall and Susan Brooks','','TBA ','','','','5940 US 64/74A Hwy ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28746 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:36','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('82de7bca-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','DBA TOMATO FARM','DBA TOMATO FARM is a sole proprietor that has been in existence for 2 years. I raise good, tasty, healthy tomatoes. They are naturally grown chemical-free. Customers can\'t get enough. ','828-245-8585 ','abcusedtires@yahoo.com ','Donald B. Abrams','','Hours of operation are 6:00 a.m. - 6:00 p.m., Monday - Saturday.','','www.dbatomatofarm.com ','','130 Dillashaw Drive ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28043 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:36','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('82dffb8d-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Four Foot Farm  ','Located in the Oakland Community of Rutherford County, Four Foot Farm is situated on 78 acres of farm land which has been in the same family for over 100 years. The original farm house, built in 1848, is a lovely example of Federal architecture with a southern style veranda across the front offering views of the front pasture and vegetable gardens. Dogwoods, crepe myrtles, magnolias, azaleas, and old growth oaks provide a profusion of seasonal interest.     Currently run by business partners Jill Maner and Paula Wilson, Four Foot Farm produces rabbits, poultry, eggs, goats, goat products, cut flowers, bedding plants, transplants and a variety of vegetables all grown using sustainable methods. Our produce is grown on land which has been fallow for over fifty years. We strive to provide our clients with a variety of current favorites, heirloom standbys, and European imports.     We market our produce and cut flowers through FootHills Connect\'s Virtual Farmers\' Fresh Market to restaurants in Charlotte, N.C., Foothills Connect Farmers\' Tailgate Market in Rutherford County and the tailgate markets in Columbus, and Tryon, N.C. as well as from our own on site produce stand which is open afternoons from 2pm to 8pm. ','828-305-0871 ','4footfarm@gmail.com ','Jill Maner/Paula Wilson','','Currently, Saturday afternoons by appointment, Hours will expand as the season progresses ','','','','850 Crowe Dairy Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28043 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:36','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('82e1719c-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Fresh Local Art & Produce Market','We are starting a new farmers market in Lake Lure NC because: 1. It supports local farmers. 2. It saves the fuel and other resources needed to ship produce across the country. 3. It puts fresh food on the table a€“ food that was harvested at its peak rather than weeks before it was ready. 4. It avoids some of the health concerns noted in recent headlines about non-local peanuts, jalapenos and tomatoes. 5. Best of all, fresh, locally grown food just tastes better!     Since over 40,000 visitors come to Lake Lure every year, and many of them are looking for art, combining art and produce seems like a natural. And make no mistake: this will not be a yard sale or flea market. All art must be pre-approved by the F.L.A.P. Market art jury.     The Fresh Local Art & Produce Market, or F.L.A.P. Market for short, will meet on Tuesday mornings April 21-September 29, 2009. ','828-691-5009 ','ken@lakeguys.com ','Ken Jordan','','Tuesdays 8am-1pm ','','FLAPMarket.com ','','Jack London Rd and Memorial Hwy ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28746 ','','','','20