ible we purchase our provisions directly from the manufacturing source. Nielsen-Massey supplies our vanilla and our strawberry preserves are made just down the road in Winston-Salem by the family-owned TW Garner Food Company.     Our Butterbars are our specialty niche, and we take great pride in the quality of our products and the flavor selection we offer. We hope you and your customers, or gift recipients, enjoy indulging in them as much as we enjoy baking them. ','336-374-6318 ','patti@uppercrustcrumbs.com ','Patti','','N/A - We are a wholesale bakery and sell direct only through our website.','','www.uppercrustcrumbs.com ','','Foothills of the \r\nBlue Ridge Mountains','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:37','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('83553fa0-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Circle P Farm  ','We have been farming since 1984. We started with 2 riding horses,and have growed alot over the years. We purchased several head of cattle. And started mowing and putting up hay and grew corn for feed. Raising baby calfs on bottles. Now in the past 6 yrs, we have change some, but still have horses and cattle. There are lots of new projects.This year we added 14 bee hives,and have got the diary gots on a milking schedule. We have always had chickens running free range. Ducks to feed at the farm pond.The sheep arrived last year. ','336-366-5046 ','circlepfarm1984@yahoo.com','Ronnie Payne','','Monday-Saturday 8:00 - 7:00 Please call: 336-366-5046','','www.circlepfarm.com ','','P.O. Box 742 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27017 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:37','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('83562690-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Old North State Winery Inc,','','336-789-9463 ','Ben@oldnorthstatewinery.com','Ben Webb','','','','www.oldnorthstatewinery.com ','','308 N. Main St ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27030 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:37','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('8357f8cb-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Black Wolf Vineyards ','\"Black Wolf Vineyards\" and \"The Wolf\'s Lair\" restaurant are co-located in the \"Yadkin Valley Wine Country\" in Dobson, Surry County, N.C. We feature wines made only from the grapes grown here at \"Black Wolf Vineyards\". Our wine tasting room, on the second floor of \"The Wolf\'s Lair\" restaurant, offers the following Black Wolf Vineyards wines. *Red Wines* Cabernet Sauvignon Reserve - Oak Barrel Fermented, supple with great intensity, uncommon depth and concentrated flavors. Cabernet Sauvignon - Robust, deep and full bodied. True elegance and finesse. Chambourcin - Intense bouquet and taste with a hint of herbs and spice. Pinot Noir - Intimate, moody, dark as a stormy night. Powerful and subtle with an agreeable finish. Sweet Wolf Red - Charmingly pleasant, easygoing wine. A kiss rather than a bite. *White Wines* Chardonnay Reserve - Oak Barrel Fermented. Creamy and dry, with good fruit flavor. One of the best! Chardonnay - Fruity, excellent bouquet with much breed. Blue Moon White - Velvety, soft and mellow. Refreshing and pleasant Sauvignon Blanc - A well made wine. Dry, clear and brilliant. A product of cooperation between man and nature. Perfect for celebrations. Seyval Blanc - Complex, dry and altogether excellent. Consistently exhibits the finesse and delicacy of the Black Wolf line of fine wines. Moonlight White - Sauvignon Blanc with a light peach flavor. The sweetness of summer fruit and first romance. Try our \"Wine Flights\". Tastings just $6.00 for a 2 oz. pour. \"Big Bad Wolf\" - 3 White Wines \"Red Riding Hood\" - 3 Red Wines \"Howl at the Moon\" - 3 Sweet Wines or do it all.... 12 Wine Tastings and a free \"Black Wolf Vineyards\" Souvenir Wine Glass for $5.00 per person. Tasting Hours: Monday to Saturday - 11 am to 2:30 pm and on Sunday - Noon to 4 pm.      \"The Wolf\'s Lair\" is a gourmet restaurant that has been featured in newspapers, magazines, on radio and television. It has been rated \"4 STARS\" by the Greensboro News and Record and \"3 DIAMONDS\" by AAA. Our Chef, Adam Williams, has the expertise and experience to tantalize your taste buds with Magnificent Entrees such as Grilled Loin of Elk, Pan Seared Filet Mignon, Grilled Salmon, Fresh Rainbow Trout, Braised Free Range Chicken with Fusilli Pasta, Roasted Rack of Lamb with Cassolet, Grilled Pork Tenderloin with Hoppin John and Roasted Duckling with Coffee Orange Glaze. Dine in soft candlelight in The Grand Room in front of a huge stone fireplace or in The Wolf Room which features a large stained glass window with the Black Wolf Vineyards crest. For large parties we have The Gallery a room for meetings and social gatherings. Restaurant Hours: Lunch - Monday thru Saturday 11 am to 2:30 pm. Dinner- Thursday thru Saturday 5 pm to 10 pm. Open Sunday 12 Noon to 8 pm. Reservations are recommended. TEL: 336 374-2532 FAX: 336 374-3496 WEB: www.blackwolfvineyards.com','336 374-2532 ','wolfslair@surry.net ','Dana Theis','','Restaurant Hours: Lunch: Monday thru Saturday 11 am to 2:30 pm, Dinner: Thursday thru Saturday 5 pm to 10 pm, Sunday: Noon to 8 pm. Reservations are recommended.','','www.blackwolfvineyards.com ','','283 Vineyard Ln. ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27017 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:37','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('8358de42-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Blue Mountain Shiitake  ','Blue Mountain Shiitake, located in the foothills of the Blue Ridge has been growing mushrooms 20 years and has been selling to restaurants and farmers markets commercially for 2 years. We grow our mushrooms organically ','336-320-2078 ','dwight.seal@ncmail.net ','Dwight Seal','','No certain hours mostly weekend, Should call prior to coming','','','','813 West Imogene Ch Rd ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27030 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:37','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('835a7efa-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Carolina Heritage Vineyard & Winery  ','The mission of Carolina Heritage Vineyard & Winery is to deliver sustainably-grown fruit and honey bee products which are reasonably priced and promote a healthy environment and lifestyle for all involved: our neighbors, our customers and our family.      Carolina Heritage Vineyards was established in 2005 on a farm three miles east of Elkin on Highway 268 in the middle of the Yadkin Valley Viticultural Area (AVA.)     With a commitment to organic viticultural practices, varieties of grapes were chosen which are native to this region and/or are disease and insect resistant. Eight acres have been planted with Muscadines (Noble, Doreen, and Carlos) and American varietals and hybrids (Cynthiana, Rubiana (GR-7), Traminette and Chambourcin.) In addition 1.5 acres of blueberries have been planted along with initial apple and pear trees and trial kiwi, elderberries, cranberries and rhubarb plants. All are being actively pollinated by bees from the vineyard\'s hives.     The vineyard, fruit and honey bees are doing very well, as are the vineyard\'s chickens and guinea fowl (whose job it is to ensure insect pests do not damage the vines.) Third-leaf vines produced strong fruit for their first harvest in 2008 and are well on their way for a great 2009 harvest and wine production! ','336 366-3301 ','','Clyde & Pat Colwell','','Tours/tastings: Saturdays and Sundays from 1-6PM or by appointment - call (336)366-3301.','','carolinaheritagewinery.com ','','170 Heritage Vines Way ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28621','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:37','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('835bf932-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Horne Creek Farm State Historic Site ','At Horne Creek Living Historical Farm, a multi-year project is underway to reconstruct the physical environment and seasonal work cycle of an early 20th century North Carolina family farm. Visitors may visit an apple orchard featuring vintage southern apple varieties no longer grown or watch as staff experiment with traditional log construction techniques. You can try your hand at cutting grass with a scythe or listen to an elderly woman explain how to make lye soap. Through educational programs ranging from lessons on how to cook on a wood stove to white oak basket making workshops to an annual corn shucking frolic, Horne Creek Living Historical Farm provides a unique opportunity to learn about our rural past. ','336/325-2298 ','lisa.turney@ncmail.net ','Lisa Turney','','Tuesday - Saturday 10 a.m.-4 p.m., Closed Sunday and Monday. ','','www.ah.dcr.state.nc.us/sections/hs/horne/horne.htm ','','308 Horne Creek Farm Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27043 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:37','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('835cdae2-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Hutton Vineyards LLC ','','336-374-2621 ','malcolm@huttonwinery.com','Malcolm Hutton','','Every day 12 noon to 6:00 PM ','','huttonwinery.com ','','176 Hutton Vineyards ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27017 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:37','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('835e49dc-62e8-11e1-b30d-10