zes in everything from tobacco harvesters to greenhouse equipment. We carry name brands such as: DeCloet, Mahindra, Valtra, Husqvarna,just to name a few. We, at PT Equipment Co.,Inc. take great pride in the service that we provide on all our products.    PT Equipment Co., Inc. would like to thank you for your support. If we can be of any service to you, please call us at 800-645-4264. ','800-645-4264 ','piedtobacco@surry.net ','Gary Hodges or David Haynes','','Monday-Friday 8:00am-5:00pm, Saturday 8:00am-12:00pm','','www.piedmonttobaccoequipment.com ','','105 Lola Lane (intersection of 52 and 268) ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27041 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:37','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('836578e3-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Soaring Eagle Farm','We are a small family run farm at the foothills of the Blue Ridge Mountains. We raise many animals including milk goats and bees. All of our baked products have no preservatives.','336-366-4053 ','questions@soaringeaglefarm.com','Dori Fritzinger','','','','soaringeaglefarm.com ','','565 John\'s Pond Lane ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27017 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:37','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('83674501-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Trotting C Farm ','At Trotting C Farm, we have bred, raised, trained and shown horses, dogs, and other livestock since the early 1970\'s. It is our goal to produce the most correct and near perfect animal possible by combining the top bloodlines in the industry with emphasis on outstanding conformation, beautiful color, and super disposition! Our Miniature Horses are registered with the American Miniature Horse Association (AMHA) and most are also registered with the American Miniature Horse Registry (AMHR). We are members of the American Boer Goat Association (ABGA) and the International Boer Goat Association (IBGA). Our Boer Goats carry the industry\'s top genetics with multiple ennoblements in their pedigrees. We have both 100% South African, percentage, and commercial goats for sale. We are also breeders of Miniature Donkeys and offer a good selection of breeding stock and young donkeys for sale at most times. We also breed Chihuahuas, and Great Pyrenees and our dogs are AKC and/or CKC registered. We normally have a couple of litters a year so if you are interested please contact us and we can tell you what is available or place you on our waiting list.     Trotting C Sales Co. was established in 1996 when we acquired a partnership in the Mount Airy Miniature Horse Sale. Over the years we have grown the sale company as well as expanding our company\'s footprint in the ever growing market. Our partner in the Mount Airy Sale was killed in a tragic farm tractor accident in January 1999 and we are now the sole proprietors of the oldest miniature horse sale in the world. The Mount Airy Miniature Horse Sale has been in continuous operation since November 1986 originally holding two sales a year and three sales a year since 1995. We have expanded the sale business to include managing and/or working sales in multiple states including North Carolina, Virginia, West Virginia, Delaware, Texas, Florida, and Georgia. Ronnie is a past President of the AMHA and served six years on the B.O.D. and three years on the Executive Committee and is a licensed and bonded auctioneer in multiple states. Janet is a sale manager having managed the office for some of the biggest production and consignment sales in the industry. Ronnie, Janet, and their family and staff are very knowledgeable and well known in the Miniature Horse Industry and offer professional services putting their experience and reputation to work for you. Being well know by both the sellers and consignors and having extensive knowledge of the top breeders and bloodlines is a great advantage to the sales and if we can help you with your future sales whether it is a production, consignment, reduction, or dispersal sale, from just professional auctioneer to a turn key job of complete management, or anywhere in between please let us know.     If you are interested in our animals or sales and would like to visit, please don\'t hesitate to call, fax, or e-mail us. We look forward to meeting you! Breeding For Excellence - Visitors Always Welcome - Come See The Difference','336-326-7400 ','trottingc@yahoo.com ','Ronnie or Janet Clifton','','By appointment','','www.trottingc.com ','','1486 Round Peak Church Rd. ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','',' 27024 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:37','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('83683777-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Zodiac Nursery ','','336-374-5773 ','gingerhemmings@yahoo.com','Chad Hemmings','','Open by appointment','','','','168 Allred Lane ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27017 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:37','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('83699d7d-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Cherokee Bottled Water  ','Cherokee Bottled Water is an enterprise of the Eastern Band of Cherokee Indians. It was created in 1998 to market the exceptionally good water that flows through the Cherokee Indian reservation in Western North Carolina.     Our bottled water has won numerous awards for taste, including the gold medal at the 2002 Berkeley Springs International Water Tasting Contest. Many of our customers have told us that once they have tried our water they won\'t settle for anything other brand. ','828-497-1857 ','gregduff@nc-cherokee.com ','Greg Duff','','Office hours are 7:45 a.m. to 4:30 p.m., Monday through Friday except for federal holidays.','','www.cherokeebottledwater.com ','','P.O. Box 488 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28719 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:37','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('836a98a7-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','A Blueberry Farm  ','Originally, we planted a blueberry patch to supplement the family menu. Soon, the bushes were producing enough to supply the neighborhood. After a fire burned several acres of pine trees, we replanted a half acre with blueberries. This was the start of A Blueberry Farm.     A Blueberry farm is run by John Boaze along with the assistance of his wife, children and grandchildren. The bushes are located beside the family\'s business office, providing colorfull foliage throughout the year as well as summer snacks for the office staff.     Approximately 150 adult bushes provide the majority of the crop, with younger bushes in various stages of development also producing. There are nine varities of blueberries on the farm, ripening from late June through to frost. The farm is primarily a U-Pick field, but orders are taken and filled for those who are not able to pick for themselves.','828-497-7253 ','info@shadetreecabins.com ','John Boaze','','July through September, dawn to dusk ','','','','25 Water Tower Lane ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28789 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:37','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('836c1bd2-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Alpacas of Nantahala ','We raise Suri Alpacas for show, breeding, and excellent fleece. We shear each year and send our fleece to a Co-op to have products made here in the USA to sell in our farm store.    We have currently 10 Alpacas on the farm the youngest is 7 months old with 5 Crias (Baby)Alpacas in the early fall of 2009.    Please call for an appointment to visist the farm. We also have a miniature donkey that loves attention from everyone. ','828 321 3165 ','Patrick@AlpacasofNantahala.com','Patrick Graham','','By appoinment but most weekends we are here','','AlpacasOfNantahala.com ','','559 Grassy Branch Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28781 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:37','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('836da8a5-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Beautiful Day Farmers and Artists Market','In its third season, our market is still growing strong. We are a community of farmers, gardeners, and artists who envision breaking free of dependence upon chain-stores and corporations for our livelihoods and products.     We are always looking to add new vendors to our group- as long as the product is hand/locally made or grown within 50 miles of the Bryson City/Swain County area. We welcome all farmers, gardeners, and artists to join us each Saturday morning for a beautiful day!    Beautiful Day’s commitment to local agriculture and quality of life means that vendors offer produce grown within fifty miles of Bryson City that is delivered fresh to The Market on Saturday mornings. We are also committed to offering organic and certified organic produce and community farmers and gardeners are invited to bring produce to sell and to shop at The Market for the best of the truly fresh and local.     We also offer local artisans and crafters an outlet for marketing their works to local consumers. We welcome craft and art demonstrators, educators, and volunteers to help spread the word about our region and all it has to offer.     BD Market also encourages community groups to utilize the market as a fundraising outlet. Bring your group down and earn some $ for continuing and new projects. *all items must be locally grown/made.   Many of our farmers offer educational tours- ask when you visit! Many of our artisans offer demonstrations- see art before your eyes! You never know what you\'ll find on a Beautiful Day!','828-321-9810 ','beautifuldaymarket@yahoo.com','Nicole Denison','','Saturdays, 9:00 a.m.- 1:00 p.m.','','','','PO Box 449 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28713 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:37','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('836f1d44-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Nantahala Brewing Company, Inc. ','Located in the shadow of the Great Smoky Mountains National Park, Nantahala Brewing artfully brews award-winning, unfiltered ales made with fresh hops, whole grains and clean, crisp Great Smoky Mountain water, from one of the purest, protected watersheds on the planet.     The brewery is open daily for tours and tastings. Growlers (1/2 gallon) of our fresh ales are available for purchase at the brewery. ','828 488-6688 ','joe@nantahalabrewing.com ','Joe Rowland','','Noon until 8 pm daily. ','','www.nantahalabrewing.com ','','67 Depot Street ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28713 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:37','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('836ff50d-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Sacred Circle Farm and Nursery ','','828 497 4856 ','taxicatt@aol.com ','Joseph Redcloud','','','','sacredcirclesalves.com ','','144 Old Sherrill Cove Rd ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28719 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:37','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('83716bbe-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Full Circle Crab Company, Inc  ','We are 