ket the very best North Carolina made Dairy Products.   Look for the \"Got to be NC Dairy Products\" label! http://www.ncagr.gov/markets/commodit/dairy/index.htm, http://www.ncdairyadvantage.com/, http://www.adga.org/, http://www.ncsu.edu/foodscience/dairy/howlingcow/index.html ','336-402-5817 ','steven.lathrop@ncagr.gov ','Steve Lathrop','','We are serving 24/7 ','','www.gottobencdairy ','','2 West Edenton ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27699 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:38','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('842a98f6-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Gracewood Farm Paso Fino Horses  ','Gracewood Farm, since 1975, specializes in the breeding and sales of quality, versatile, pleasure, smooth gaited Paso Finos with friendly and willing dispositions. They sell their Paso Fino horses to many first time horse owners and first time Paso Fino owners all over the USA. The herd stallion also has offspring located in Canada. Visitors are welcome by appointment or at Gracewood Farm\'s Open House. Test rides on a Paso Fino are available to experience the smooth ride.     Gracewood Farm stands at stud to approved Paso Fino mares -- Emperador La Estrella, a beautiful very natural gaited, grulla Paso Fino stallion. He has produced 65% fillies, all colors with many being black, grulla and dun with the primitive stripe markings. His heritage is from Colombia, South America. His stud fee is $1000 with a $200 discount booked by April 1st. There are offspring available for sale and for viewing.     Gracewood Farm\'s owner Lynn Gallup is a Gaited Horse Show Judge for Paso Finos, Rocky Mountain Horses, and Kentucky Mountain Horses. Her judging affiliations include: PFHA, USEF, RMHA, UMH. Available are 1 hour Gaited Horsemanship Riding Lessons to help people improve their riding skills, equitation, horsemanship, to know how to get their horse gaiting more correctly, and to improve their showring skills. A Paso Fino Video Consultation can evaluate a horse for their value, aptitude, conformation, gait and qualities for the purposes of insurance, breeding, proposed stallion selection, sale or purchase. Unbridled Visions can design and help market your agricultural, horse business or club with a custom designed website, logo, photo editing, and/or graphic design. Our slogan is Creativity at Full Gallop! More can be seen at www.unbridledvisions.com ','919-362-5966 ','info@gracewoodpasos.com ','Lynn Gallup','','Visitors by private appointment, Week day and weekend appointments are available. ','','www.smoothride4u.com ','','4316 Old US 1 Hwy. ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27562 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:38','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('842c2b62-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Green Acres Farm','Our farm is located on the West side of Cary. This farm has been in my family for over 110 years in a continous farming operation. We are the fourth generation to live in our house which was build by my great grandfather Charles Ferrell in the year 1900. Many of the original farm buildings are still in place today. Myself, my wife Beth and daughter Sarah reside here today.     Our farm produced Flue-Cured Tobacco up until 2000 when we decided to discontinue the tobacco to pursue other business interest. It is still an active farm today producing Soybeans and is operating a Cow/Calf beef operation.     Development has come our way in the past 20 years. We welcome the new people and hope to be able to provide them with the beauty of our farm that we have been so blessed to retain. We have had to diversify into other farm options due to the loss of surrounding land to development. We think that you will find our farm a welcoming place that you can relax and enjoy. God has blessed us and as Christians we welcome everyone. ','919-481-2435 ','baccaman@aol.com ','David Ferrell','','','','','','1132 Morrisville-Carpenter Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27519 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:38','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('842dc169-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Greenlevel Gourd Farm  ','Virgil Jockisch grows 15 varieties of gourds and his wife Sandy decorates them. Their farm in Greenlevel Community outside of Apex and Cary and has been in the family since 1916. Virgil sells pumpkins, gourds, and also offers a spooky Halloween hayride Wednesday though Sunday 10:00 - 6:00 during the month of October. Admission is $4 per person. Small babies are free. Admission ticket includes a free spooky hayride, access to playground and picnic area. Pumpkins and gourds are priced individually.      The gourd gift shop is open 6 days a week year round by appointment (call 919-387-7352). It features seasonal decorations and unique gifts for everyone. You will find everything from baskets, bowls, Christmas decorations and ornaments, and jewelry made from the versatile gourd.      Green Level Gourd Farm offers birthday parties for young children. Children enjoy hayrides, donkey rides, games, crafts,face painting, and farm animals. Call for party prices. ','919-387-7352 ','sandrajockisch@att.net ','Sandy Jockisch','','10:00 to 6:00 PM Wednesday - Sunday during the month of October for pumpkins and hay rides, Gourd gift shop is open year round by appointment, Birthday parties are offered during the months of April and September, Call 919-387-7352. ','','greenlevelgourdfarm.com ','','3800 Greenlevel Rd. West ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27523 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:38','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('842f2f55-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','GroWild ','GroWild was founded by Amanda in Raleigh, NC, on a tiny budget and in a small kitchen. She wanted to create food that had unique flavor without compromising nutrition. GroWild hopes to inspire people to make the right choices for themselves, their family, and Mother Earth.     GroWild is about offering healthy food, without sacrificing the choice to make a positive impact on our planet. ','919-556-5683 ','info@growild.net ','Amanda Harriman','','','','www.growild.net ','','P.O. Box 99432 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27624 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:38','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('8430176c-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','H & H Organic Farms','Currently, we sell CSA\'s the first quarter of each year and then we furnish produce during the growing season to people who have purchased a CSA(community supported agriculture)     We also intend to grow excess produce each year that may be purchased by anyone who wants to purchase organic produceand who want to be added to our e-mail list. ','919-783-9245 ','H-H-OrganicFarms@nc.rr.com ','Tom Hewitt/ Trish Haney','','','','','','5328 Collingswood Drive ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27609','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:38','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('8431bf5b-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Hilltop Farms  ','Hilltop Farm of Willow Springs is a USDA Certified Organic produce farm that adheres to strict organic and sustainable agricultural practices. This ensures the consumer of safe and reliable growing methods and healthy foods. We are committed to growing in a completely natural and sustainable way that protects the soil and the health of our farm members. We will use NO PESTICIDES, HERBICIDES, FUNGICIDES, OR ARTIFICIAL FERTILIZERS on our crops. We provide a connection that has been lost in recent decades between consumers and the land on which their food is grown. Our members share in the risk and the bounty that nature provides.     We operate a modified version of a Community Supported Agriculture venture (CSA). We distribute on a weekly basis to families who become members of the farm. A set number of memberships are offered in the winter and spring prior to the growing season. Members pay in advance for the food they will receive throughout the months of May through October. This advance payment allows the farm to purchase seed and other materials needed to grow the food, and allows the members to become partners in the farming process.     Members may come to the farm on the designated pick-up day to receive their weekly “share” or choose to attend one of the drop-sites in either Cary or Raleigh, NC. We grow: Beans, Blueberries,Bok Choi, Broccoli, Cabbage, Cantaloupe, Corn, Cucumbers, Eggplant, Kale, Lettuces, Onions, Okra, Peas, Peppers, Potatoes, Radishes, Spinach, Squash, Strawberries, Sweet Potatoes, Swiss Chard, Tomatoes, Turnips, Watermelons, Zucchini, Flowers & Herbs. We also offer farm tours of our organic fields and greenhouse, and our horse barn and pastures. ','919 552-5541 ','info@hilltopfarms.org ','Fred Miller','','Call the farm to reserve tour hours, CSA deliveries are Monday at the farm, Wednesday to Raleigh, and Thursday to Cary. ','','www.hilltopfarms.org ','','6612 Kennebec Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27592 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:38','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('8433655f-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Historic Oak View County Park','Originally founded in the 1830s and once encompassing more than 900 acres, Historic Oak View County Park is a historic farmstead listed on the National Register of Historic Places. Included on the site are five historic buildings: c. 1825 Plank Kitchen, c. 1855 Main Farmhouse, and the Carriage House, Cotton Gin House, and Livestock Barn, all c. 1900.     A day at Historic Oak View County Park offers visitors a variety of cultural, educational, agricultural, and recreational activities. This 27-acre site includes a number of historic buildings and the Farm History Center, a museum dedicated to telling the story of North Carolina\'s agricultural development. Visitors are also welcomed to enjoy the park grounds by strolling through the pecan grove, fruit orchard, and herb garden, picnicking, or fishing in the pond.     Historic Oak View County Park\'s mission is to interpret the agricultural heritage and rural history of North Carolina through educational programs, special events and exhibitions, while also providing recreational opportunities. ','(919)250-1013 ','oakview@wakegov.com ','Sara Drumheller','','Monday - Saturday 8:30 - 5:00, Sunday 1:00 - 5:00 ','','www.wakegov.com/parks/oakview ','','4028 Carya Drive ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27610','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:38','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('8434f728-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Holy Smokes BBQ  ','Holy Smokes is a family owned and operated business and a long-time dream of two brothers; Troy and Kyle Hogue. They grew up in Raleigh and attended Wake Christian Academy. Their vision is one of hospitality and serving customers the kind of down-home bar-b-que, they first had as children; pig pickins in the backyard with deck and lawn chairs full of friends and family enjoying good food and lots of laughter.     Kyle Hogue is a graduate of Lee University in Cleveland, Tennessee with a BS Degree in Business Administration . Troy\'s has a Culinary Of Arts Degree and a BS Degree in Food Service Management from Johnson Wales University in Charleston, South Carolina.     Get ready for bar-b-que with a new attitude. Chef Troy along with his brother Kyle take great pleasure in providing expertly smoked meats for the folks of Raleigh, North Carolina. Troy has had years of experience as a a€?pit mana€? at Rudya€?s Barbecue in San Antonio, Texas, where he became an expert in smoking beef brisket, pork barbecue, pork and beef ribs, chicken, sausage, and smoked turkey to perfection. The secret is in Troya€?s own Holy Smokes Rubs and bar-b-cue sauces. Kyle\'s years of experience in food service, and his management expertise have helped to make Holy Smokes Bar-B-Que one of Raleigh\'s best Restaurants. ','919-661-BBQ1, 2271 ','sjhogue@nc.rr.com ','Troy Hogue','','11:00 am to 8:30 pm, Monday -- Thursday 11:00 am to 9:00 pm Friday and Saturday, Closed Sunday ','','www.holysmokesnc.com ','','335 Tryon Rd ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27603 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:38','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('84366b69-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','InFusion Foods  ','Our name InFusion stands for Indian Fusion. We provide unique and exotic culinary experience by creating fusion foods well suited for an international pallette. We blend locally available produce with herbs and spices from all over the world using eastern cooking styles, in our own Indian Vegetarian Kitchen. We don\'t use any preservatives, artificial color and flavoring. None of our products contain wheat, oat, rye, barley, or malt (Gluten Free) or MSG.     If you would like to taste any of our product just stop by at our location and we will be delighted to offer you sampling oppurtunity ','919-345-7715 ','infusion@infusionfoods.com','Shirish Shevade','','','','www.InFusionFoods.com ','','113 Highlands Lake Drive ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-