ks to everyone who has helped support our business, and encouraged us to grow year after year! ','919-552-4635 ','Yamoonkey@aol.com ','R. L. Vaughan','','Monday through Saturday 8:00 to 6:30, Sunday 10:00 to 4:00 ','','beverly@ec.rr.com ','','824 Wilbon Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27540 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:39','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('8472e3fb-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Victory Catering Company','','9199541190','caterer@quixnet.net ','vernon griffin','','private parties ','','victorycatering.biz ','','8711 six forks rd, ste 104,','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27615','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:39','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('84747cd0-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','White Pear (Natural Bath and Body Products) ','From the start, we have strived to create products that stand apart from the rest by choosing the highest quality ingredients and beautiful scents that nourish body & soul and leave you feeling refreshed and renewed. We have carefully chosen simple bright colored labels that remind us of how bright nature and life can be.    At White Pear, we understand the importance of environmental friendliness and recognize our responsibility to be a good steward to the planet. We make natural biodegradable bath and body products. We do not test on animals - never have, never will. We use a great percentage of recycled copy paper for office work. We recycle our ink cartridges and batteries. We recycle our furniture (buy used and refurbished) whenever possible. We have a paperless order filing system. We use recyclable plastic containers. We open our windows to promote cross ventilation and save energy whenever possible. We recycle our trash, magazines, newspapers, etc. We recycle/reuse packaging and shipping material whenever possible. We do not water our lawn. We use a hybrid vehicle to conduct 90% of our business. We are committed to keep taking steps to help the environment as much as we can.     IN THE NEWS - White Pear was featured in The Life etc section of the News and Observer of Raleigh NC Monday April 13, 2009 as part of \"The Green Scene.\" - http://www.newsobserver.com/105/story/1480997-p2.html - And also featured in the June 2009 issue of Carolina Parent. - http://tinyurl.com/mnq5qr ','919-616-8794 ','cacosta@whitepearshop.com ','Claudia Acosta','','our website is open 24 hrs, Please visit our website for locations, please contact them for hours.','','www.whitepearshop.com ','','The Cotton Co - 306 S. White Street ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27587 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:39','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('84756ecf-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','WILDFLOUR PIZZA  ','Wildflour Pizza is all homemade delightful food. We make our famous salad dressing right in the restaurant. Wildflour has been serving Raleigh for over 17 years. We have received many awards for best pizza. Wildflour is family owned and operated      We offer accommodations for large parties and/or catering ','919-847-8982 ','bryantbubbajane@aol.com','KEN','','Everyday, 11:00am-10:30pm','','','','7456 Creedmoor Rd ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27613','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:39','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('8476e3f2-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','William E Smith Farm','Our farmhouse was originally my Great Aunt\'s, and for the last seven years, was a B&B. My great aunt took possession of her brother\'s home somewhere around 1900, when she married. She became the local egg lady, and she and my great uncle also served as the mail folks, to catch the mail off the train. They also offered cold drinks for sale to folks waiting for the train, as well as children who attended a near-by school. We ran the home as a B&B, until the end of 2008.     We have closed our B&B, and continue to farm goats and honey bees. We hope to do more agritourism beginning in 2013. Currently we are a private farm, and no longer offer tours. ','','fidge36457@mypacks.net ','','','','','','','7221 Sunset Lake Rd ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27526','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:39','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('8477cf75-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Williams Nursery & Produce','We offer a variety of shrubs, trees, seasonal produce and gardening needs. We now carry slate for gardens, water ponds, etc. We also have decorative seasonal flags. ','919-817-6056 ','WilliamsPlants@aol.com ','Beth & Lanny Williams','','Thursday and Friday from 10-5, Saturday from 9-5, Sunday from 1-5','','','','2832 NC Hwy 42 West ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27504','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:39','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('84794c1d-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Williamson House Sauce  ','We are proud to offer you our family sauce. We believe that flavors should enhance, not overpower, your food. Let our unique flavors create a memorable expereience for your family and friends. Enjoy! The Williamson Family ','919-380-0943 ','shaywilliamson@nc.rr.com ','Shay Williamson','','Web site 24/7 ','','www.WilliamsonHouseSauce.com ','','1381 Kildaire Farm Rd. #363 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27511','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:39','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('847b0914-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Yummy Minies ','Yummy Minies was created as a result of having them as a child at the NC State Fair every year and remembering the wonderful taste you experience when eating a dozen or two. In 2008 after discussing this adventure for many years with my wife Leanne we agreed to this business adventure. Since then we have been growing each year and have been invited to many rewarding events. Future plans are to franchise the business which will include mall kiosk, vending kiosk and concessions. We are taking things slow to ensure the longevity of a successful business. Visit one of our locations and if you arent 100% satisfied I will be glad to discuss how we can make it right.     OUR DONUTS Ingredients: enriched wheat flour (wheat flour, malted barley flour, niacin, reduced iron, thiamine mononitrate, riboflavin, folic acid), sugar, soybean oil, soy flour, nonfat dry milk, egg yolk solids, leavening (sodium acid pyrophosphate, sodium bicarbonate), dex- trose, salt, buttermilk solids, soy lecithin, natural flavors, sodium diacetate, vegetable color extracted from annatto and turmeric. **Contains: Wheat, Soy, Milk and Egg Ingredients. Process: Our donuts are made using the Lil Orbits machine. The donut mix is poured into the hopper and is plunged out into liquid shortning at a temperature of 375 degrees. Each donut is cooked on each side for approximately 10 seconds then goes on a ramp which flips the donut on the other side to complete its cooking process. Once the donut has been cooked on each side it is then dispensed out at the end. Donuts are coated using powder sugar or cinnamon sugar. If you desire we can top your donuts with a drizzle flavor. Pricing: 1 Dozen Plain.....$3 (Cinnamon Sugar or Powder Sugar) 1 Dozen Drizzle.....$4 (chocolate,strawberry,blueberry,blackberry,apple,cherry) ','919-906-8164 ','info@yummyminies.com ','Scott Strother','','We are open every weekend during Flea Market hours. ','','www.YummyMinies.com ','','','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27606 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:39','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('847caf3e-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Hawks Family Farm Angus Beef ','We are a family owned and operated farm, located in Warren County. We raise the cows right here on our farm, and when they are the proper age and weight to be processed, we transport them to Chaudhry Halal Meats in Siler City, NC, for slaughter, processing, and packaging. Everything is done according to strict USDA guidelines.      Our cows are raised in a natural outdoor environment. They graze our pasture grasses, and are also fed nutrient rich hay. Our cows also enjoy fresh, cool well-water from automatic waterers which have been installed in our pastures. A minimum of 100 days prior to slaughter, we supplement their diet with a high quality blended grain feed. This ensures the meat will be lean, but will have the marbling that enhances the flavor, tenderness, and texture of the beef.      After being slaughtered, the meat is dry aged for a minimum of 21 days in a temperature controlled cooler room. Next, the meat is cut to order, vacuum sealed and frozen. We transport the beef here to our freezer, and offer it for sale to you.      We opted to market our beef in this vacuum-packed and frozen state because we do not add preservatives. We also do not add any hormones, and we do not administer any antibiotics to any animal we intend to slaughter for meat. We are proud of the quality and taste of Hawks Family Farm beef, and we are confident that you will enjoy it!      We are blessed to live on a farm, and we are thankful for all that God provides for us from this rich soil. We appreciate your interest in our product. From 