er classes on various farm related subjects through out the year. From bee keeping, soap making, and animal care field to fork.     Our family stands ready to help you in anyway we can and share in the bounty of all North Carolina has for us. ','2522570516','hollandfarmnc@gmail.com ','Mike Holland','','Since we are a family farm, and have bee\'s on our property \"at large\" we request a call ahead before coming out, and we are open to by appointment visits most anytime. ','','www.hollandfarmnc.org ','','531 Lickskillet Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27589','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:39','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('8480fd05-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Collier Farm  ','Collier Farm is a 180 acre retired tobacco farm located in the serene southern part of historical Warren County where cotton was once king and old plantation homes still dot the countryside. This provides the perfect stage for our easy camping adventure.     We supply a camping hut, which is 12 feet X 20 feet, having 12 feet enclosed and 8 feet screened. No tent is needed. The camps are also supplied with a table and chairs, charcoal grill, wood for a campfire and convenient bath facilities. Enjoy the abundance of wildlife, nature trails, and a big bass pond; then fall asleep to the melody of the whippoorwills, and awaken to the gobble of an old Tom calling the roll.     We are located in the gentle hills and tall pines just 12 miles from the antique shops and historical architecture of Warrenton and 25 miles from Lake Gaston and Kerr Lake. This is a great place for the entire family to camp in privacy and become as one with nature. ','252-257-1812 ','','Bennie P. Collier','','','','','','664 Rabbit Bottom Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27589','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:39','a1c3e20e-f181-11e