06-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28605 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:39','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('8494d6ef-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Apple Hill Farm','Apple Hill Farm sits on top of Valle Mountain on the site of a 45-year-old apple orchard. The remaining apple trees serve as the focal point for the farm, which is now home to a menagerie of animals. Magnificent mountain views, wooded footpaths, and landscaped gardens are the visual backdrop for the barns and animals.      The mission of Apple Hill Farm is to educate people about animals and farming. A 1 1/2 hour guided walking tour starts at the Horse barn, winding around the farm to visit alpacas, donkeys, llamas, goats, chickens, vegetable garden, and horses. Tour guides give information about the animals, their stories and their purpose to the farm. The terrain is hilly. Wear comfortable walking shoes and don\'t forget to bring a camera.      The Apple Hill Farm Store (upstairs in the barn) features clothing made from alpaca fiber, arts and crafts from local artisans and a unique selection of gift items. We also have eggs, garden produce in season and honey. ',' 828 963-1662 ','applehillalpaca@aol.com ','Lee Rankin','','Public tours Saturdays at 2pm, Mid-May through Mid-October. Adults $10, Age 10 and under $5, Under 3 are free, (Reservations are requested) Private tours available for groups and individuals year round, please call for rates, 828-963- 1662.','','www.applehillfarmnc.com ','','400 Apple Hill Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28604 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:39','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('84967fb8-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Blue Ridge Bones, LLC ','Organic & All Natural Dog Treats made with ingredients from here in the high country. Fresh eggs, honey, goat\'s milk,blueberries are gathered from local small farms and organic flours from the midwest. All ingredients are human grade and tested by independant labs. All treats are made by loving hearts and hands.     Originally created in Sarah\'s kitchen for her Border Collie, Belle, our Cream & Honey treat was so well received by family & friends that the kitchen was soon replaced by a bakery in her basement. Our clients soon requested products with no wheat, no bha, etc..      Three years later, a full bakery located on FunEFarm in Grassy Creek, NC bakes up fresh Quinoa & Blueberry, Flax & Honey, Banana Peanut Butter, and our flagship product Cream & Honey. Shipped fresh daily. ',' 866-512-6637 ','tina@blueridgebones.com ','Sarah Ernst','','','','blueridgebones.com ','','PO Box 3457 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28607 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:39','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('849836a8-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Cornett Deal Christmas Tree Farm & Songbird Cabin ','The Cornett Deal Christmas Tree farm was established in 1986 in Mountain Dale Community in the western part of Watauga County (18 miles west of Boone, NC). In 2000 I added a two bedroom cabin to the farm as a way of sharing my 26 acres with my customers and friends throughout the year.      The farm is open for Choose & Cut on weekends beginning the weekend prior to Thanksgiving each year. After enjoying a hayride around the farm and choosing that perfect tree, you are invited into the shop for a cup of hot cider and cookies. Our shop now offers several locally made crafts including pottery items by Diane, jewelry by Amantha, and knitted items by Diane, Melissa, & Maggie. In 2007 we also plan to feature other local crafters and have the gift shop open each Saturday throughout the year.      After visiting the gift shop and enjoying some refreshments, you can venture outside to watch your tree be prepared for loading. We offer a tree shaker to help remove loose needles from the trees. We also have a drill machine for pre-drilling your tree for the stands we now offer at the Cornett Deal Tree Farm. And everyone enjoys watching the tree being baled for the trip home. Merry Christmas and Happy New Year to everyone..... ','828-297-1136 ','cdtreefarm@skybest.com ','Diane Cornett Deal','','Cornett Deal Christmas Tree Farm is open for Choose & Cut beginning the Saturday prior to Thanksgiving and is open each weekend through and including the 3rd weekend of December, 9:00 am -5:00 pm on Saturdays and 10 am - 5 pm on Sundays. ','','www.songbirdcabin.com ','','142 Tannenbaum Lane ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28692 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:39','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('849a08f0-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Crippen\'s Country Inn & Restaurant  ','We are a casual atmosphere, fine dining restaurant with a daily changing menu featuring a variety of homemade breads and soups, homegrown organic salads, creative appetizers, pasta, fresh fish, meats and game meats, homemade desserts and ice creams.      Nine spacious, luxurious guest rooms with king beds and sofa sitting areas, continental breakfast. Located in the center of downtown Blowing Rock, walking distance to Main St.      In 1995 Chef James Welch and Jimmy Crippen opened Crippen\'s Country Inn and Restaurant in Blowing Rock, North Carolina. The restaurant was instantly awarded five stars for food by Greensboro News and Record\'s food critic, John Batchelor, titling James\' cuisine \"Best Food in North Carolina\". In 1996 James was invited to the coveted James Beard House in New York City as a part of the Great Country Inns Chef\'s Series sponsored by Country Inns Bed and Breakfast Magazine. Throughout the twelve year career, Chef James and Crippen\'s Country Inn and Restaurant have been featured in numerous magazines and newspapers spanning the entire Southeastern United States such as, Southern Living, The New York Times, Our State, Blue Ridge Country, Country Living, Gold Coast, US Air Magazine and more. The Food Network featured Chef James\' Coca Cola Marinated & Grilled Kangaroo on their show \"The Secret Life','877-295-3487 ','crippenscountryinn@crippens.com','Jimmy Crippen','','June - October open 7 days a week serving dinner starting at 6pm, November - May open Thurs-Sat serving dinner staring at 6pm.','','www.crippens.com ','','239 Sunset Dr. ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28605 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:39','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('849b8456-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Fire From the Mountain, Inc.  ','Fire From The Mountain was incorporated in January of 2005. We own a small farm in the North Carolina mountains where we grow our hot peppers and other ingredients for our hot sauces and salsa. When not available, we purchase from other farmers. Our peppers are smoked over apple wood which gives the intense unique flavor. We make our products in small batches to ensure proper quality.      We are members of Goodness Grows in North Carolina. Goodness Grows in North Carolina is a marketing program through the NC Department of Agriculture for growing, processing and manufacturing products that are made in North Carolina.     We currently produce and pack our products at a non-profit FDA approved shared use kitchen called Blue Ridge Food Ventures located in Asheville, NC. ','828-297-7956 ','hotsauce@firefromthemountain.com','Peter Jankowski','','','','www.firefromthemountain.com ','','2452 NC HWY 88 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28698 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:39','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('849d371d-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Longview Farm  ','Longview Farm is at a high elevation, around 4200 feet, and has almost a 360-degree view of Grandfather Mountain and Beech and Sugar Mountain Ski Resorts from atop Howards Creek Road. We offer hayrides, hot chocolate and other amenities that make a trip to the High Country a yearly family tradition. Our family farm is a rare example of a successful mountain farm that hasn\'t and hopefully will never be developed. We think our farm is unique in that we have had 6 generations now working on the farm with the full intentions of many more generations keeping the farm productive. Letting people know that our farm is enrolled in Farmland Preservation also shows our commitment to the land and keeping it in agriculture. Farming is very important to us because it is our way of life and how we choose to raise our children. By promoting the importance of family farms, and taking that message to our customers and other people visiting the area, we will help more people understand the importance for preserving farms and appreciating all they offer. We would be happy to share with others our lessons learned and show how wea€?ve made things work on our family farm. Since the whole family works on the farm, and we are one of the largest family farms left in the area, we thought that would also appeal to people who didn\'t know much about farming. We want to tell our familya€?s farming history so people will realize what a special farm they are visiting.      Throughout the years, our family has worked together in all our farming projects. We grew tobacco, cabbage and potatoes for many years and recently began dealing with cattle and Christmas trees. From growing our own garden to harvesting trees, we all take a part in helping and what money is made just helps to keep it all going. We feel that time spent together as a family farming cannot be replaced. Danny says, \"Tree farming reminds me of something my mother and grandparents would say about tobacco farming. It is a 13 month a year job because it seems like there is always something to do on a tree farm.\" ','828-297-4202 ','longviewfarm@skybest.com','Danny Miller','','November 19-21 and November 26-28 December 3-5 and December 10-12 Friday & Saturday: 10am-6pm Sunday: 1pm-6pm ','','www.longviewfarm.info ','','6167 Howards Creek Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28607 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:39','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('849e99dc-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','New River Corn Maze','Located on the historic Brown Family Farm located beside the scenic New River. Enjoy beautiful scenery, picnics by the New River, Hayrides throughout the farm and get lost in the Maze. Come back and see us to pick your perfect Christmas tree. ','828-406-6305 ','tuckertrees@gmail.com ','David tucker','','Friday-Saturday 10:00 AM till Dark Sunday 1:00 PM till Dark ','','www.newrivercornmaze.com ','','660 Laurel Gap Ridge ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28607 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:39','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('849f6596-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','River and Earth Adventures, Inc','','828-963-5491 ','laura@raftcavehike.com ','Laura Mallard','','call ahead...we may be on the river!','','raftcavehike.com ','','581 Dewitt Barnett Rd ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28692 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:39','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('84a0f5f3-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7