nd miss engines for the last few years.  About four years ago I rebuilt a John Deere hit and miss engine and then needed to find some work for it. I found that an Amish man was building the 20 quart Country Freezer. They do no use electricity and therefore no internet. I volunteered to help out selling the units on the internet.     It has been a great experience!     You may send email me any time about ice cream.','336-984-2885 ','tmgraves@wilkes.net ','Tom Graves','','','','www.7springsranch.com ','','765 Hunting creek Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28659','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:40','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('84df2ba7-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Smoot Park Farmer\'s Market  ','The market will be opening on July 3 in 2004 and fresh grown produce will be sold on Saturday mornings from 7:30 am until noon. Produce will also be sold on Tuesday afternoons from 3:30 pm until 5:30 pm.     All produce offered at the market is locally grown. Starting in July, fresh tomatoes, beans, corn, nectarines, and other fruits and vegetables will be offered at the market. ','336 696 2020 ','','Roger Owens','','Saturday 7:30 am til noon Tuesday 3:30 pm til 5:30 pm ','','','','199 Chestnut Street ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28659','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:40','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('84e0bf25-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Tumbling Shoals Farm ','Nestled in the bucolic valley where Tumbling Shoals Creek meanders beneath the shadow of Bullhead Mountain in beautiful Wilkes County, Tumbling Shoals Farm is owned and operated by Shiloh Avery and Jason Roehrig. The farm is transitional organic which means that we grow everything according to the USDA organic standards and will be certified organic in 2010.     We have been farming since returning from Peace Corps service as agriculture volunteers in Madagascar in 2002. We began as partners at Gardens of Paradise in Pittsboro, NC, while Shiloh took sustainable agriculture courses at Central Carolina Community College and Jason began working with conventional farmers in his job at RAFI-USA. In 2003, Melvin Whitfield invited us to farm an idle piece of land beside the horse pasture and the pond at his third generation farm in White Cross, NC.      Eventually though, we got tired of commuting to the farm and began looking for a place of our own to put down roots (quite literally in the form of perennial crops). It took three years of rollercoaster searching to find the absolute perfect spot here in Millers Creek, but here we are! 2009 marks our second year of production here, with one more to go until our three year organic land transition is up and we\'ll be certified! ','336-452-2920 ','shiloh@blast.com ','Shiloh Avery','','Tuesdays, May-October, from 5p.m.-7p.m for CSA pick up or veggie purchases, All other times by appointment. ','','www.tumblingshoalsfarm.com ','','841 Sand Ridge Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28651','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:40','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('84e25e64-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Whippoorwill Academy and Village ','Whippoorwill Academy and Village is a delightful place to visit and tour the past as you walk through this small village of yesteryear. Owner and operator, Mrs. Edith Ferguson Carter started this village by moving historical buildings to the family farm many years ago. As an artist, Mrs. Carter has made several videos using art work to tell the stories of \"NC Legends.\" The \"Legend of Tom Dooley\" is the most popular one. She is happy to share those with groups and give them a tour of the buildings. A favorite is the local jail and chapel. This quaint chapel called \"The Chapel of Peace,\" has been the setting for many lovely weddings over the years.      Many generations have been very active in working this family farm. Presently, there are cattle, four llamas and two farm dogs.      Daniel Boone Day held the second Saturday in May, is a small, but fun filled day for the family to enjoy music, arts and craftsman, food, hayrides, cloggers and a self guided tours, Tom Dooley Dramatic Skit by the Wilkes Playmakers and the \"Strong Southern Woman Skillet Toss\" contest. In December, a Christmas Open House is held. No admission fee is charged for tours, but donations for the upkeep of the village are appreciated. There is a small fee for weddings at the chapel. This is a perfect place to bring a group for a tour, picnic, wedding or a leisurely time of learning about our heritage. Mountains views are spectacular! ','(336) 973-3237 ','whippoorwillvillage@hotmail.com','Edith Ferguson Carter','','The village is open to the public on Saturday and Sunday, 3-5 pm and during the week by appointment, The Village is closed January through March, Call (336) 973-3237 for an appointment. ','','www.wilkesnc.org/history/whippoorwill ','','P.O. Box 458 ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28624 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:40','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('84e400d5-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Wiggle Hill Farm ','We are a small hobby farm located in the foothills of NC. We raise JSBA registered Jacob sheep, selecting for strong horns and excellent fleeces. Jacob sheep are an ancient, primitive breed of sheep. Males and females have horns, usually 2 or 4, but sometimes 5 or 6. They are white with black or gray (called lilac) spots. They are very hardy with friendly and outgoing personalities. Their fleeces are prized by handspinners and crafters. They are smaller than the average commercial breeds, and usually give birth with few complications in the spring. Twins are common, triplets are rare.      We also raise medium and heavy wooled llamas. We value interesting colors, nice fleeces, and even temperaments in our llamas. ','336-902-8655 ','RoyalDVM@aol.com ','Lillian Royal','','Please call to schedule a visitation. ','','http://www.wigglehillfarm.com ','','489 Huie Rd ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28635 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:40','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('84e5aa85-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Yadkin Valley Construction, Inc.','Yadkin Valley Construction, Inc. is a family owned and operated company. My father and I do 90% of our work ourselves, hiring part time help only when necessary. We take pride in our work and believe that you will too. We are members of the NCBBB and have our NC contractors license.     We specialize in agricultural grading and farm fencing. We have plenty of experience with cost share plans and can take care of your fencing, cattle drinkers, stock trails, etc. We have also built/repaired several farm ponds. We have equipment to clean and close out waste storage ponds. Also, we can replace your old, rotten fence with new fence without animal removal. Let us design/build your new catching/working facility.      Our grading experience includes agricultural, residential, commercial and environmental projects. We can take care of almost any grading or fencing need you may have. We are also a member of the NCBBB and have our NC contractors license. References are available upon request. ','336 244 5762 ','bradyvc@netzero.com ','Brad Benton','','Monday thru Friday 7:00am - 6:00pm.','','','','2961 Old 60 Hwy. ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','28670 ','','','','2012-02