ll on North Deep Creek and contains the ruins of a gristmill, circa 1895.     Come and visit....watch the seasons change....listen to the rush of the water over the rocks! This is a primitive, historic site: \"take only pictures, leave only footprints, keep only memories\". ','','mutter@triad.rr.com ','Marti Spillman Utter','','Sunrise \'til sunset, year-round. ','','www.ShacktownNC.com ','','Styers Mill Road ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27055 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:40','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('85221c5c-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Swan Creek Farm','Catherine Browne, L.Ac., MH, Dipl.Ac., an acupuncturist, and herbalist of 24 years, developed Ageless Herbs product line to meet the needs of her patients. Patients had such great results with the formulas that Catherine began selling them through her website, and the herbs are now shipped throughout the US and to 18 foreign countries. \"I am determined that my patients and customers are taking Chinese herb formulas that are effective and safe. I know that Ageless Herbs Formulas work because I have seen their great benefits in clinic for patients!\"     We are growing Chinese medicinal herbs at our farm in rural North Carolina to help insure the purity and quality of our Ageless Herbs product line. We are located along the scenic North Carolina wine trail. We hope to develop an agritourism spot in the next few years. ','336-464-2958 ','info@agelessherbs.com ','Catherine Browne','','We sell on the internet only.','','www.swancreekfarm.com ','','1736 Swan Creek Farm ','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27020 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:40','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('8523bcc3-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Two T\'s Goat Farm','Our goal is to produce quality Savanna goats, not just quantity. A small family farm allows us time to nurture the animals as they grow and mature. We strive to improve the genetics of our goats and produce the highest quality Savanna goat in North Carolina. Our closed farm promotes improved health and safety for our animals.     A small operation such as ours must produce the best quality breed stock possible, which is why we selected the Savanna goat as our primary stock. In order for a small farm to be profitable, we needed a breed that consistently produces. We are always looking for ways to reduce manual labor and costs. Having Savanna goats reduces the cost per animal, improving the bottom line of a farma€?s operations. The Savannaa€?s breeding characteristics contribute to its great reputation. Originating in the adverse conditions of South Africa, the Savanna goat is a€?tougha€? and disease resistant, hardy, and heat tolerant. Savanna does are known for being fertile and natural mothers, producing heartier and larger kids which grow remarkably fast. These traits plus the adaptability of the Savanna goat, which eats most of our local vegetation, makes it a low-maintenance small farm animal. The well-bred Savanna goat survived in unfavorable weather conditions in South Africa. We believe it will do wonderfully in the NC foothills. ','336-306-5959 ','2t@savannagoat.com ','Tim Swain','','Very flexiable.','','www.savannagoat.com ','','','7f7a92b8-ea4c-11e0-8606-00306701b527','ed336e0f-f48c-11e0-b192-00306701b527','','27020 ','','','','2012-02-29 15:17:40','a1c3e20e-f181-11e0-8a53-00306701b527',1),('85252d8a-62e8-11e1-b30d-101f74b66417','ff2b0b4d-203c-11e1-8a87-000c29a5c50c','','06a017ae-28cb-11e1-abb7-000c29a5c50c','Bzzz Mountain Honey Farm','We are local beekeepers who maintain 100+ hives in Yancey and surrounding counties of western North Carolina.     Our honey is considered \"raw\" honey. We carry all hive products in their natural form. ','(828) 208-543